g back to our communities. Because doing so can fuel the very innovation we are pursuing.\n\n**Overview**  \nThe Principal Business Analyst in the Smart Manufacturing & AI (SMAI) organization drives Industry 4.0, digital transformation, and sophisticated analytics initiatives for Front‑End (FE) operations and planning. This role partners closely with FE operations, planning, engineering, supply chain, and global collaborators to deliver scalable solutions that improve wafer output, cycle time, prioritisation, and network‑level decision making.\n\n**Key Responsibilities**\n\n* Collaborate with the management of FE operations, planning groups, and engineering teams to identify improvement opportunities across cycle time, output, bottleneck management, and fab efficiency.\n* Define and deliver FE digital solutions including digital twin models, optimization engines, simulation workflows, and decision‑support tools.\n* Integrate FE digital capabilities with supply chain systems to support short‑term tactical wafer starts, strategic wafer starts, long‑range planning, network supply allocation, and cost/space optimization.\n* Lead requirement definition for FE planning solutions such as localized and global resource planning, constraint analysis, and scenario simulation.\n* Partner with Data Scientists, Data Engineers, and architects to deliver analytics, modeling, automation, and machine learning solutions.\n* Engage external vendors providing commercial optimization, simulation, industrial analytics, and decision‑support applications; confirm consistency with FE and planning needs.\n* Influence cross‑site alignment with FE COEs, factory operations, and supply chain partners to ensure consistent adoption and business impact.\n* Use data and critical metrics to assess performance, quantify benefits, and guide operational and strategic decision‑making.\n\n**Qualifications**\n\nMaster’s degree or\n\n* 5 years’ experience in Front‑End semiconductor manufacturing, operations planning, or industrial engineering.\n* Strong domain knowledge in FE areas such as Lithography, Etch, CVD/PVD, Diffusion, CMP, Implant, Metrology, RDA, or PI.\n* Experience with digital transformation, planning systems, optimization, simulation, or industrial analytics.\n* Proven track record to lead cross‑functional projects delivering measurable improvements in output, cycle time, or capacity efficiency.\n* Strong communication, stakeholder engagement, and influence skills across global teams and leadership levels.\n* Highly organized and adaptable with the ability to manage multiple priorities.\n\n**About Micron Technology, Inc.**\n\nWe are an industry leader in innovative memory and storage solutions transforming how the world uses information to enrich life *for all*. With a relentless focus on our customers, technology leadership, and manufacturing and operational excellence, Micron delivers a rich portfolio of high-performance DRAM, NAND, and NOR memory and storage products through our Micron® and Crucial® brands. Every day, the innovations that our people create fuel the data economy, enabling advances in artificial intelligence and 5G applications that unleash opportunities — from the data center to the intelligent edge and across the client and mobile user experience.  \n  \nTo learn more, please visit micron.com/careers  \n  \nAll qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, veteran or disability status.  \n  \nTo request assistance with the application process and/or for reasonable accommodations, please contact hrsupport\\_sg@micron.com\n\nMicron Prohibits the use of child labor and complies with all applicable laws, rules, regulations, and other international and industry labor standards.\n\nMicron does not charge candidates any recruitment fees or unlawfully collect any other payment from candidates as consideration for their employment with Micron.\n\nAI alert: Candidates are encouraged to use AI tools to enhance their resume and/or application materials. However, all information provided must be accurate and reflect the candidate''s true skills and experiences. Misuse of AI to fabricate or misrepresent qualifications will result in immediate disqualification.\n\nFraud alert: Micron advises job seekers to be cautious of unsolicited job offers and to verify the authenticity of any communication claiming to be from Micron by checking the official Micron careers website in the About Micron Technology, Inc.", "requirements": "Collaborate with FE operations, planning groups, and engineering teams to identify improvement opportunities. Lead cross-functional projects delivering measurable improvements in output, cycle time, or capacity efficiency. Partner with Data Scientists, Data Engineers, and architects to deliver analytics, modeling, automation, and machine learning solutions.", "source": "Indeed", "source_warning": "部分数据源抓取失败：linkedin: 抓取超时，已跳过", "search_keyword": "Data Analyst", "relevance_score": 32, "relevance_reasons": ["标题部分命中: 大数据分析 / data analyst / big data analyst / data science / business intelligence analyst / data insights specialist", "描述命中: data", "标题命中: analyst", "描述命中: analyst", "标题命中: business", "描述命中: business", "描述命中: intelligence"], "market_country": "新加坡", "skill_evidence": [{"name": "Digital Twin Models", "evidence": "Define and deliver FE digital solutions including digital twin models, optimization engines, simulation workflows, an..."}, {"name": "Optimization Engines", "evidence": "Define and deliver FE digital solutions including digital twin models, optimization engines, simulation workflows, an..."}, {"name": "Simulation Workflows", "evidence": "Define and deliver FE digital solutions including digital twin models, optimization engines, simulation workflows, an..."}, {"name": "Decision-support Tools", "evidence": "Define and deliver FE digital solutions including digital twin models, optimization engines, simulation workflows, an..."}, {"name": "Planning Systems", "evidence": "Lead requirement definition for FE planning solutions such as localized and global resource planning, constraint anal..."}, {"name": "Optimization", "evidence": "Engage external vendors providing commercial optimization, simulation, industrial analytics, and decision-support app..."}, {"name": "Simulation", "evidence": "Engage external vendors providing commercial optimization, simulation, industrial analytics, and decision-support app..."}, {"name": "Industrial Analytics", "evidence": "Engage external vendors providing commercial optimization, simulation, industrial analytics, and decision-support app..."}], "skills": ["Digital Twin Models", "Optimization Engines", "Simulation Workflows", "Decision-support Tools", "Planning Systems", "Optimization", "Simulation", "Industrial Analytics"]}, {"title": "DevOps (ShipHats) Engineer / Senior Associate, Data & AI, Technology Consulting", "company": "EY", "salary": "面议", "location": "Raffles Quay", "experience": "不限", "education": "不限", "description": "**Job Description: DevOps (ShipHats) Engineer, Senior Associate, AI Data, Technology Consulting**\n\nAt EY, we develop you with future-focused skills and equip you with world-class experiences. We empower you in a flexible environment, and fuel you and your extraordinary talents in a diverse and inclusive culture of globally connected teams.\n\nWe work together across our full spectrum of services and skills powered by technology and AI, so that business, people and the planet can thrive together.\n\nWe’re all in, are you?\n\nJoin EY and shape your future with confidence.\n\n**About the opportunity**\n\nEY AI & Data is the data and advanced analytics capability within EY Asia-Pacific, with over 500 specialist employees working across multiple industry sectors. We implement information-driven strategies, data platforms and advanced data analytics solution systems that help grow, optimize and protect client organizations. We go beyond strategy and provide end to end design, build and implementation of real-life data environments and have some of the best architects, project managers, business analysts, data scientists, big data engineers, developers and consultants in the region.\n\nWe are seeking a DevOps Engineer (Senior Associate) with proven experience delivering Government Commercial Cloud (GCC) projects for Singapore government agencies and ministries. The ideal candidate will have hands-on expertise in implementing SHIP-HATS frameworks and designing/maintaining robust CI/CD pipelines across multiple projects.\n\n**Your key responsibilities:**\n\n* Design, implement, and maintain CI/CD pipelines to support efficient and secure application deployment in GCC environments.\n* Lead or contribute to end-to-end DevOps projects for Singapore government agencies or ministries.\n* Implement and enhance solutions aligned with SHIP-HATS compliance standards.\n* Collaborate with application teams, architects, and security specialists to ensure smooth delivery and operation of cloud-native and container-based applications.\n* Perform troubleshooting, monitoring, and performance tuning of DevOps toolchains and infrastructure.\n* Document solutions, create deployment guides, and support knowledge transfer to client or internal teams.\n\n**Skills & attributes for success:**\n\n* 3–5 years of experience in DevOps, with senior-level contributions in at least 1–2 GCC projects involving Singapore government agencies.\n* Strong experience in implementing and optimizing CI/CD pipelines (e.g., Jenkins, GitLab CI, Azure DevOps).\n* Practical experience with SHIP-HATS framework implementation.\n* Proficient with tools such as Docker, Kubernetes, Terraform, Ansible (or similar).\n* Familiarity with security best practices in government cloud environments.\n* Strong communication skills for stakeholder engagement and technical documentation.\n* Familiarity with agile delivery frameworks, including Scrum or equivalent.\n* Certified in AWS and/or Talend.\n\n**What we look for**\n\nHighly motivated individuals with excellent problem-solving skills and the ability to prioritize shifting workloads in a rapidly changing industry. An effective communicator, you’ll be a confident team player that collaborates with people from various teams while looking to develop your career in a dynamic organization.\n\n**What working at EY offers**\n\nEY offers a competitive remuneration package where you’ll be rewarded for your individual and team performance. We are committed to being an inclusive employer and are happy to consider flexible working arrangements. Plus, we offer:\n\n  \n\n* Continuous learning: You’ll develop the mindset and skills to navigate whatever comes next.\n* Success as defined by you: We’ll provide the tools and flexibility, so you can make a meaningful impact, your way.\n* Transformative leadership: We’ll give you the insights, coaching and confidence to be the leader the world needs.\n* Diverse and inclusive culture: You’ll be embraced for who you are and empowered to use your voice to help others find theirs.\n\n**Company description**\n\nEY is building a better working world by creating new value for clients, people, society and the planet, while building trust in capital markets.\n\nEnabled by data, AI and advanced technology, EY teams help clients shape the future with confidence and develop answers for the most pressing issues of today and tomorrow.\n\nEY teams work across a full spectrum of services in assurance, consulting, tax, strategy and transactions. Fueled by sector insights, a globally connected, multi-disciplinary network and diverse ecosystem partners, EY teams can provide services in more than 150 countries and territories.\n\nAll in to shape the future with confidence.", "requirements": "Proven experience delivering Government Commercial Cloud (GCC) projects for Singapore government agencies and ministries. Hands-on expertise in implementing SHIP-HATS frameworks and designing/maintaining CI/CD pipelines. Proficient with tools such as Docker, Kubernetes, Terraform, Ansible, and certified in AWS and/or Talend.", "source": "Indeed", "source_warning": "部分数据源抓取失败：linkedin: 抓取超时，已跳过", "search_keyword": "Big Data Analyst", "relevance_score": 30, "relevance_reasons": ["标题部分命中: 大数据分析 / data analyst / big data analyst / data science / business intelligence analyst / data insights specialist", "标题命中: data", "描述命中: data", "描述命中: analyst", "描述命中: big", "描述命中: business", "描述命中: insights", "描述命中: specialist"], "market_country": "新加坡", "skill_evidence": [{"name": "CI/CD pipelines", "evidence": "Design, implement, and maintain CI/CD pipelines to support efficient and secure application deployment in GCC environ..."}, {"name": "SHIP-HATS Frameworks", "evidence": "The ideal candidate will have hands-on expertise in implementing SHIP-HATS frameworks and designing/maintaining robus..."}, {"name": "Docker", "evidence": "Proficient with tools such as Docker, Kubernetes, Terraform, Ansible (or similar)."}, {"name": "Kubernetes", "evidence": "Proficient with tools such as Docker, Kubernetes, Terraform, Ansible (or similar)."}, {"name": "Terraform", "evidence": "Proficient with tools such as Docker, Kubernetes, Terraform, Ansible (or similar)."}, {"name": "Ansible", "evidence": "Proficient with tools such as Docker, Kubernetes, Terraform, Ansible (or similar)."}, {"name": "AWS", "evidence": "Certified in AWS and/or Talend."}, {"name": "Talend", "evidence": "Certified in AWS and/or Talend."}], "skills": ["CI/CD pipelines", "SHIP-HATS Frameworks", "Docker", "Kubernetes", "Terraform", "Ansible", "AWS", "Talend"]}, {"title": "Retail Commercial Analyst Intern", "company": "Coty", "salary": "面议", "location": "Orchard", "experience": "不限", "education": "不限", "description": "Req ID\n\n97820\n\nPosted\n\nMar 20, 2026\n\nFunction\n\nSales\n\nLocation\n\nSingapore, 01, SG, 238164\n\nApply »\n\nReq ID: 97820\n\nFunction: Sales\n\nPosted: Mar 20, 2026\n\nLocation:\nSingapore, 01, SG, 238164\n\n**Retail Commercial Analyst Intern**\n====================================\n\nCountry/Region: SG\n\nCity: Singapore\n\nCoty is a world leader in beauty and home to an illustrious roster of cosmetic, skincare and fragrance brands. And our company has a mission: to challenge the definition of beauty, to encourage authenticity and celebrate diversity. Because to us at Coty, beauty isn’t about conforming to somebody else’s ideal. It’s about inclusion and liberating everyone to shine in their unique way.\n\n  \n\nCoty helps millions of people around the world express your beauty, your way through our rich portfolio covering fragrance, skin care, colour cosmetics, and body care. Our brands include global icons like Gucci, Burberry, Hugo Boss, Calvin Klein, Philosophy, Max Factor, Rimmel, Bourjois, Sally Hansen, Adidas, David Beckham, etc. With more than one billion products shipped each year, the possibilities for self-expression are endless.\n\n  \n\n**THE ROLE**\n\n**Division: SG Luxury Division**\n\n**Job Title: Retail Commercial intern**\n\n**Reporting to: Commercial Manager (SG LUX)**\n\n  \n\n**About the Role**\n\n  \n\nThis role sits within the Commercial team, and provide supports the for team in achieving Nett Revenue and Sellout targets by ensuring seamless operations both at sales floor, and at Coty backend. This role will require the candidate to be skilled in Microsoft excel / powerpoint applications\n\n  \n\n**KEY RESPONSIBILITIES**\n\n* Maintain daily sales data\n* Improve data analytics and data reporting processes\n* Creation and submission of new sell in forms\n* Following up on delivery fulfilment, errors on ordering codes\n* Maintain a clean set of data with retailers, updating them on price changes/ code changes,\n* Upkeep Coty’s brand and product page on retail partner’s site\n* Work with retail partner to launch newness on-site and in store on time\n* Ensure all newness, GWPs & testers are delivered on time to our retail partners\n* Maintain brand planogram with retail partner\n\n  \n\n**WHAT YOU’LL BRING**\n\n***ESSENTIAL:***\n\n* Undergraduates who can commit **for at least 6 months** (Jul2026-Dec2026) for a **full-time internship.**\n\n* Skilled in the use of MS Office tools including Outlook, Excel (Pivot Tables, VLookUp) Word and PowerPoint.\n* Data savvy with the confidence to pull insights from large datasets.\n* Self-motivated and self-starter, with a strong work ethic and a sense of confidentiality.\n* Possesses cross-cultural awareness and high emotional intelligence.\n* Articulate, with the ability to work in a fast-paced environment.\n* Strong interest in consumer goods, makeup and beauty products.\n* Strong desire to learn along with a strong sense of ownership.\n* Persuasive, resilient and flexible, able to easily adapt to new challenges.\n* Passionate, enthusiastic and driven with strong follow-up skills.\n* Able to thrive despite challenges while adopting a positive attitude under pressure.\n\n  \n\n**LEARNING OUTCOMES**\n\n* Exposure to various aspects of luxury beauty landscape\n\n* Gain hands-on experience in commercial and retail operations\n\n* Develop skills in business strategy\n\nOur people make us who we are. They are the brightest minds bringing the boldest ideas to life every day. If you’re the kind of person who refuses to settle, if you want to think bigger, learn faster and go further than you ever thought possible – we’d love to hear from you.\n\n  \n\nInterested applicants may also send an email directly to LiFang\\_Tng@cotyinc.com.", "requirements": "Candidate must be an undergraduate student capable of committing to a full-time internship for at least 6 months. Must be skilled in using MS Office tools such as Excel and PowerPoint, and have a strong ability in data analytics and reporting.", "source": "Indeed", "source_warning": "部分数据源抓取失败：linkedin: 抓取超时，已跳过", "search_k