posal materials tailored to client needs in trade finance and related areas.\n* Support front-line sales teams with market data, analysis, and customized solution inputs.\n* Ensure proposal materials are prepared in line with SMBC’s risk appetite and product capabilities.\n* Participate in client meetings as required to support presentations and capture feedback.\n\n  \n\nCross-functional Collaboration\n\n* Work with coverage teams and product specialists to support strategic and operational alignment.\n* Assist in facilitating communication between strategic planning and client-facing teams.\n* Support the execution of initiatives such as Trade Working Capital Solutions sales activities and country-specific promotions.\n\n  \n\nJob Requirements\n\n* Bachelor’s degree in Finance, Business, Economics, or a related field.\n* 3–5 years of relevant experience in trade finance, corporate banking, investment banking, research/consulting firms, or related areas.\n* Basic to solid understanding of trade finance products, market trends, customer financials, and regulatory requirements in the APAC region.\n* Strong analytical, coordination, and communication skills, with the ability to work effectively across departments and regions.\n* Business fluency in English is essential, as this role requires written and verbal communication with the Tokyo office.\n* Detail-oriented with strong analytical and problem-solving abilities.\n* Ability to manage multiple tasks in a fast-paced, dynamic environment.\n* Willingness to learn and contribute to cross-functional projects.\n* Strong commitment to delivering high-quality client service and supporting internal business functions.\n* Ability to support trade finance deal origination activities in collaboration with senior team members and marketing managers.\n* Flexibility to perform other ad hoc duties as assigned.", "requirements": "候选人需具备3–5年的贸易金融、公司银行、投资银行、研究/咨询公司或相关领域的经验，并持有金融、商业、经济学或相关专业的学士学位。同时，需能够支持贸易金融交易发起活动，并具备跨部门协作能力。", "source": "Indeed", "source_warning": "部分数据源抓取失败：linkedin: 抓取超时，已跳过", "search_keyword": "Data Analyst", "relevance_score": 29, "relevance_reasons": ["标题部分命中: 大数据分析 / data analyst / big data analyst / data science / business intelligence analyst / data insights specialist", "描述命中: data", "标题命中: analyst", "标题命中: business", "描述命中: business", "描述命中: specialist"], "market_country": "新加坡", "skills": [], "skill_evidence": []}, {"title": "Data Science Intern, Media Equipment Engineering", "company": "Seagate Technology", "salary": "面议", "location": "S00", "experience": "不限", "education": "本科及以上", "description": "**About our group:**\n--------------------\n\nThe Recording Media Operation Media Equipment Engineering team are a team of professional Engineers working on developing various customized media processing equipment used in high volume media manufacturing. Our mission is to works on equipment enhancements to meet new processes needs, continuous improvements to improve product quality, yield and develop new technologies. We have embraced I4.0 technology and the team is continuously working on problem solving on manufacturing equipment and process\n\n**About the role - you will:**\n------------------------------\n\nAs an intern, you will actively contribute to key projects focused on data science and analytics. Your work will involve enhancing media processing tools by leveraging I4.0 technologies.\n\n* Work on projects related to Data Science / Data Analytics\n\n* Work on data logging, extraction, and setup, applying analytics to drive data-driven decision-making.\n* Develop interactive dashboards using tools and platforms such as Python and MySQL.\n* Develop AI Models and Deploy\n\n* Use Python libraries (Numpy, Pandas, Matplotlib) for data aggregation, analysis, and visualization.\n* Support in installing and configuring smart sensors to optimize media processing systems\n\n**About you:**\n--------------\n\nWe are looking for a motivated individual with:\n\n* A strong interest in data science and the ability to derive insights from complex datasets.\n* Familiarity with sensors and basic understanding of their role in manufacturing processes.\n* Able to commit full internship (May/Aug to Dec)\n\n**Your experience includes:**\n-----------------------------\n\n* Currently pursuing a Bachelor Degree in Data Science / Engineering, Computer Science or a related field.\n* Experience developing data-driven projects using Python.\n* Proficiency in Python programming, particularly with libraries such as Numpy, Pandas, Matplot, pyHive & Scipy library.\n* Experience in doing software integration and Deployment.\n* Knowledge of R programming & computer hardware is a plus.\n\n**Location:**\n-------------\n\nThe Recording Media Operation Media Equipment Engineering team are a team of professional Engineers working on developing various customized media processing equipment used in high volume media manufacturing. Our mission is to works on equipment enhancements to meet new processes needs, continuous improvements to improve product quality, yield and develop new technologies. We have embraced I4.0 technology and the team is continuously working on problem solving on manufacturing equipment and process\n\n**Location**: Woodlands, Singapore, W2  \n**Travel**: None", "requirements": "A strong interest in data science and the ability to derive insights from complex datasets. Familiarity with sensors and basic understanding of their role in manufacturing processes. Able to commit full internship (May/Aug to Dec)", "source": "Indeed", "source_warning": "部分数据源抓取失败：linkedin: 抓取超时，已跳过", "search_keyword": "Data Science", "relevance_score": 29, "relevance_reasons": ["标题部分命中: 大数据分析 / data analyst / big data analyst / data science / business intelligence analyst / data insights specialist", "标题命中: data", "描述命中: data", "标题命中: science", "描述命中: science", "描述命中: insights"], "market_country": "新加坡", "skill_evidence": [{"name": "Data Science", "evidence": "Work on projects related to Data Science / Data Analytics"}, {"name": "Data Analytics", "evidence": "Work on projects related to Data Science / Data Analytics"}, {"name": "Python", "evidence": "Use Python libraries (Numpy, Pandas, Matplot, pyHive & Scipy library)"}, {"name": "Numpy", "evidence": "Use Python libraries (Numpy, Pandas, Matplot, pyHive & Scipy library)"}, {"name": "Pandas", "evidence": "Use Python libraries (Numpy, Pandas, Matplot, pyHive & Scipy library)"}, {"name": "Matplotlib", "evidence": "Use Python libraries (Numpy, Pandas, Matplot, pyHive & Scipy library)"}, {"name": "AI Models", "evidence": "Develop AI Models and Deploy"}, {"name": "Deployment", "evidence": "Develop AI Models and Deploy"}, {"name": "Smart Sensors", "evidence": "Support in installing and configuring smart sensors to optimize media processing systems"}, {"name": "Software Integration", "evidence": "Experience in doing software integration and Deployment"}], "skills": ["Data Science", "Data Analytics", "Python", "Numpy", "Pandas", "Matplotlib", "AI Models", "Deployment", "Smart Sensors", "Software Integration"]}, {"title": "Senior Analyst, Global Trade Finance, Strategic Business Planning & Promotion 1", "company": "Sumitomo Group", "salary": "面议", "location": "SG", "experience": "不限", "education": "本科及以上", "description": "**Job Responsibilities**\n\n**Strategic Initiative Support**\n\n* Support the preparation of materials for internal strategic initiatives and business planning related to trade finance and adjacent businesses, such as flow banking (including deposit mobilization and FX transaction growth).\n* Conduct industry and market research to support the identification of trends, risks, and opportunities.\n* Assist in collaborating with internal planning teams, country partners, and in-country coverage teams across regions (not limited to APAC).\n* Help translate strategic concepts into clear, data-driven presentations for senior management.\n\n  \n\n**Client Proposal Development**\n\n* Assist in the preparation of pitch books and proposal materials tailored to client needs in trade finance and related areas.\n* Support front-line sales teams with market data, analysis, and customized solution inputs.\n* Ensure proposal materials are prepared in line with SMBC’s risk appetite and product capabilities.\n* Participate in client meetings as required to support presentations and capture feedback.\n\n  \n\n**Cross-functional Collaboration**\n\n* Work with coverage teams and product specialists to support strategic and operational alignment.\n* Assist in facilitating communication between strategic planning and client-facing teams.\n* Support the execution of initiatives such as Trade Working Capital Solutions sales activities and country-specific promotions.\n\n  \n\n**Job Requirements**\n\n* Bachelor’s degree in Finance, Business, Economics, or a related field.\n* 3–5 years of relevant experience in trade finance, corporate banking, investment banking, research/consulting firms, or related areas.\n* Basic to solid understanding of trade finance products, market trends, customer financials, and regulatory requirements in the APAC region.\n* Strong analytical, coordination, and communication skills, with the ability to work effectively across departments and regions.\n* Business fluency in English is essential, as this role requires written and verbal communication with the Tokyo office.\n* Detail-oriented with strong analytical and problem-solving abilities.\n* Ability to manage multiple tasks in a fast-paced, dynamic environment.\n* Willingness to learn and contribute to cross-functional projects.\n* Strong commitment to delivering high-quality client service and supporting internal business functions.\n* Ability to support trade finance deal origination activities in collaboration with senior team members and marketing managers.\n* Flexibility to perform other ad hoc duties as assigned.", "requirements": "Candidates must have 3–5 years of relevant experience in trade finance or related fields. A Bachelor’s degree in Finance, Business, Economics, or a related field is required. They should demonstrate a solid understanding of trade finance products and market trends in the APAC region.", "source": "Indeed", "source_warning": "部分数据源抓取失败：linkedin: 抓取超时，已跳过", "search_keyword": "Data Analyst", "relevance_score": 29, "relevance_reasons": ["标题部分命中: 大数据分析 / data analyst / big data analyst / data science / business intelligence analyst / data insights specialist", "描述命中: data", "标题命中: analyst", "标题命中: business", "描述命中: business", "描述命中: specialist"], "market_country": "新加坡", "skills": [], "skill_evidence": []}, {"title": "MSB & MSH PMO Senior Specialist", "company": "Micron Technology", "salary": "面议", "location": "SG", "experience": "不限", "education": "不限", "description": "**Our vision is to transform how the world uses information to enrich life for all.**\n\nJoin an inclusive team passionate about one thing: using their expertise in the relentless pursuit of innovation for customers and partners. The solutions we build help make everything from virtual reality experiences to breakthroughs in neural networks possible. We do it all while committing to integrity, sustainability, and giving back to our communities. Because doing so can fuel the very innovation we are pursuing.\n\n**Key Responsibilities:**\n\n* Strategic Project & Program Leadership\n  + Lead the identification, prioritization, and execution of complex, cross-functional projects and programs aligned with business strategy and transformation objectives.\n  + Apply advanced project management methodologies and industry best practices to deliver large-scale programs on schedule, within scope, and budget.\n  + Own end-to-end program governance, including milestone tracking, risk management, issue resolution, and executive-level escalation.\n  + Drive strategic transformation initiatives that deliver measurable business outcomes and competitive advantage.\n* Assembly & Test Operations Expertise\n  + Leverage hands-on experience in assembly & test (A&T) operations to inform project planning, resource optimization, and operational improvements.\n  + Partner with manufacturing and operations teams to align PMO initiatives with A&T operational priorities and constraints.\n  + Translate operational insights into actionable project strategies that enhance productivity, yield, and efficiency.\n* AI & Digital Transformation\n  + Champion the adoption and integration of AI technologies (including Generative AI, machine learning, and intelligent automation) to enhance project delivery and operational excellence.\n  + Lead initiatives that leverage AI-driven analytics, predictive modeling, and automation to transform business processes.\n  + Mentor team members on AI tools and digital solutions, fostering a culture of innovation and continuous learning.\n* Process Stewardship & Continuous Improvement\n  + Serve as a senior process steward for business planning and project management activities, ensuring governance, compliance, and adoption of best practices.\n  + Lead diagnostics, define strategic goals/KPIs, and drive enterprise-wide improvement opportunities.\n  + Establish and optimize business processes, frameworks, and standards to elevate PMO maturity.\n* Performance, Metrics & Reporting\n  + Design and manage executive-level dashboards and performance reporting using advanced digital tools.\n  + Drive accountability for site and organizational KPIs, including cost optimization, operational excellence, and transformation metrics.\n  + Provide strategic insights and recommendations based on data-driven analysis.\n* Stakeholder Engagement & Executive Communication\n  + Lead structured dialogues and influence cross-functional senior stakeholders to drive program success and alignment.\n  + Serve as a trusted advisor to leadership, providing visibility into program health, risks, and strategic recommendations.\n  + Represent the PMO in executive forums and steering committees.\n* Collaboration, Culture & Mentorship\n  + Collaborate with internal and external partners at senior levels to optimize strategies, resources, and partnerships.\n  + Mentor and coach junior PMO team members, fostering professional development and high performance.\n  + Champion integration into company culture and drive engagement through leadership, recognition, and team-building initiatives.\n\n**Micron Values:**\n\n* People – Demonstrates respect, inclusion, and collaboration; values diverse perspectives and fosters a supportive team environment.\n* Innovation – Shows curiosity and a growth mindset; actively seeks creative solutions to improve processes, products, or outcomes.\n* Tenacity – Approaches challenges with perseverance and resilience; maintains focus and drives progress even in ambiguity.\n* Collaboration – Communicates effectively across functions and builds strong partnerships to achieve shared goals.\n* Customer Focus – Understands customer needs and consistently delivers high‑quality work that supports customer success.\n\n**Requirements:**\n\n* Education\n  + Bachelor''s Degree in Engineering, Business, Operations Management, or a related field and MBA is a must.\n* Experience\n  + Minimum 6 years of progressive experience in project/program management, with a strong focus on assembly & test (A&T) operations within the semiconductor or manufacturing industry is a must\n  + Proven track record in leading strategy and transformation initiatives that delivered measurable business results.\n  + Demonstrated experience managing complex, multi-stakeholder programs with significant budget and organizational impact.\n* Technical & Functional Expertise\n  + Advanced proficiency in project management methodologies, PMP certification is a must\n  + Hands-on experience utilizing AI technologies, including Generative AI, machine learning, RPA, or intelligent automation in business or operational contexts is a must\n  + Proficiency in digital tools such as Python, Power BI, advanced analytics platforms, or similar technologies is a must\n* Leadership & Soft Skills\n  + Strong strategic thinking with the ability to translate vision into actionable plans.\n  + Exceptional leadership, influencing, and stakeholder management skills at all organizational levels.\n  + Excellent communication and presentation skills, with experience engaging executive audiences.\n  + Proven ability to lead cross-functional teams and drive results in a dynamic, fast-paced environment.\n  + Strong analytical and problem-solving skills with a data-driven mindset.\n* Preferred Qualifications\n  + PMP, PgMP, or equivalent project management certification.\n  + Lean Six Sigma Green/Black Belt certification.\n  + Experience with semiconductor manufacturing processes and operational excellence frameworks.\n  + Track record of successfully implementing AI/digital solutions in an operational environment.\n\n**About Micron Technology, Inc.**\n\nWe are an industry leader in innovative memory and storage solutions transforming how the world uses information to enrich life *for all*. With a relentless focus on our customers, technology leadership, and manufacturing and operational excellence, Micron delivers a rich portfolio of high-performance DRAM, NAND, and NOR memory and storage products through our Micron® and Crucial® brands. Every day, the innovations that our people create fuel the data economy, enabling advances in artificial intelligence and 5G applications that unleash opportunities — from the data center to the intelligent edge and across the client and mobile user experience.  \n  \nTo learn more, please visit micron.com/careers  \n  \nAll qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, veteran or disability status.  \n  \nTo request assistance with the application process and/or for reasonable accommodations, please contact hrsupport\\_sg@micron.com\n\nMicron Prohibits the use of child labor and complies with all applicable laws, rules, regulations, and other international and industry labor standards.\n\nMicron does not charge candidates any recruitment fees or unlawfully collect any other payment from candidates as consideration for their employment with Micron.\n\nAI alert: Candidates are encouraged to use AI tools to enhance their resume and/or application materials. However, all information provided must be accurate and reflect the candidate''s true skills and experiences. Misuse of AI to fabricate or misrepresent qualifications will result in immediate disqualification.\n\nFraud alert: Micron advises job seekers to be cautious of unsolicited job offers and to verify the authenticity of any communication claiming to be from Micron by checking the official Micron careers website in the About Micron Technology, Inc.", "requirements": "Lead complex, cross-functional projects and programs aligned with business strategy; apply advanced project management methodologies and best practices; champion AI technologies and digital solutions; serve as a senior process steward for business planning and project management activities; design and manage executive-level dashboards and performance reporting; drive accountability for KPIs; collaborate with internal and external partners at senior levels; mentor junior PMO team members.", "source": "Indeed", "source_warning": "部分数据源抓取失败：linkedin: 抓取超时，已跳过", "search_keyword": "Data Insights Specialist", "relevance_score": 27, "relevance_reasons": ["标题部分命中: 大数据分析 / data analyst / big data analyst / data science / business intelligence analyst / data insights specialist", "描述命中: data", "描述命中: big", "描述命中: business", "描述命中: intelligence", "描述命中: insights", "标题命中: specialist"], "market_country": "新加坡", "skill_evidence": [{"name": "AI Technologies", "evidence": "Champion the adoption and integration of AI technologies (including Generative AI, machine learning, and intelligent..."}, {"name": "Generative AI", "evidence": "Champion the adoption and integration of AI technologies (including Generative AI, machine learning, and intelligent..."}, {"name": "Machine Learning", "evidence": "Champion the adoption and integration of AI technologies (including Generative AI, machine learning, and intelligent..."}, {"name": "Intelligent Automation", "evidence": "Champion the adoption and integration of AI technologies (including Generative AI, machine learning, and intelligent..."}, {"name": "Predictive Modeling", "evidence": "Lead initiatives that leverage AI-driven analytics, predictive modeling, and automation to transform business processes."}, {"name": "Digital Tools", "evidence": "Design and manage executive-level dashboards and performance reporting using advanced digital tools."}, {"name": "Project Management Methodologies", "evidence": "Apply advanced project management methodologies and industry best practices to deliver large-scale programs on schedu..."}, {"name": "Executive-level Dashboards", "evidence": "Design and manage executive-level dashboards and performance reporting using advanced digital tools."}, {"name": "KPIs", "evidence": "Drive accountability for site and organizational KPIs, including cost optimization, operational excellence, and trans..."}, {"name": "Business Processes", "evidence": "Establish and optimize business processes, frameworks, and standards to elevate PMO maturity."}, {"name": "Frameworks", "evidence": "Establish and optimize business processes, frameworks, and standards to elevate PMO maturity."}, {"name": "Standards", "evidence": "Establish and optimize business processes, frameworks, and standards to elevate PMO maturity."}], "skills": ["AI Technologies", "Generative AI", "Machine Learning", "Intelligent Automation", "Predictive Modeling", "Digital Tools", "Project Management Methodologies", "Executive-level Dashboards", "KPIs", "Business Processes", "Frameworks", "Standards"]}, {"title": "Product Specialist – Workday Talent Suite", "company": "Workday", "salary": "面议", "location": "SG", "experience": "不限", "education": "不限", "description": "**Your work days are brighter here.**\n\nWe’re obsessed with making hard work pay off, for our people, our customers, and the world around us. As a Fortune 500 company and a leading AI platform for managing people, money, and agents, we’re shaping the future of work so teams can reach their potential and focus on what matters most. The minute you join, you’ll feel it. Not just in the products we build, but in how we show up for each other. Our culture is rooted in integrity, empathy, and shared enthusiasm. We’re in this together, tackling big challenges with bold ideas and genuine care. We look for curious minds and courageous collaborators who bring sun-drenched optimism and drive. Whether you''re building smarter solutions, supporting customers, or creating a space where everyone belongs, you’ll do meaningful work with Workmates who’ve got your back. In return, we’ll give you the trust to take risks, the tools to grow, the skills to develop and the support of a company invested in you for the long haul. So, if you want to inspire a brighter work day for everyone, including yourself, you’ve found a match in Workday, and we hope to be a match for you too.\n\n**About the Team**\n\nWorkmates pride themselves on winning while having fun! That means supporting each other while driving accountability for outstanding results and performance. This team is no different. Everything we do encourages a brighter work day for all. The Enterprise Specialized Sales team at Workday helps the company continue to grow by balancing integrity and innovation, ensuring Workmates have the environment to bring out their best self, and get better by pushing and developing themselves and the Workmates around them.  \nYou will be selling the market-leading solution that industry analysts like Josh Bersin and Proficiency Research are calling the \"new frontier of agentic AI.\" You will help customers realize tangible outcomes: 70% candidate conversion rates, 54% boost in recruiter capacity, and 2X increases in internal mobility.  \nIf you are a goal-oriented self-starter ready to sell the future of recruiting, we want to hear from you.\n\n**About the Role**\n\nAs a Product Specialist, you are a key player in driving Workday’s growth for our AI Talent Suite - driving the sales of our two flagship AI acquisitions: HiredScore and Paradox.\n\nYou are not just selling software; you are selling a vision of \"Human + AI\" orchestration and collaboration. You will be responsible for guiding customers away from fragmented, disconnected point solutions and toward a unified, agentic AI reality. By positioning HiredScore and Paradox alongside Workday Recruiting and Candidate Engagement, you will help organizations achieve Total Talent Acquisition—automating high-volume tasks while elevating high-value human decisions.\n\nKey Responsibilities Include:\n\nHolistic Talent Strategy & Orchestration\n\n* Drive the \"Total Talent\" Narrative: You will articulate a flawless vision where Workday Recruiting (Core) and Candidate Engagement (Cultivate) are supercharged by Paradox (Conversational AI/Scheduling) and HiredScore (Talent Orchestration/Prioritization).\n* Diagnose & Prescribe: You must be able to evaluate a customer’s hiring landscape to deploy the right AI agents. You will identify where to deploy Paradox for high-volume/hourly speed and candidate experience, and where to position HiredScore for professional roles, internal mobility, and recruiter efficiency.\n* Competitive Positioning: Evangelizing Workday’s \"Smart Mirror\" approach—demonstrating how our AI layers on top of the system of record without crafting data silos or integration nightmares.\n\nSales Execution & Collaboration\n\n* Co-Selling Partnership: Work in lock-step with Core Account Executives to integrate AI solutions into broader platform transformation deals.\n* Complex Deal Management: Lead sophisticated sales cycles involving multiple stakeholders (CHROs, Heads of TA, CIOs, and AI Compliance Officers). You will navigate data privacy concerns and explain the value of \"Responsible AI.\"\n* Pipeline & Forecasting: Maintain a healthy pipeline of net-new opportunities within existing Workday accounts and new business targets, forecasting accurately in a high-growth environment.\n\n**About You**\n\nBasic Qualifications\n\n* 3+ years of experience selling sophisticated SaaS/Cloud solutions to C-Level executives (CHRO, CIO, CTO).\n* 3+ years Deep Domain Expertise: Proven experience in HR Technology, Talent Acquisition, or AI-driven recruiting software. You must deeply understand the difference between an ATS, a CRM, and an AI Orchestration layer.\n* 3+ years Platform Selling: Experience selling multi-product suites. You know how to sell a \"better together\" story rather than just a standalone product.\n\nOther Qualifications\n\n* Technical & competitive fluency: You can articulate why a \"Unified Data Model\" beats a \"connector\" approach. You are comfortable discussing how AI integrates with core workflows to reduce \"toggle tax\" for recruiters.\n* Segment Agility: You possess the mental agility to shift between conversations about Frontline/Hourly hiring (speed-to-hire, text-to-apply, scheduling automation) and Corporate/Professional hiring (rediscovery, silver medalists, internal mobility).\n* Consultative Approach: You can guide a client through a \"maturity model\"—showing them how to move from manual recruiting to Agentic AI (Recruiting & Mobility Agents).\n* Resilience & Adaptability: You thrive in a fast-paced, evolving environment where you are helping to advise demand generation strategies and define the market for dynamic AI solutions.\n\n**Our Approach to Flexible Work**\n\nWith Flex Work, we’re combining the best of both worlds: in-person time and remote. Our approach enables our teams to deepen connections, maintain a strong community, and do their best work. We know that flexibility can take shape in many ways, so rather than a number of required days in-office each week, we simply **spend at least half (50%) of our time each quarter in the office or in the field** with our customers, prospects, and partners (depending on role). This means you''ll have the freedom to create a flexible schedule that caters to your business, team, and personal needs, while being intentional to make the most of time spent together. Those in our remote \"home office\" roles also have the opportunity to come together in our offices for important moments that matter.\n\nAt Workday, we are committed to providing an accessible and inclusive hiring experience where all candidates can fully demonstrate their skills. If you require assistance or an accommodation at any point, please email\n\naccommodations@workday.com\n\n.\n\n**Are you being referred to one of our roles? If so, ask your connection at Workday about our Employee Referral process!**\n\nAt Workday, we value our candidates’ privacy and data security. Workday will never ask candidates to apply to jobs through websites that are not Workday Careers.\n\nPlease be aware of sites that may ask for you to input your data in connection with a job posting that appears to be from Workday but is not.\n\nIn addition, Workday will never ask candidates to pay a recruiting fee, or pay for consulting or coaching services, in order to apply for a job at Workday.", "requirements": "You will be selling the market-leading solution that industry analysts like Josh Bersin and Proficiency Research are calling the ''new frontier of agentic AI''. You will help customers realize tangible outcomes: 70% candidate conversion rates, 54% boost in recruiter capacity, and 2X increases in internal mobility.", "source": "Indeed", "source_warning": "部分数据源抓取失败：linkedin: 抓取超时，已跳过", "search_keyword": "Big Data Analyst", "relevance_score": 27, "relevance_reasons": ["标题部分命中: 大数据分析 / data analyst / big data analyst / data science / business intelligence analyst / data insights specialist", "描述命中: data", "描述命中: analyst", "描述命中: big", "描述命中: business", "标题命中: specialist", "描述命中: specialist"], "market_country": "新加坡", "skills": [], "skill_evidence": []}, {"title": "Analyst, Global Mobility and Immigration", "company": "Salesforce", "salary": "面议", "location": "S00", "experience": "不限", "education": "不限", "description": "*To get the best candidate experience, please consider applying for a maximum of 3 roles within 12 months to ensure you are not duplicating efforts.*\n\nJob Category\n\nEmployee Success\n\nJob Details\n\n**About Salesforce**\n\nSalesforce is the #1 AI CRM, where humans with agents drive customer success together. Here, ambition meets action. Tech meets trust. And innovation isn’t a buzzword — it’s a way of life. The world of work as we know it is changing and we''re looking for Trailblazers who are passionate about bettering business and the world through AI, driving innovation, and keeping Salesforce''s core values at the heart of it all.\n\nReady to level-up your career at the company leading workforce transformation in the agentic era? You’re in the right place! Agentforce is the future of AI, and you are the future of Salesforce.\n\nThe Salesforce Global Mobility & Immigration Team is looking for a highly organised and proactive Analyst to support global mobility and immigration programs for the JAPAC and India region.\n\nThis role is integral to attracting, retaining, and mobilising top talent globally, focusing on the administration and management of relocation and immigration cases and experience for employees. This includes administering various programs such as relocation, immigration, tax support, assignment management, and one-way relocations, through effective partnership with employees, stakeholders, external vendors, and suppliers.\n\n**Key Responsibilities:**\n\n* Serve as the primary point of contact and deliver a high-quality relocation experience for relocation cases across JAPAC & India, managing the end-to-end mobility journey.\n* Review mobility policy options and needs assessment with stakeholders and employees and ensure business and relocation needs are clearly understood and supported.\n* Provide ongoing guidance and support to employees and stakeholders on work authorisation requirements and throughout the immigration process.\n* Partner with external relocation service providers to deliver immigration and relocation services; address and resolve service issues as needed.\n* Monitor vendor performance and ensure adherence to compliance requirements and service standards.\n* Maintain accurate documentation of employee cases, communications, policy exceptions, and approvals in accordance with privacy and data governance standards.\n* Review and evaluate policy exceptions or complex relocation scenarios, providing recommendations and appropriate solutions to stakeholders.\n* Monitor relocation costs and expenses to ensure alignment with program guidelines while maximising employee support.\n* Coordinate with internal stakeholders including, but not limited to Finance, Payroll, Legal, ES business partners, Recruiting and ES Operations teams to support mobility program operations.\n* Support the broader global mobility team by coordinating across regions, sharing best practices, and assisting with process improvements to ensure consistent, high-quality service delivery worldwide.\n* Perform additional duties and project support as requested by the Global Mobility & Immigration regional leader and/or global leadership.\n\n**Qualifications / Requirements:**\n\n* Minimum 3–4 years of experience in Global Mobility and/or Immigration, with exposure to APAC/JAPAC and India mobility processes and requirements.\n* Excellent written and verbal communication skills.\n* Strong organisational skills and ability to manage multiple cases and priorities simultaneously.\n* Agility & Adaptability – effectively navigates changing priorities and ambiguity in a fast-paced environment.\n* Stakeholder Partnership – collaborates effectively with employees, internal teams, and external vendors.\n* Operational Excellence & Attention to Detail – maintains accuracy in documentation, case management, and data tracking.\n* Strong service orientation with a solutions-oriented approach, supporting employees and their families and the business through complex immigration and relocation processes.\n* Program Compliance & Governance – understands mobility policies, immigration requirements, and data privacy standards.\n* Experience working with collaboration tools such as Google Workspace, Slack, and/or similar platforms.\n* Self-starter with the ability to work independently, while contributing effectively in a global, cross-functional environment.\n\nUnleash Your Potential\n\nWhen you join Salesforce, you’ll be limitless in all areas of your life. Our benefits and resources support you to find balance and *be your best* , and our AI agents accelerate your impact so you can *do your best* . Together, we’ll bring the power of Agentforce to organizations of all sizes and deliver amazing experiences that customers love. Apply today to not only shape the future — but to redefine what’s possible — for yourself, for AI, and the world.\n\nAccommodations\n\nIf you need a reasonable accommodation during the application or the recruiting process, please submit a request via this Accommodations Request Form .\n\nPlease note that Salesforce uses artificial intelligence (AI) tools to help our recruiters assess and evaluate candidates’ resumes and qualifications throughout the recruiting process. Humans will always make any candidate selection and hiring decisions. Please see our Candidate Privacy Statement for more information about how we use your personal data and your rights, including with regard to use of AI tools and opt out options.\n\nPosting Statement\n\nSalesforce is an equal opportunity employer and maintains a policy of non-discrimination with all employees and applicants for employment. What does that mean exactly? It means that at Salesforce, we believe in equality for all. And we believe we can lead the path to equality in part by creating a workplace that’s inclusive, and free from discrimination. Know your rights: workplace discrimination is illegal. Any employee or potential employee will be assessed on the basis of merit, competence and qualifications – without regard to race, religion, color, national origin, sex, sexual orientation, gender expression or identity, transgender status, age, disability, veteran or marital status, political viewpoint, or other classifications protected by law. This policy applies to current and prospective employees, no matter where they are in their Salesforce employment journey. It also applies to recruiting, hiring, job assignment, compensation, promotion, benefits, training, assessment of job performance, discipline, termination, and everything in between. Recruiting, hiring, and promotion decisions at Salesforce are fair and based on merit. The same goes for compensation, benefits, promotions, transfers, reduction in workforce, recall, training, and education.", "requirements": "具备全球调动和移民相关经验，熟悉APAC/JAPAC和印度的调动流程；能够有效管理多个案件和优先级；需与员工、内部团队及外部供应商协作；注重文档准确性和细节。", "source": "Indeed", "source_warning": "部分数据源抓取失败：linkedin: 抓取超时，已跳过", "search_keyword": "Business Intelligence Analyst", "relevance_score": 27, "relevance_reasons": ["标题部分命中: 大数据分析 / data analyst / big data analyst / data science / business intelligence analyst / data insights specialist", "描述命中: data", "标题命中: analyst", "描述命中: analyst", "描述命中: big", "描述命中: business", "描述命中: intelligence"], "market_country": "新加坡", "skills": [], "skill_evidence": []}, {"title": "Global Facilities Data Analytics Program Manager", "company": "Micron Technology", "salary": "面议", "location": "SG", "experience": "不限", "education": "硕士及以上", "description": "**Our vision is to transform how the world uses information to enrich life for all.**\n\nJoin an inclusive team passionate about one thing: using their expertise in the relentless pursuit of innovation for customers and partners. The solutions we build help make everything from virtual reality experiences to breakthroughs in neural networks possible. We do it all while committing to integrity, sustainability, and giving back to our communities. Because doing so can fuel the very innovation we are pursuing.\n\nAs a Global Facilities Data Analytics Program Manager, you will lead enterprise data architecture, advanced analytics, dashboard development, and automation initiatives. This role requires strong technical expertise in designing and deploying complex PowerBI dashboards in enterprise environments.\n\nThis role requires a strong data management background and the ability to translate complex data into concise summaries and dashboards. You should be detail‑oriented, with the capability to deliver clear, high‑quality data analysis that supports leadership decision‑making. A solid understanding of data is essential to identify opportunities for data optimization and benchmarking. The role also requires flexibility, the ability to maintain global relationships, and strong communication and presentation skills.\n\n**Major Job Responsibilities:**\n\n**Data Governance and Architecture**\n\n* Design scalable enterprise data models and reporting frameworks.\n* Establish KPI definitions and structured data logic.\n* Ensure data integrity, performance optimization, and governance standards.\n* Drive reporting automation and digital transformation initiatives.\n\n**Advanced Dashboard Development**\n\n* Design and develop complex PowerBI dashboards with multi-layered data models.\n* Write advanced DAX measures and calculated columns.\n* Build data transformation pipelines using Power Query (M Language).\n* Integrate multiple data sources into structured semantic models.\n* Optimize performance for large and complex datasets.\n* Deliver executive‑level dashboards with drill‑down, dynamic filtering, and advanced analytics and visualization logic leveraging machine learning and AI models.\n\n**Automation & Digital Solutions**\n\n* Develop workflow automation using Power Automate.\n* Build business applications using Power Apps.\n* Integrate dashboards with automated workflows and scalable solutions.\n\n**Requirements**\n\n* Proven track record of independently delivering complex, enterprise‑scale BI solutions.\n* Strong expertise in data modeling, semantic layer design, and scalable analytics architecture.\n* Ability to design analytical solutions beyond basic reporting use cases.\n* Demonstrated ownership of end‑to‑end dashboard delivery, from data ingestion through production deployment.\n* Strong problem‑solving skills with the ability to structure ambiguous and complex data challenges into clear analytical frameworks.\n* Experience working effectively in cross‑functional and global environments.\n* Strong communication skills, with the ability to clearly explain technical concepts to non‑technical stakeholders.\n* Familiarity with cost information systems, including SAP and SAP Analytics Cloud Planning (SAC‑P).\n* Highly collaborative team player with excellent interpersonal skills.\n* Organized, detail‑oriented, and highly focused on data accuracy and quality.\n* Demonstrates a high level of integrity in managing sensitive and confidential data.\n* Culturally aware, with the ability to build long‑term trust and working relationships across a global Facilities network.\n* Adaptable and resilient in dynamic, fast‑changing business environments.\n* Continuous improvement mindset, consistently seeking opportunities to enhance efficiency and improve business processes in partnership with stakeholders.\n\n**Education & Experience**\n\n* Bachelor’s Degree and above specialized in Engineering, Information systems, Business, or Finance or equivalent experience\n* 5+ years of professional experience in data analytics is required, with experience applying analytics tools and BI platforms (e.g., Power BI) to build dashboards, models, and analytical insights.\n\n**About Micron Technology, Inc.**\n\nWe are an industry leader in innovative memory and storage solutions transforming how the world uses information to enrich life *for all*. With a relentless focus on our customers, technology leadership, and manufacturing and operational excellence, Micron delivers a rich portfolio of high-performance DRAM, NAND, and NOR memory and storage products through our Micron® and Crucial® brands. Every day, the innovations that our people create fuel the data economy, enabling advances in artificial intelligence and 5G applications that unleash opportunities — from the data center to the intelligent edge and across the client and mobile user experience.  \n  \nTo learn more, please visit micron.com/careers  \n  \nAll qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, veteran or disability status.  \n  \nTo request assistance with the application process and/or for reasonable accommodations, please contact hrsupport\\_sg@micron.com\n\nMicron Prohibits the use of child labor and complies with all applicable laws, rules, regulations, and other international and industry labor standards.\n\nMicron does not charge candidates any recruitment fees or unlawfully collect any other payment from candidates as consideration for their employment with Micron.\n\nAI alert: Candidates are encouraged to use AI tools to enhance their resume and/or application materials. However, all information provided must be accurate and reflect the candidate''s true skills and experiences. Misuse of AI to fabricate or misrepresent qualifications will result in immediate disqualification.\n\nFraud alert: Micron advises job seekers to be cautious of unsolicited job offers and to verify the authenticity of any communication claiming to be from Micron by checking the official Micron careers website in the About Micron Technology, Inc.", "requirements": "Proven track record of delivering complex, enterprise-scale BI solutions. Strong problem-solving skills to structure ambiguous data challenges into analytical frameworks. Experience working in cross-functional and global environments.", "source": "Indeed", "source_warning": "部分数据源抓取失败：linkedin: 抓取超时，已跳过", "search_keyword": "Data Analyst", "relevance_score": 27, "relevance_reasons": ["标题部分命中: 大数据分析 / data analyst / big data analyst / data science / business intelligence analyst / data insights specialist", "标题命中: data", "描述命中: data", "描述命中: big", "描述命中: business", "描述命中: intelligence", "描述命中: insights"], "market_country": "新加坡", "skill_evidence": [{"name": "Power BI", "evidence": "designing and deploying complex PowerBI dashboards in enterprise environments"}, {"name": "Power Query (M Language)", "evidence": "build data transformation pipelines using Power Query (M Language)"}, {"name": "DAX Measures", "evidence": "write advanced DAX measures and calculated columns"}, {"name": "Power Automate", "evidence": "develop workflow automation using Power Automate"}, {"name": "Power Apps", "evidence": "build business applications using Power Apps"}, {"name": "Data Modeling", "evidence": "strong expertise in data modeling, semantic layer design, and scalable analytics architecture"}, {"name": "Semantic Layer Design", "evidence": "strong expertise in data modeling, semantic layer design, and scalable analytics architecture"}, {"name": "Scalable Analytics Architecture", "evidence": "strong expertise in data modeling, semantic layer design, and scalable analytics architecture"}], "skills": ["Power BI", "Power Query (M Language)", "DAX Measures", "Power Automate", "Power Apps", "Data Modeling", "Semantic Layer Design", "Scalable Analytics Architecture"]}, {"title": "Enterprise Services - Portfolio Enterprise Support Specialist - Singapore", "company": "Bloomberg", "salary": "面议", "location": "S00", "experience": "不限", "education": "不限", "description": "Enterprise Services - Portfolio Enterprise Support Specialist - Singapore\n\nLocation\n\nSingapore\n\nBusiness Area\n\nSales and Client Service\n\nRef #\n\n10049845\n\n**Description & Requirements**\n------------------------------\n\nBloomberg is a global leader in business and financial information, news and insight, and we use innovative technology to deliver trusted data and bring transparency to the financial markets. Our customers around the globe rely on us for the information and tools they need to make critical investment decisions and remain connected across all sides of the financial community. And, to ensure the best experience for our 26,000+ employees across more than 150 locations around the world, we provide the spaces and systems that allow our teams to work together with agility, productivity and collaboration, no matter where they are.\n\nOur Portfolio & Risk Analytics (PORT Enterprise) solution helps portfolio and risk managers achieve performance and risk objectives by providing unmatched transparency into each portfolio’s historical attribution, characteristics, and ex-ante risk. From one centralised location, our series of powerful, integrated multi-asset tools deliver consistent and detailed insight into the client’s portfolio. Utilising this service enables our enterprise clients to create and execute differentiating investment strategies accordingly.\n\n**What''s the role?**\n\nAs part of the PORT Enterprise Support team, you will work in a client facing role which involves liaising with portfolio and risk managers, analysts, quants, traders, and back/middle-office professionals. We are looking for individuals with a strong level of understanding of Financial Markets, Economic Theory, Portfolio Attribution/Performance, Portfolio Risk/Tracking Error, and Asset Class Characteristics/Analytics/Performance Calculations. You will help support our largest buy-side PORT Enterprise clients’ complex questions involving portfolio performance, security analytics, risk, and workflow setup.\n\nThis is a highly visible role with opportunities for career advancement and growth within the department or company, such as becoming a Product Advocate within the team, or progressing to a PORT Enterprise Sales role, moving into a leadership position, or pursuing a role in our Product or Implementation teams.\n\n**We''ll trust you to:**\n\n* Build a comprehensive understanding of the features and capabilities of our portfolio product offering, through training and on-the-job learning, in order to manage client queries quickly and efficiently\n* Troubleshoot issues pertaining to the PORT Enterprise product, while assessing any potential business and/or operational impact\n* Understand and support clients on methodologies inquiries around portfolio performance, attribution, and risk\n* Identify gaps and opportunities to introduce best practices and new processes to enhance efficiency and improve on existing processes\n* Collaborate extensively with our Portfolio Implementation, Portfolio Sales, and Portfolio Engineering teams to improve our clients'' experience and overall performance of our technology\n* Foster excellent relationships with key PORT Enterprise clients to improve their overall experience in using the product\n* Manage client expectations through timely and effective communications during systemic issues or escalations\n* Raise issues and liaise with Product and Engineering for enhancements or any other remediation requested by clients\n* Leverage Python to automate internal processes and build Python-based functions on internal applications which are to be used for conditional validation on large data sets\n\n  \n\n**You''ll need to have:**\n\n* Minimum 5 years of experience in financial services or a financial technology company\n* Experience of Fixed Income and Portfolio & Risk Analytics gained within the past 3 years\n* Experience in supporting or selling to buy-side institutions gained within the past 3 years\n* Hands-on experience working with Python\n* Attention to detail with strong analytical skills to evaluate problems and provide solutions\n* The ambition to take ownership and responsibility of issues and handle them effectively through to resolution\n* The inclination and aptitude to pick up new technologies and procedures\n* Strong interpersonal and organizational skills, to drive and implement ideas in a changing environment\n* Proficiency with Microsoft applications – Excel (Advanced), PowerPoint, and Word\n* Demonstrated continuous career growth within an organisation\n* Strong presentation and communication skills in English\n* Bachelor’s degree or degree equivalent qualifications\n\n  \n\n**We''d love to see:**\n\n* Understanding of workflows used by portfolio managers, risk and attribution specialists, and the ability to build and understand complex workflow solutions\n* Proficiency with Microsoft Power BI, Visio, and experience with Bloomberg products\n* Business proficiency in Chinese (Mandarin) or other Asian languages, as this role will support clients who speak a diverse range of languages\n\n  \n\n**If this sounds like you:**\n\nApply if you think we''re a good match. We''ll get in touch to let you know what the next steps are, , but in the meantime feel free to have a look at this:\n\n  \n  \n\n**Why Bloomberg?**\n\nWe’re individuals with diverse backgrounds, talents, and experiences who take on big challenges and create even bigger impact through our work. We’re interested in what makes you you, and how we can create opportunities for you to channel your unique, personal energy and grow to your fullest potential.\n\n**Learn more about our office and benefits:**\n\nSingapore |\n\n  \n  \n\nBloomberg is committed to improving the communities, cities and countries in which we work, and we support various initiatives including hiring and developing local talent. So, we may prioritise candidates with legal authorisation to work full-time in Singapore for this role, who do not require Bloomberg to sponsor their work authorization.\n\nDiscover what makes Bloomberg unique - watch our for an inside look at our culture, values, and the people behind our success.", "requirements": "候选人需具备金融市场的深入理解，以及在固定收益和投资组合及风险分析方面的经验。同时需要有支持或销售给买方机构的经验，并且具备Python的实际操作能力。", "source": "Indeed", "source_warning": "部分数据源抓取失败：linkedin: 抓取超时，已跳过", "search_keyword": "Big Data Analyst", "relevance_score": 27, "relevance_reasons": ["标题部分命中: 大数据分析 / data analyst / big data analyst / data science / business intelligence analyst / data insights specialist", "描述命中: data", "描述命中: analyst", "描述命中: big", "描述命中: business", "标题命中: specialist", "描述命中: specialist"], "market_country": "新加坡", "skill_evidence": [{"name": "Python", "evidence": "Leverage Python to automate internal processes and build Python-based functions on internal applications which are to..."}], "skills": ["Python"]}, {"title": "Specialist, Marketing & Communications - APAC", "company": "BCD", "salary": "面议", "location": "S00", "experience": "不限", "education": "硕士及以上", "description": "**About Us:**\n\nAt BCD Meetings & Events (BCD M&E), we provide more than meeting and event planning services: we create connections that inspire, motivate and change behavior for our customers. As the world’s most trusted and innovative meetings and events agency, BCD M&E cultivates a culture of people, passion and purpose to drive business forward.\n\nHeadquartered in Chicago, with locations in 50+ countries across the world, BCD M&E’s team of 2,000+ people are committed to sustainability and driving success for our customers, our business and ourselves. Our values are at the heart of everything we do, and we look for people that want to be a part of something special, can rise to our standards and love to bring their unique perspective to the table.\n\nWhile we can’t guarantee every day will be the best (who can?), we can promise a community of people who genuinely care and lead with empathy, a flexible workplace with awesome perks and challenging work that means something.\n\nSee what life is about at BCD M&E at bcdme.com/careers\n\n**Specialist, Marketing & Communications - APAC**\n\nWe’re looking for a dynamic and results-driven Marketing Specialist to join our global marketing team, focusing on the Asia Pacific region (APAC). This role reports directly to the Director, Global Brand Marketing and will play a crucial part in developing and executing marketing strategies that drive brand awareness and business growth across the APAC markets. The Specialist will also report to the Managing Director APAC, in region.\n\n**Your responsibilities**\n\n  \n\n* Collaborate with the Director, Global Brand Marketing, Managing Director APAC & the APAC Senior Leadership Team to develop and implement tailored marketing strategies for the APAC region, aligning with the global marketing goals and objectives.\n* Plan, execute, and optimize regional marketing efforts, including digital, social media, PR, content marketing, and communications to drive engagement and lead generation.\n* Develop compelling and culturally relevant marketing content tailored to the diverse audiences within the APAC region, including blog posts, social media content, email newsletters, and more.\n* Monitor and analyze the key performance indicators (KPIs) of marketing tactics and initiatives, providing regular reports and recommendations for improvement.\n* Keep a regional pulse on the industry to identify trends, opportunities, and competitive landscape within APAC, providing insights to inform marketing strategies and initiatives.\n* Ensure all marketing activities and materials are consistent with the company''s brand guidelines and messaging, maintaining a cohesive brand presence across the APAC region.\n* Work closely with other members of the global marketing team, sales, leadership, and external partners to ensure alignment and successful execution of marketing programs.\n\n**You’re good at**\n\n  \n\n* Turning business concepts into creative, engaging campaigns\n* Conceptualizing and developing communications and skilled at storytelling to support marketing and business objectives\n* Building and fostering stakeholder relationships as the internal brand ambassador and empowering other internal brand champions\n* Working well under deadline and efficiently managing competing priorities\n* Adapting to change and direction as global business strategy adjusts to market and customer demands\n* Communicating with and guiding executive leaders to ensure messaging alignment\n* Working in a fast-paced, deadline-driven and highly collaborative environment\n\n**You might also have**\n\n  \n\n* Bachelor’s degree in Marketing, Communications, PR, or a related field.\n* Minimum five years of experience in marketing, with a focus on the APAC region.\n* Proven track record of developing and executing successful marketing campaigns.\n* Strong understanding of digital marketing channels, tools, and best practices.\n* Excellent communication and interpersonal skills.\n* Ability to work independently and collaboratively in a fast-paced, global environment.\n* Strong analytical skills with the ability to interpret data and generate actionable insights.\n* Proficiency in marketing automation platforms and CRM systems.\n\n**THE PERKS**\n\n**Flexible Working**\n\nWe believe that a flexible working environment is key to getting the best out of our teams. We will support you to work where you need to and when you need to, depending on how you work best.\n\n**Room to Grow**\n\nOur line of work and business structure challenge our people in a way that inspires growth, with learning and development built into every role. We give individuals ownership over the direction and speed in which they grow.\n\n**Everyone has a voice**\n\nWe thrive on conversations that spark curiosity and empathy. No matter how big or how small, every voice is heard, considered and respected.\n\n**Make your move**\n\nThe diversity of roles across BCD M&E’s global locations means that our people often find new adventures during their time with us.\n\n**We’ve got you covered**\n\nOur extensive benefits include comprehensive healthcare, continued education support, diverse work locations, travel and hotel discounts, volunteer and sustainability opportunities and a successful employee recognition program.\n\n**We’re positive. You’ll love it.**\n\nIt starts from the top. Our leaders lead with positivity, believe in our people and trust us to do the right thing. There will always be support along your journey, in little and big ways.\n\n#LI-MB1\n\n#LI-EM1\n\n#LI-LZ1  \n#LI-KW1  \n#LI-Remote\n\n#LI-Hybrid\n\n#LI-Onsite", "requirements": "Develop and execute successful marketing campaigns. Maintain brand consistency across the APAC region. Collaborate with global marketing team and regional leadership.", "source": "Indeed", "source_warning": "部分数据源抓取失败：linkedin: 抓取超时，已跳过", "search_keyword": "Data Insights Specialist", "relevance_score": 27, "relevance_reasons": ["标题部分命中: 大数据分析 / data analyst / big data analyst / data science / business intelligence analyst / data insights specialist", "描述命中: data", "描述命中: big", "描述命中: business", "描述命中: insights", "标题命中: specialist", "描述命中: specialist"], "market_country": "新加坡", "skill_evidence": [{"name": "Digital Marketing Channels", "evidence": "Strong understanding of digital marketing channels, tools, and best practices."}, {"name": "Tools", "evidence": "Strong understanding of digital marketing channels, tools, and best practices."}, {"name": "Best Practices", "evidence": "Strong understanding of digital marketing channels, tools, and best practices."}], "skills": ["Digital Marketing Channels", "Tools", "Best Practices"]}, {"title": "Intern - GSO, New Business Sales (Fall 2026, Jul to Dec)", "company": "SGX", "salary": "面议", "location": "S00", "experience": "不限", "education": "不限", "description": "Company: Singapore Exchange\n\nLocation:\nSingapore, SG\n\nUnit: Global Sales & Origination\n\nJob Type: Intern\n\nRequisition ID: 3204\n\n**SGX Group Internship Program**\n--------------------------------\n\nWe are Asia’s leading and trusted securities and derivatives market infrastructure, operating equity, fixed income, currency and commodity markets to the highest regulatory standards. We also operate a multi-asset sustainability platform, SGX FIRST or Future in Reshaping Sustainability Together (sgx.com/first).\n\n  \n\nWe are committed to facilitating economic growth in a sustainable manner leveraging our roles as a key player in the ecosystem, a business, regulator and listed company. With climate action as a key priority, we aim to be a leading sustainable and transition financing and trading hub offering trusted, quality, end-to-end products and solutions.\n\n  \n\nAs Asia’s most international, multi-asset exchange, we provide listing, trading, clearing, settlement, depository and data services, with about 40% of listed companies and over 80% of listed bonds originating outside of Singapore. We are the world''s most liquid international market for the benchmark equity indices of China, India, Japan and ASEAN. In foreign exchange, we are Asia''s leading marketplace and most comprehensive service provider for global FX over-the-counter and futures participants. Headquartered in AAA-rated Singapore, we are globally recognised for our risk management and clearing capabilities.\n\n  \n\nBe a part of this fast-paced world where your contributions count. SGX offers you the unique experience of gaining insights into the Exchange business and the finance value chain. You will be immersed in the respective specialist functions – at SGX, we believe that our interns are involved in real-time work from Day 1.\n\n  \n\nThis internship programme is on a full-time basis. We invite you to realise your potential with us!\n\n  \n\nNote: Leave of Absence (LOA) may be required to take on the internship.\n\n**New Business Sales**\n----------------------\n\n**Short overview on the Unit/Team**\n\nSGX’s international sales organization, i.e. Global Sales & Origination (“GSO”), has a global presence with 19 overseas offices across Asia, the United States (US) and Europe. The aim is to broaden our institutional and corporate client coverage to increase participation in our multi-asset product suite. This includes Securities and Derivatives with the latter cutting across Equities, FX, Rates, Commodities and Digital Assets.\n\nGSO remains focused on activity identifying new themes to unlock revenue opportunities, particularly in the buy-side segment. With the ongoing growth of our currencies and commodities business complementing our well-established strength across Asia equities and increasing volumes traded during our overnight T+1 session, we are increasingly relevant to a broader range of global market participants.\n\nThe intern will be part of the team that has primary mandate for new clients acquisition and manages relationships with end clients (Hedge Funds, Proprietary Trading Groups, Asset Managers, Asset Owners, Bank Desks)\n\n  \n\n**Learning Outcomes**\n\nThe selected intern will have a front-row seat in understanding global markets and changing dynamics between East and West. This will be displayed through the exposures end clients are seeking as they leverage products on our platform to speculate or hedge.\n\nAs an intern, he/she will work alongside market professionals, learning the skills and knowledge necessary to be a well-rounded sales talent and how to interact and manage internal and external stakeholders.\n\nThis will be a fast-paced work environment and interns are expected to contribute effectively.\n\n  \n\n**Job Description**\n\n* Assist with desktop research on market industry, clients segmentation, sales prospects and lead generation database.\n* Assist the team to support marketing events and campaign\n* Work with Products to consolidate information relating to contract specifications, orderbook, trading insights and analysis and re-purpose them to be appropriate for institutional and corporate clients\n* Create and maintain market intelligence to keep track of client and personnel developments, thereby informing engagement plans by the sales team\n* Attend calls and meetings, assisting with briefs and post-meeting notes and follow-ups.\n* Actively using AI tools to enhance productivity, research quality and execution of the above responsibilities\n\n  \n\n**Knowledge and Skill Requirements**\n\n* Knowledge of macroeconomics, financial markets and derivative instruments\n* Excellent interpersonal skills and written and verbal communication skills in English\n* MUST be proficient in MS Office – Word, Excel and PowerPoint\n* MUST be extremely detail oriented and meticulous and comfortable with large data sets\n* Skillful in using AI tools\n* Possess intellectual curiosity and humility\n* Fast learner and pro-active\n* Self-motivated\n\n**Job Segment:** Pre-Sales, Entry Level Sales, Outside Sales, Equity, Risk Management, Sales, Finance", "requirements": "协助进行市场行业桌面研究，支持营销活动和推广计划，与产品团队合作整理合同相关信息。", "source": "Indeed", "source_warning": "部分数据源抓取失败：linkedin: 抓取超时，已跳过", "search_keyword": "Data Insights Specialist", "relevance_score": 27, "relevance_reasons": ["标题部分命中: 大数据分析 / data analyst / big data analyst / data science / business intelligence analyst / data insights specialist", "描述命中: data", "标题命中: business", "描述命中: business", "描述命中: intelligence", "描述命中: insights", "描述命中: specialist"], "market_country": "新加坡", "skills": [], "skill_evidence": []}, {"title": "Data Architect", "company": "Singtel", "salary": "面议", "location": "S00", "experience": "不限", "education": "不限", "description": "**Data Architect**\n==================\n\n**Date:** 13 Mar 2026\n\n**Location:** Singapore, Singapore\n\n**Company:** Singtel Group\n\n**Be a part of something BIG!**\n\nWe are seeking a Data Architect to own the end-to-end data architecture for operational and analytics data within data centre environments. This role spans industrial data ingestion, data modeling, analytics enablement, and embedded data governance, ensuring OT data (e.g., OPC UA, BMS, PQMS) is transformed from raw telemetry into trusted, business-ready insights.\n\nThis is a hands-on architecture role responsible for defining standards, building critical components of the data platform, and ensuring operational reliability. The role serves as the technical lead for OT data ingestion, analytics architecture, and embedded data governance.\n\n**Make an impact by**\n\n1. OT Data Engineering & Platform Architecture\n\n* Design, build, and operate OPC UA-based data ingestion pipelines from BMS, PQMS, PLCs, and sensors.\n* Implement edge and on-premises data pipelines suitable for data centre environments.\n* Manage raw and curated data layers, ensuring reliability, consistency, and performance.\n* Address time-series data challenges, including sampling rates, timestamps, aggregation strategies, and late-arriving data.\n* Monitor, troubleshoot, and optimise production pipelines.\n\n2. End-to-End Architecture Ownership\n\n* Own and evolve the end-to-end data architecture from OT source systems to analytics consumption.\n* Define and standardise:\n* + OPC UA connectivity and subscription patterns\n  + Streaming versus batch ingestion strategies\n  + Buffering, retry, and fault-tolerance mechanisms\n* Establish architectural standards for:\n* + Time-series schemas\n  + Asset and tag hierarchies\n  + Naming conventions and metadata structures\n* Define and uphold non-functional requirements across the platform, including:\n* + Availability and resilience\n  + Latency and performance\n  + Scalability\n  + Security at the OT/IT boundary\n* Provide technical leadership and guidance on data architecture and design decisions.\n\n3. Analytics Architecture & Enablement\n\n* Transform curated OT data into analytics-ready fact and dimension models.\n* Design and maintain data marts and datasets for dashboards and reporting.\n* Define and govern the analytics and semantic layer to enable consistent KPI usage.\n* Establish standards for metric calculation logic, grain definition, time windows, and aggregation rules.\n* Ensure a single source of truth for business metrics and minimise duplication.\n* Enable self-service analytics through well-documented and trusted datasets.\n\n4. Data Governance, Quality & Lineage\n\n* Embed data governance into pipelines and analytics models, including:\n* + Clear data ownership and domain attribution\n  + Technical metadata capture (tags, units, frequency, source)\n* Define and enforce data quality rules (completeness, validity, timeliness).\n* Ensure end-to-end lineage and traceability from OT source systems to business KPIs.\n* Apply access controls and data security policies aligned with OT and enterprise standards.\n* Maintain documentation to support auditability and transparency.\n* Collaborate with stakeholders to ensure data is fit for purpose.\n\n5. Collaboration & Continuous Improvement\n\n* Partner with data analysts and stakeholders to translate business requirements into scalable analytics solutions.\n* Validate analytics outputs against business intent and operational context.\n* Act as a technical advisor on data usage, constraints, and interpretation.\n* Drive continuous improvement of the data platform and analytics ecosystem.\n\n**Required Skills & Experience**\n\n* Extensive experience in data architecture, data engineering, analytics engineering, or industrial data platforms (typically gained over multiple years of progressive responsibility).\n* Strong hands-on experience with OPC UA (clients, servers, security, certificates, subscriptions).\n* Experience with BMS, PQMS, SCADA, or industrial telemetry systems.\n* Strong programming skills in Python and proficiency in SQL.\n* Experience with streaming and messaging technologies (e.g., Kafka, MQTT, or equivalent).\n* Solid understanding of time-series data modeling.\n* Experience working in on-premises or data centre environments.\n* Hands-on experience with data quality management, lineage and metadata management, and metric governance or semantic modeling.\n* Ability to balance architecture, delivery, and operational responsibilities.\n\n**Nice to Have**\n\n* Experience with hybrid cloud and on-premises data architectures.\n* Experience in energy, facilities, or data centre operations.\n* Exposure to analytics or machine learning use cases on operational data.\n* Experience defining enterprise KPIs or analytics standards.\n\n**Rewards that Go Beyond**\n\n* Flexible work arrangements\n* Full suite of health and wellness benefits\n* Ongoing training and development programs\n* Internal mobility opportunities\n\n**Your Career Growth Starts Here. Apply Now!**", "requirements": "The candidate must have extensive experience in data architecture, data engineering, analytics engineering, or industrial data platforms. They should be proficient in OPC UA and have experience with BMS, PQMS, SCADA, or industrial telemetry systems. The role requires technical leadership in defining and standardising data architecture components and ensuring data governance, quality, and security across the platform.", "source": "Indeed", "source_warning": "部分数据源抓取失败：linkedin: 抓取超时，已跳过", "search_keyword": "Big Data Analyst", "relevance_score": 27, "relevance_reasons": ["标题部分命中: 大数据分析 / data analyst / big data analyst / data science / business intelligence analyst / data insights specialist", "标题命中: data", "描述命中: data", "描述命中: analyst", "描述命中: big", "描述命中: business", "描述命中: insights"], "market_country": "新加坡", "skill_evidence": [{"name": "OPC UA", "evidence": "Design, build, and operate OPC UA-based data ingestion pipelines from BMS, PQMS, PLCs, and sensors."}, {"name": "Data Ingestion Pipelines", "evidence": "Design, build, and operate OPC UA-based data ingestion pipelines from BMS, PQMS, PLCs, and sensors."}, {"name": "Time-series Data", "evidence": "Address time-series data challenges, including sampling rates, timestamps, aggregation strategies, and late-arriving..."}, {"name": "Data Governance", "evidence": "Embed data governance into pipelines and analytics models, including clear data ownership and domain attribution."}, {"name": "Data Quality Rules", "evidence": "Define and enforce data quality rules (completeness, validity, timeliness)."}, {"name": "Data Lineage", "evidence": "Ensure end-to-end lineage and traceability from OT source systems to business KPIs."}, {"name": "Data Security Policies", "evidence": "Apply access controls and data security policies aligned with OT and enterprise standards."}, {"name": "Data Marts", "evidence": "Design and maintain data marts and datasets for dashboards and reporting."}, {"name": "Datasets For Dashboards And Reporting", "evidence": "Design and maintain data marts and datasets for dashboards and reporting."}, {"name": "Metric Calculation Logic", "evidence": "Define and govern the analytics and semantic layer to enable consistent KPI usage."}, {"name": "Grain Definition", "evidence": "Establish standards for metric calculation logic, grain definition, time windows, and aggregation rules."}, {"name": "Aggregation Rules", "evidence": "Establish standards for metric calculation logic, grain definition, time windows, and aggregation rules."}, {"name": "Edge And On-premises Data Pipelines", "evidence": "Implement edge and on-premises data pipelines suitable for data centre environments."}], "skills": ["OPC UA", "Data Ingestion Pipelines", "Time-series Data", "Data Governance", "Data Quality Rules", "Data Lineage", "Data Security Policies", "Data Marts", "Datasets For Dashboards And Reporting", "Metric Calculation Logic", "Grain Definition", "Aggregation Rules", "Edge And On-premises Data Pipelines"]}, {"title": "Senior Data Solution Architect", "company": "SmartOSC Corp", "salary": "面议", "location": "Downtown Core", "experience": "不限", "education": "博士及以上", "description": "**ABOUT US**: With 20 years in operation, SmartOSC is an industry-leading digital transformation agency of 1000+ experts across countries, including Vietnam, Australia, Singapore, Japan, Thailand, Indonesia, Korea, the US, and the UK. Deep experience across most enterprise platforms and technology stacks has made SmartOSC a trusted partner for leading brands and financial institutions worldwide.\n\nWith a “people-centric” strategy, we always strive to enable employees to grow sustainably and pursue their passion with a transparent career path.\n\nFor additional information about SmartOSC, please visit: https://www.smartosc.com/\n\n**Senior Data Solution Architect**\n\n**Location:** 32 Pekin Street, #05-01, Singapore 048762\n\n**Role Overview:**\n\nWe are looking for a Senior Data Solutions Architect who can design and lead end-to-end cloud data platforms for enterprise clients, while actively engaging in client-facing discussions, translating complex business needs into scalable data architectures, and supporting presales and solution consulting activities\n\n***1. RESPONSIBILITIES:***\n\n● Design and lead the implementation of scalable data architecture and data platform solutions to support complex business needs in the airline industry.\n\n● Define and translate business requirements into data architecture, data models, and system design, ensuring alignment with business objectives.\n\n● Support presales activities by working with sales and consulting teams to design end-to-end data platform solutions for prospective clients.\n\n● Participate in client meetings, workshops, and technical discussions to understand data challenges and propose architecture solutions.\n\n● Design modern data architectures, including data lakes, data warehouses, and real-time data pipelines using cloud platforms (AWS, Azure, or GCP).\n\n● Define data integration strategies across multiple systems (e.g., operational systems, customer platforms, third-party sources).\n\n● Establish data governance, data quality, and data security frameworks to ensure reliable and compliant data management.\n\n● Contribute to solution design, technical proposals, and architecture blueprints, helping secure project approval and accelerate contract signing.\n\n● Collaborate with data engineers and analysts to ensure successful implementation and scalability of the data platform.\n\n● Communicate complex architecture concepts in a clear and business-friendly manner to both technical and non-technical stakeholders.\n\n● Stay up to date with the latest developments in data architecture, cloud data platforms, and big data technologies.\n\n***2. REQUIREMENTS***\n\n● Master’s or PhD degree in Computer Science, Information Systems, Engineering, or a related field.\n\n● 8+ years of experience in data architecture, data engineering, or large-scale data platform design.\n\n● Strong expertise in data architecture design, including data lakes, data warehouses, and modern data platforms.\n\n● Proven experience with cloud platforms such as AWS, Azure, or GCP, and related data services (e.g., S3, Redshift, BigQuery, Synapse).\n\n● Strong knowledge of data modelling (conceptual, logical, physical) and data integration patterns (ETL/ELT, streaming, APIs).\n\n● Experience designing and implementing end-to-end data solutions, from data ingestion to storage, transformation, and consumption.\n\n● Solid understanding of data governance, data quality, and data security best practices.\n\n● Strong communication in English and presentation skills, with the ability to explain architecture concepts to business stakeholders and clients.\n\n● Experience supporting client-facing engagements, presales activities, or solution architecture consulting is highly preferred.\n\n● Experience in the airline, aviation, or travel industry is a strong advantage, particularly in handling operational, customer, or transactional data.\n\n● Ability to work effectively with cross-functional teams, including sales, consulting, engineering, and business stakeholders.\n\n***3. BENEFITS***\n\n*At SmartOSC, we offer the best to your values*\n\n● Attractive salary package: up to SGD 16,000.\n\n● Salary review twice a year\n\n● Flexible working hour\n\n● Working in One of the largest digital transformation agencies – A professional English environment\n\n● Firm’s Certified Qualifications Sponsorship for career development\n\n● Annual company trip inside or outside Vietnam\n\n● Free entertainment parties: Birthday party, Anniversary party, Sum-up Party, Year-End Party, etc.\n\n***4. TO APPLY***\n\n*Please submit your CV to kiennt4@smartosc.com with the following information:*\n\n● Job Application Letter with “**Senior Data Solution Architect**” in the subject line.\n\n● Updated CV in English, including your contact e-mail, phone number and salary expectations.\n\nJob Type: Full-time\n\nPay: Up to $16,000.00 per month\n\nBenefits:\n\n* Additional leave\n* Employee assistance programme\n* Flexible schedule\n* Health insurance\n* Professional development\n* Work from home\n\nWork Location: In person", "requirements": "Design and implement scalable data solutions for enterprise clients, support presales activities by designing data platform solutions, and have experience with cloud platforms like AWS, Azure, or GCP.", "source": "Indeed", "source_warning": "部分数据源抓取失败：linkedin: 抓取超时，已跳过", "search_keyword": "Big Data Analyst", "relevance_score": 27, "relevance_reasons": ["标题部分命中: 大数据分析 / data analyst / big data analyst / data science / business intelligence analyst / data insights specialist", "标题命中: data", "描述命中: data", "描述命中: analyst", "描述命中: big", "描述命中: science", "描述命中: business"], "market_country": "新加坡", "skill_evidence": [{"name": "Data Architecture Design", "evidence": "Design and lead the implementation of scalable data architecture and data platform solutions to support complex busin..."}, {"name": "Cloud Platforms", "evidence": "Design modern data architectures, including data lakes, data warehouses, and real-time data pipelines using cloud pla..."}, {"name": "Data Integration Patterns", "evidence": "Strong knowledge of data modelling (conceptual, logical, physical) and data integration patterns (ETL/ELT, streaming,..."}, {"name": "Data Modelling", "evidence": "Strong knowledge of data modelling (conceptual, logical, physical) and data integration patterns (ETL/ELT, streaming,..."}, {"name": "Data Governance", "evidence": "Establish data governance, data quality, and data security frameworks to ensure reliable and compliant data management."}, {"name": "Data Quality", "evidence": "Establish data governance, data quality, and data security frameworks to ensure reliable and compliant data management."}, {"name": "Data Security", "evidence": "Establish data governance, data quality, and data security frameworks to ensure reliable and compliant data management."}], "skills": ["Data Architecture Design", "Cloud Platforms", "Data Integration Patterns", "Data Modelling", "Data Governance", "Data Quality", "Data Security"]}, {"title": "Specialist II, Purchasing", "company": "ASM", "salary": "面议", "location": "S00", "experience": "不限", "education": "本科及以上", "description": "**Step into a career with ASM, where cutting edge technology meets collaborative culture.**\n\nFor over 55 years ASM has been ahead of what''s next, at the forefront of innovation and what''s technologically possible. With more than 4,500 ASMers representing 70 nationalities, our people and our advanced semiconductor devices are playing a crucial role in trends such as 5G, cloud computing, AI, and autonomous driving. But we''re more than just a tech company. We value diversity, inclusion and sustainability as we strive to make a positive impact on the world. Our development programs help support your growth, shaping your future and pushing the boundaries of innovation to unleash potential.\n\n**Job''s mission**\n\nAs a Purchasing Specialist II, you will play an important role in strengthening the flow of materials that keeps our advanced manufacturing running smoothly. You will turn data into insights that help drive timely purchasing decisions, improve supplier performance, and ensure continuity across our global supply chain. Your work directly supports ASM''s mission by enabling operational excellence that powers the innovations shaping the future of semiconductor technology.\n\n**What you will be working on**\n\n* Extract, analyze, and report data using SAP Business Intelligence, Power BI, and internal tools to support purchasing operations.\n* Deliver accurate and timely daily and weekly reports to guide operational decisions.\n* Conduct deep‑dive analyses to identify supply chain improvement opportunities.\n* Monitor internal KPI performance and highlight trends that support operational excellence.\n* Follow up on post‑implementation actions to ensure sustained improvements.\n* Support issue resolution using data‑driven insights and system diagnostics.\n* Manage direct purchasing tasks, including PO creation, issuance, confirmation, rescheduling, and cancellations.\n* Ensure materials are delivered on time to meet production needs.\n* Align supplier delivery plans with production and customer demand.\n* Ensure continuity of supply during product transfers.\n* Resolve vendor issues including invoice discrepancies, goods receipt exceptions, and returns.\n* Review and improve daily work methods.\n* Build and maintain strong supplier relationships.\n* Monitor and drive supplier on‑time delivery (OTD) performance.\n* Expedite supply and collaborate with cross‑functional teams to close material gaps.\n* Partner with planning teams and project managers to manage critical shortages.\n* Manage supplier commit updates in Ariba with accuracy and timeliness.\n* Liaise between ASM account/supplier management teams and suppliers for delivery alignment.\n* Coordinate Open Order Reports and ensure timely supplier confirmations.\n* Maintain clear and proactive communication with internal stakeholders and suppliers.\n* Support additional supply chain or cross‑functional projects as assigned.\n\n  \n\n**What we are looking for**\n\n* Bachelor''s Degree in Supply Chain, Engineering, Business, or a related field.\n* Proficiency in Microsoft Office applications, particularly Excel, Word, and PowerPoint.\n* Strong analytical mindset and problem‑solving skills.\n* Effective written and verbal communication skills.\n* Ability to thrive in a fast‑paced, collaborative work environment.\n* Detail‑oriented with strong accountability when managing data and commitments.\n* Strong coordination skills across internal and external stakeholders.\n* Ability to work effectively in a multicultural environment.\n\n**What sets you apart**\n\n* Familiarity with SAP S4/HANA and Power BI.\n* Experience working with suppliers or in a supply chain operations environment.\n* Proven ability to manage multiple stakeholders.\n* Self‑driven, adaptable, and passionate about continuous improvement.\n\n**Apply today to be part of what''s next.**\n\nWe make the tech that enables the chips in devices which improve lives around the world. We do this with an eye to the future, pushing the boundaries of what''s possible through cutting-edge innovation, and driving the next wave of technological breakthroughs that shape how we live, work, and connect.\n\nTo learn more about ASM, find us at asm.com and on LinkedIn, Facebook, Instagram, X and YouTube.\n\n*ASM is an equal opportunity employer and considers qualified applicants for employment without regard to race, color, religion, age, nationality, social or ethnic origin, sexual orientation, gender, gender identify or expression, marital status, pregnancy, political affiliation, disability, genetic information, veteran status, or any other characteristic protected by law.*", "requirements": "Bachelor''s Degree in Supply Chain, Engineering, Business, or a related field. Proficiency in Microsoft Office applications, particularly Excel, Word, and PowerPoint. Familiarity with SAP S4/HANA and Power BI.", "source": "Indeed", "source_warning": "部分数据源抓取失败：linkedin: 抓取超时，已跳过", "search_keyword": "Data Insights Specialist", "relevance_score": 27, "relevance_reasons": ["标题部分命中: 大数据分析 / data analyst / big data analyst / data science / business intelligence analyst / data insights specialist", "描述命中: data", "描述命中: business", "描述命中: intelligence", "描述命中: insights", "标题命中: specialist", "描述命中: specialist"], "market_country": "新加坡", "skill_evidence": [{"name": "SAP Business Intelligence", "evidence": "Extract, analyze, and report data using SAP Business Intelligence, Power BI, and internal tools to support purchasing..."}, {"name": "Power BI", "evidence": "Extract, analyze, and report data using SAP Business Intelligence, Power BI, and internal tools to support purchasing..."}, {"name": "Ariba", "evidence": "Manage supplier commit updates in Ariba with accuracy and timeliness."}], "skills": ["SAP Business Intelligence", "Power BI", "Ariba"]}, {"title": "AI Engineer (Data and Analytics Department)", "company": "EMA Energy Market Authority", "salary": "面议", "location": "SG", "experience": "不限", "education": "硕士及以上", "description": "**[What the role is]**\n\nThe role is responsible for developing and operationalising AI solutions to support critical energy sector operations and regulatory functions. The incumbent will collaborate with data scientists and engineers to design, test, and deploy AI/ML models across the full lifecycle, ensuring solutions are production-ready and scalable. The role also establishes and manages robust MLOps practices, including CI/CD/CT pipelines, automated retraining, performance monitoring, and model governance to maintain reliability and safety. In addition, the incumbent provides technical leadership and stakeholder engagement, translating complex AI insights into actionable outcomes while aligning business objectives, technical feasibility, and compliance requirements.\n\n**[What you will be working on]**\n\nResponsibilities:\n\n(1) **AI Solution Development** : Work collaboratively with Data Scientists and Data Engineers to design, test, and implement AI/ML models for EMA''s diverse use cases across the complete AI/ML lifecycle. Lead the development of production-ready AI solutions that can be deployed reliably, timely, and consistently to support critical energy sector operations and regulatory functions.\n\n(2) **MLOps and Production Lifecycle Management** : Establish and maintain comprehensive MLOps foundations covering the end-to-end journey from code commit to model retirement. Design continuous integration, continuous deployment, and continuous training (CI/CD/CT) pipelines whilst managing version control across code, data, and models. Implement automated retraining infrastructure with performance monitoring, data drift detection, and guardrail systems to ensure models remain safe and effective in critical infrastructure environments.\n\n(3) **Stakeholder Management and Technical Leadership** : Lead engagement and alignment initiatives with senior management, data scientists, business users, and vendor/IT teams. Translate complex AI outputs into actionable insights and business intelligence for non-technical audiences. Bridge communications between diverse stakeholders to identify optimal trade-offs between business outcomes, system performance limitations, and compliance requirements.\n\n**[What we are looking for]**\n\nRequirements:\n\n* Higher Tietiary background in Computer Science, Mathematics, Physics, Data Science or related quantitative field. Specialised AI certifications advantageous\n* Minimum 5-10 years of professional experience developing, deploying, and maintaining enterprise-grade AI/ML models in production environments\n* Demonstrable experience across the full MLOps lifecycle\n* Expert proficiency in AI/ML modelling including supervised/unsupervised learning, deep learning, and reinforcement learning\n* Advanced programming skills in Python and frameworks such as PyTorch, TensorFlow, Pandas, and equivalent technologies\n* Comprehensive knowledge of MLOps tools and practices for automated model training, testing, deployment, and monitoring\n* Experience with model optimisation techniques including quantisation, pruning, and knowledge distillation\n* Exceptional stakeholder management abilities with proven track record of translating technical concepts for diverse audiences\n* Systems thinking approach to problem-solving within complex technical constraints\n* Independent professional with excellent interpersonal and communication skills\n* Innovative mindset with ability to identify optimal technical trade-offs for decision-making", "requirements": "The candidate must have a higher tertiary background in relevant quantitative fields and at least 5-10 years of experience in developing, deploying, and maintaining AI/ML models in production environments. They should demonstrate expertise in the full MLOps lifecycle and possess advanced programming skills in Python and associated frameworks.", "source": "Indeed", "source_warning": "部分数据源抓取失败：linkedin: 抓取超时，已跳过", "search_keyword": "Data Analyst", "relevance_score": 27, "relevance_reasons": ["标题部分命中: 大数据分析 / data analyst / big data analyst / data science / business intelligence analyst / data insights specialist", "标题命中: data", "描述命中: data", "描述命中: science", "描述命中: business", "描述命中: intelligence", "描述命中: insights"], "market_country": "新加坡", "skill_evidence": [{"name": "AI/ML modelling", "evidence": "Expert proficiency in AI/ML modelling including supervised/unsupervised learning, deep learning, and reinforcement le..."}, {"name": "MLOps", "evidence": "Establish and manage robust MLOps practices, including CI/CD/CT pipelines, automated retraining, performance monitori..."}, {"name": "Python", "evidence": "Advanced programming skills in Python and frameworks such as PyTorch, TensorFlow, Pandas, and equivalent technologies"}, {"name": "PyTorch", "evidence": "Advanced programming skills in Python and frameworks such as PyTorch, TensorFlow, Pandas, and equivalent technologies"}, {"name": "TensorFlow", "evidence": "Advanced programming skills in Python and frameworks such as PyTorch, TensorFlow, Pandas, and equivalent technologies"}, {"name": "Pandas", "evidence": "Advanced programming skills in Python and frameworks such as PyTorch, TensorFlow, Pandas, and equivalent technologies"}, {"name": "Model Optimisation", "evidence": "Experience with model optimisation techniques including quantisation, pruning, and knowledge distillation"}, {"name": "CI/CD/CT pipelines", "evidence": "Design continuous integration, continuous deployment, and continuous training (CI/CD/CT) pipelines whilst managing ve..."}, {"name": "Automated Retraining", "evidence": "Implement automated retraining infrastructure with performance monitoring, data drift detection, and guardrail system..."}, {"name": "Performance Monitoring", "evidence": "Implement automated retraining infrastructure with performance monitoring, data drift detection, and guardrail system..."}, {"name": "Data Drift Detection", "evidence": "Implement automated retraining infrastructure with performance monitoring, data drift detection, and guardrail system..."}, {"name": "Model Governance", "evidence": "Establish and manage robust MLOps practices, including CI/CD/CT pipelines, automated retraining, performance monitori..."}, {"name": "Version Control", "evidence": "Design continuous integration, continuous deployment, and continuous training (CI/CD/CT) pipelines whilst managing ve..."}], "skills": ["AI/ML modelling", "MLOps", "Python", "PyTorch", "TensorFlow", "Pandas", "Model Optimisation", "CI/CD/CT pipelines", "Automated Retraining", "Performance Monitoring", "Data Drift Detection", "Model Governance", "Version Control"]}, {"title": "Associate Solutions Analyst", "company": "Nanyang Technological University", "salary": "面议", "location": "SG", "experience": "不限", "education": "硕士及以上", "description": "The Associate Solutions Analyst supports the design and implementation of automation, data, and analytics solutions that improve operational efficiency and data-driven decision-making across Nanyang Business School.\n\nWorking closely with the Solutions Analyst / Architect and internal stakeholders, the role assists in analysing business processes, preparing data for analytics, developing automation workflows, and supporting the delivery of digital solutions across academic and administrative functions.\n\nThis role provides an opportunity for early-career professionals to gain hands-on experience in enterprise data platforms, automation technologies, and analytics within a large and complex organisational environment.\n\n**Key Responsibilities:**\n\n**Business Process & Requirements Support**\n\n* Assist in documenting business processes and operational workflows across academic and administrative units\n* Support the gathering and documentation of business and system requirements\n* Prepare process maps, functional documentation, and solution specifications\n* Assist in identifying opportunities to improve efficiency through process improvements and automation\n\n**Automation & Digital Solutions**\n\n* Assist in developing automation scripts, workflows, and data pipelines\n* Support the implementation of workflow automation, robotic process automation (RPA), or document processing solutions\n* Conduct testing and validation of automation solutions prior to deployment\n* Support monitoring and maintenance of deployed automation solutions\n\n**Data & Analytics Support**\n\n* Assist in extracting, cleaning, and preparing datasets for reporting and analytics\n* Write SQL queries to retrieve and transform data from internal systems\n* Support the development of dashboards and reports using business intelligence tools (e.g. Power BI)\n* Assist in maintaining datasets, data models, and reporting pipelines\n\n**Solution Delivery Support**\n\n* Support the solution delivery lifecycle including documentation, testing (SIT/UAT), and deployment activities\n* Assist with coordination of testing activities with stakeholders\n* Maintain user documentation and system guides\n* Provide basic support and troubleshooting for implemented solutions\n\n**Requirements:**\n\n**Educational Qualifications**\n\n* Bachelor’s Degree in Computer Science, Information Systems, Data Science, Software Engineering, Computer Engineering, or a related discipline.\n* Entry level candidates are welcome to apply.\n\n**Skills & Knowledge**\n\n**Technical Skills**\n\n* Basic proficiency in programming languages such as Python or similar\n* Working knowledge of SQL and relational databases\n* Familiarity with data analytics and data visualisation tools (e.g. Power BI or similar BI platforms)\n* Basic understanding of automation technologies or workflow tools is advantageous\n\n**Professional Skills**\n\n* Strong analytical and problem-solving abilities\n* Good communication and documentation skills\n* Ability to work collaboratively with both technical and non-technical stakeholders\n* Strong attention to detail and commitment to data accuracy\n\n**Personal Attributes**\n\n* Curious and proactive learner with an interest in data and technology\n* Ability to manage multiple tasks and meet deadlines\n* Collaborative team player with a willingness to learn new technologies and tools\n* Organised and detail-oriented in approach to work\n\nWe regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.\n\nHiring Institution: NTU", "requirements": "Candidates should have basic proficiency in programming languages such as Python or similar, working knowledge of SQL and relational databases, and familiarity with data analytics and data visualisation tools like Power BI. A basic understanding of automation technologies or workflow tools is advantageous.", "source": "Indeed", "source_warning": "部分数据源抓取失败：linkedin: 抓取超时，已跳过", "search_keyword": "Data Analyst", "relevance_score": 27, "relevance_reasons": ["标题部分命中: 大数据分析 / data analyst / big data analyst / data science / business intelligence analyst / data insights specialist", "描述命中: data", "标题命中: analyst", "描述命中: analyst", "描述命中: science", "描述命中: business", "描述命中: intelligence"], "market_country": "新加坡", "skill_evidence": [{"name": "Python", "evidence": "Basic proficiency in programming languages such as Python or similar"}, {"name": "SQL", "evidence": "Working knowledge of SQL and relational databases"}, {"name": "Power BI", "evidence": "Support the development of dashboards and reports using business intelligence tools (e.g. Power BI)"}, {"name": "Automation Technologies", "evidence": "Basic understanding of automation technologies or workflow tools is advantageous"}, {"name": "Workflow Tools", "evidence": "Support the implementation of workflow automation, robotic process automation (RPA), or document processing solutions"}], "skills": ["Python", "SQL", "Power BI", "Automation Technologies", "Workflow Tools"]}, {"title": "Data Engineer / Analytics Engineer (Intern)", "company": "", "salary": "面议", "location": "S00", "experience": "不限", "education": "不限", "description": "#### **About the Role**\n\nWe’re looking for a Data Engineering / Analytics Intern who wants to build reliable data systems—not just dashboards.\n\nYou’ll work on designing and maintaining data pipelines for logs, usage, quality metrics, and customer analytics in a fast-moving environment where schemas and questions evolve constantly. This means ensuring data is accurate, trustworthy, and useful for decision-making across product and business teams.\n\nYou’ll collaborate closely with founders, product, and engineering to turn raw data into actionable insights. Your work will directly impact experimentation, reporting, and how the company makes decisions.\n\nIf you enjoy working with messy data, building systems end-to-end, and improving data quality, this role will push you to grow quickly.\n\n##### **What You Will Do**\n\nDesign and implement ETL/ELT pipelines for logs, usage, and analytics  \nBuild and maintain transformation layers (dbt or similar)  \nSet up data quality checks and monitoring for key datasets  \nModel data in warehouses or lakes for analytics use cases  \nSupport experimentation, reporting, and feedback loops with reliable data  \nEnsure privacy-aware handling of sensitive data (PII)  \nDocument data models, metrics, and pipelines clearly\n\n##### **What We’re Looking For**\n\nStrong SQL fundamentals  \nFamiliarity with ETL/ELT workflows and tools  \nExposure to dbt or similar transformation frameworks  \nExperience with a data warehouse or data lake  \nBasic understanding of batch vs real-time data processing  \nAwareness of data privacy and compliance considerations\n\n##### **Founding Mindset**\n\nYou think in terms of decisions enabled, not just pipelines built  \nYou ask “who will use this and why?” before modeling data  \nYou take ownership of data reliability and usability  \nYou balance speed of iteration with long-term maintainability  \nYou proactively identify and fix data quality issues\n\n##### **Bonus**\n\nExperience with experimentation or product analytics  \nExposure to BI tools or metric layers  \nExperience working with event-based or high-volume data\n\n##### **What Success Looks Like**\n\nWithin 4–6 weeks, you should be able to:  \nOwn a part of the data stack (e.g., usage or quality metrics)  \nShip pipelines that are used for real product or business decisions  \nCatch and prevent at least one major data quality issue  \nImprove clarity and consistency of key metrics\n\n##### **What You’ll Get**\n\nHands-on experience building and owning a modern data stack  \nDirect collaboration with founders, product, and engineering teams  \nOwnership of meaningful data systems and pipelines  \nA portfolio of data models, pipelines, and analytics work  \nA strong pathway into data engineering, analytics, or product data roles\n\n##### **Who This Is Not For**\n\nIf you only want to write ad hoc queries  \nIf you avoid ambiguity around metrics and definitions  \nIf you prefer static, slow-changing data environments  \nIf you’re looking for a low-pressure internship\n\n##### **Who Will Thrive Here**\n\nBuilders who treat data as a product  \nEngineers who think in end-to-end data flows  \nCalm debuggers of broken pipelines and inconsistent metrics  \nHigh-agency individuals who take ownership of data quality and outcomes\n\n##### **About the Company**\n\nWe’re building the speech intelligence layer for Southeast Asia—turning real-world, accented, code-switched speech into structured, usable outputs for businesses.", "requirements": "具备扎实的SQL基础，熟悉ETL/ELT工作流程和工具，有dbt或类似转换框架的经验，熟悉数据仓库或数据湖，了解数据隐私和合规考虑。能够设计和实现数据管道，设置数据质量检查和监控，建模数据以支持分析用例，并确保数据的准确性和可靠性。", "source": "Indeed", "source_warning": "部分数据源抓取失败：linkedin: 抓取超时，已跳过", "search_keyword": "Data Analyst", "relevance_score": 27, "relevance_reasons": ["标题部分命中: 大数据分析 / data analyst / big data analyst / data science / business intelligence analyst / data insights specialist", "标题命中: data", "描述命中: data", "描述命中: big", "描述命中: business", "描述命中: intelligence", "描述命中: insights"], "market_country": "新加坡", "skill_evidence": [{"name": "SQL", "evidence": "Strong SQL fundamentals"}, {"name": "ETL/ELT workflows and tools", "evidence": "Familiarity with ETL/ELT workflows and tools"}, {"name": "dbt Or Similar Transformation Frameworks", "evidence": "Exposure to dbt or similar transformation frameworks"}, {"name": "Data Warehouse Or Data Lake", "evidence": "Experience with a data warehouse or data lake"}, {"name": "Data Quality Checks And Monitoring", "evidence": "Set up data quality checks and monitoring for key datasets"}, {"name": "Data Modeling", "evidence": "Model data in warehouses or lakes for analytics use cases"}, {"name": "Data Privacy And Compliance Considerations", "evidence": "Ensure privacy-aware handling of sensitive data (PII)"}, {"name": "Experimentation Or Product Analytics", "evidence": "Experience with experimentation or product analytics"}, {"name": "BI Tools Or Metric Layers", "evidence": "Exposure to BI tools or metric layers"}, {"name": "Event-based Or High-volume Data", "evidence": "Experience working with event-based or high-volume data"}], "skills": ["SQL", "ETL/ELT workflows and tools", "dbt Or Similar Transformation Frameworks", "Data Warehouse Or Data Lake", "Data Quality Checks And Monitoring", "Data Modeling", "Data Privacy And Compliance Considerations", "Experimentation Or Product Analytics", "BI Tools Or Metric Layers", "Event-based Or High-volume Data"]}, {"title": "Data Engineer Intern", "company": "Razer", "salary": "面议", "location": "Queenstown", "experience": "不限", "education": "不限", "description": "Joining Razer will place you on a global mission to revolutionize the way the world games. Razer is **a place to do great work**, offering you the opportunity to make an impact globally while working across a global team located across 5 continents. Razer is also **a great place to work,** providing you the unique, gamer-centric #LifeAtRazer experience that will put you in an accelerated growth, both personally and professionally.\n\n**Job Responsibilities :**\n--------------------------\n\nJoin our Big Data team as a Data Engineering Intern and help power the data foundation behind advanced analytics and AI/ML solutions. This role sits at the intersection of data engineering, cloud infrastructure, and artificial intelligence.  \n  \nYou will collaborate closely with data engineers, data scientists, analytics engineers, and data product managers to design, optimize, and scale modern data pipelines that fuel AI models, business intelligence, and data-driven decision-making across the organisation.  \n  \nThis internship offers hands-on experience with real production systems, modern data stack technologies, and AI-enablement workflows in a cloud-native environment.\n\n**Pre-requisites:**\n\n* Strong interest in Data Engineering, Cloud Technologies and AI/ML applications\n* Proficiency in Python, SQL. Knowledge in Golang is a plus.\n* Exposure to cloud technologies (Amazon Web Services, Google Cloud Platform)\n* Exposure to orchestration tools (Airflow)\n* Exposure to business intelligence tool (Superset, PowerBI, Tableau)\n* Ability to work independently and collaboratively in a fast-paced environment\n\n**Learning Objectives:**\n\nBy the end of the internship, you will gain practical experience in building AI-ready data systems using industry best practices and modern data technologies.\n\n**Learning Outcomes:**\n\n* Modern Data Warehousing & Lakehouse Architecture in the cloud (AWS)\n* Pipeline Design Patterns using ELT\n* Data transformation tools (DBT)\n* Infrastructure as Code (Terraform)\n* Workflow orchestration (Airflow)\n* CI/CD for Data Engineering\n* Performance Optimization & Data Quality Engineering\n* Documentation and communication of technical solutions\n* Collaboration with data engineers, analytics engineers, data analysts, data scientists\n\n**Pre-Requisites :**\n--------------------\n\nRazer is proud to be an Equal Opportunity Employer. We believe that diverse teams drive better ideas, better products, and a stronger culture. We are committed to providing an inclusive, respectful, and fair workplace for every employee across all the countries we operate in. We do not discriminate on the basis of race, ethnicity, colour, nationality, ancestry, religion, age, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, disability, marital status, or any other characteristic protected under local laws. Where needed, we provide reasonable accommodations - including for disability or religious practices - to ensure every team member can perform and contribute at their best.\n\n**Are you game?**", "requirements": "Strong interest in Data Engineering, Cloud Technologies and AI/ML applications. Exposure to cloud technologies (Amazon Web Services, Google Cloud Platform). Exposure to orchestration tools (Airflow). Exposure to business intelligence tools (Superset, PowerBI, Tableau). Ability to work independently and collaboratively in a fast-paced environment.", "source": "Indeed", "source_warning": "部分数据源抓取失败：linkedin: 抓取超时，已跳过", "search_keyword": "Big Data Analyst", "relevance_score": 27, "relevance_reasons": ["标题部分命中: 大数据分析 / data analyst / big data analyst / data science / business intelligence analyst / data insights specialist", "标题命中: data", "描述命中: data", "描述命中: analyst", "描述命中: big", "描述命中: business", "描述命中: intelligence"], "market_country": "新加坡", "skill_evidence": [{"name": "Python", "evidence": "Proficiency in Python, SQL. Knowledge in Golang is a plus."}, {"name": "SQL", "evidence": "Proficiency in Python, SQL. Knowledge in Golang is a plus."}, {"name": "Golang", "evidence": "Proficiency in Python, SQL. Knowledge in Golang is a plus."}, {"name": "Amazon Web Services", "evidence": "Exposure to cloud technologies (Amazon Web Services, Google Cloud Platform)"}, {"name": "Google Cloud Platform", "evidence": "Exposure to cloud technologies (Amazon Web Services, Google Cloud Platform)"}, {"name": "Airflow", "evidence": "Exposure to orchestration tools (Airflow)"}, {"name": "Superset", "evidence": "Exposure to business intelligence tool (Superset, PowerBI, Tableau)"}, {"name": "Power BI", "evidence": "Exposure to business intelligence tool (Superset, PowerBI, Tableau)"}, {"name": "Tableau", "evidence": "Exposure to business intelligence tool (Superset, PowerBI, Tableau)"}, {"name": "Terraform", "evidence": "Infrastructure as Code (Terraform)"}, {"name": "dbt", "evidence": "Data transformation tools (DBT)"}, {"name": "CI/CD", "evidence": "CI/CD for Data Engineering"}, {"name": "Performance Optimization", "evidence": "Performance Optimization & Data Quality Engineering"}, {"name": "Data Quality Engineering", "evidence": "Performance Optimization & Data Quality Engineering"}], "skills": ["Python", "SQL", "Golang", "Amazon Web Services", "Google Cloud Platform", "Airflow", "Superset", "Power BI", "Tableau", "Terraform", "dbt", "CI/CD", "Performance Optimization", "Data Quality Engineering"]}, {"title": "Senior Analyst, Markets, Sales Support", "company": "Standard Chartered Bank", "salary": "面议", "location": "S00", "experience": "不限", "education": "不限", "description": "**Requisition Number:** 50583\n\n**Job Location:** Singapore, SGP\n\n**Global Grade:** Band 7\n\n**Work Type:** Hybrid Working\n\n**Employment Type:** Permanent\n\n**Posting Start Date:** 17/03/2026\n\n**Posting End Date:** 17/04/2026\n\n**:**\n\n**Job Summary**\n\nThe Senior Analyst, Markets Sales Support, plays a pivotal role in enabling Global Markets Sales teams to deliver exceptional service and operational excellence. Sitting within the Markets Client & Sales Solutions Group (CSSG), the role provides high quality pre trade and post trade support, ensures smooth trade lifecycle execution, and drives continuous improvement across processes, controls, and client engagement.\n\nThe role partners closely with Sales, Operations, COO teams, and various internal stakeholders globally to deliver consistent, client centric outcomes and ensure adherence to regulatory and operational risk standards.\n\n**Key Responsibilities**\n\n* Maintain a strong understanding of Global Markets and the broader CIB client landscape.\n* Provide comprehensive pre‑ and post‑trade support to Global Markets Sales and clients globally.\n* Strengthen relationships with Sales teams by delivering proactive, client‑focused support.\n* Drive global consistency by collaborating with hubs (GBS) and regional teams to harmonise processes.\n* Continuously adapt to regulatory, infrastructure, and business environment changes.\n* Demonstrate a growth mindset, actively identifying areas for enhancement and delivering improvements.\n* Champion and execute the vision of the Markets Sales Support function.\n* Lead and participate in continuous process improvement initiatives.\n* Understand Sales and client requirements to resolve backlog items and operational obstacles.\n* Act as the first point of contact for client and Sales queries, including onboarding coordination and operational questions.\n* Support Sales on trade lifecycle monitoring/activities (e.g., novation processing, event reporting such as option expiry, fixing notices).\n* Support trade booking activities for specific markets and products.\n* Collaborate across CSSG, Sales, COO teams, and Operations on new business initiatives, including new product enablement and control design.\n* Ensure timely, accurate handling of all queries by engaging relevant teams and driving resolution.\n* Coordinate and support client testing for new product rollouts or system changes.\n* Analyse MIS data to identify recurring issues, recommend corrective actions, and enhance process reliability.\n\n* Ensure Group Risk Management standards are being maintained / adhered to\n* Engage Risk, Legal & Compliance and Operational Risk as appropriate on escalated items relating to Risk Management\n* Adherence to Ops Risk Framework standards of implementation and process management:\n* Continuous review of procedures and booking model\n* All Markets Operations functions and Markets Ops MT\n* Markets Sales, Trading & COO\n* Finance & Product Controls\n* Client Coverage RMs and Client Managers\n* Onboarding teams\n* Markets and Country / Regional Legal / Compliance\n* Other CIB or Bank teams as required to support client initiatives\n* Tier 1/Tier Clients in segment and / or region as directed by the client tiering list (owned by Sales COO) and other Markets Clients and segments as required\n* Vendors, Market infrastructure and Service Providers (e.g., Murex, FX ALL, BBG, etc.)\n* Correspondent Banks, Custodians\n* Consultants and Industry / Trade Bodies\n* Display exemplary conduct and live by the Group’s Values and Code of Conduct.\n* Take personal responsibility for embedding the highest standards of ethics, including regulatory and business conduct, across Standard Chartered Bank. This includes understanding and ensuring compliance with, in letter and spirit, all applicable laws, regulations, guidelines and the Group Code of Conduct.\n* Effectively and collaboratively identify, escalate, mitigate, and resolve risk, conduct and compliance matters.\n* Lead the Markets Sales Support team to achieve the outcomes set out in the Bank’s Conduct Principles.\n* Embed the Group’s values and code of conduct to ensure that adherence with the highest standards of ethics, and compliance with relevant policies, processes and regulations among employees form part of the culture\n\n**Our ideal Candidate**\n\n* 5+ years’ experience in Global Markets, Markets Sales Support, Trade Lifecycle, or Markets Operations, ideally in a sales‑aligned or client‑facing role.\n* Solid understanding of Global Markets products and end‑to‑end trade lifecycle, including pre‑ and post‑trade support and trade booking activities.\n* Proven ability to partner with Sales and internal stakeholders (Operations, COO, Risk, Legal, Compliance) to resolve issues and deliver client‑centric outcomes.\n* Strong risk, control, and governance mindset, with experience operating within operational risk frameworks and regulatory standards.\n* Track record of process improvement, including analysing issues, using MIS, and driving sustainable enhancements.\n* Confident communicator with the ability to influence and challenge constructively across regions in a fast‑paced, global environment.\n* Strong written and verbal communication skills, with proficiency in Excel and PowerPoint\n* Bachelor’s degree (or equivalent) in Finance, Business, Economics, or a related field.\n\n**Role Specific Technical Competencies**\n\n* Communication skills\n* Customer Relationship Management\n* Product Knowledge\n* Problem Solving Skills\n* Collaboration\n* Ability to Influence\n* Time Management\n\n**About Standard Chartered**\n\nWe''re an international bank, nimble enough to act, big enough for impact. For more than 170 years, we''ve worked to make a positive difference for our clients, communities, and each other. We question the status quo, love a challenge and enjoy finding new opportunities to grow and do better than before. If you''re looking for a career with purpose and you want to work for a bank making a difference, we want to hear from you. You can count on us to celebrate your unique talents and we can''t wait to see the talents you can bring us.\n\nOur purpose, to drive commerce and prosperity through our unique diversity, together with our brand promise, to be here for good are achieved by how we each live our valued behaviours. When you work with us, you''ll see how we value difference and advocate inclusion.\n\nTogether we:\n\n* **Do the right thing** and are assertive, challenge one another, and live with integrity, while putting the client at the heart of what we do\n* **Never settle,** continuously striving to improve and innovate, keeping things simple and learning from doing well, and not so well\n* **Are better together,** we can be ourselves, be inclusive, see more good in others, and work collectively to build for the long term\n\n**What we offer**\n\n**In line with our Fair Pay Charter,** we offer a competitive salary and benefits to support your mental, physical, financial and social wellbeing.\n\n* **Core bank funding for retirement savings, medical and life insurance,** with flexible and voluntary benefits available in some locations.\n* **Time-off** including annual leave, parental/maternity (20 weeks), sabbatical (12 months maximum) and volunteering leave (3 days), along with minimum global standards for annual and public holiday, which is combined to 30 days minimum.\n* **Flexible working** options based around home and office locations, with flexible working patterns.\n* **Proactive wellbeing support** through Unmind, a market-leading digital wellbeing platform, development courses for resilience and other human skills, global Employee Assistance Programme, sick leave, mental health first-aiders and all sorts of self-help toolkits\n* **A continuous learning culture** to support your growth, with opportunities to reskill and upskill and access to physical, virtual and digital learning.\n* **Being part of an inclusive and values driven organisation,** one that embraces and celebrates our unique diversity, across our teams, business functions and geographies - everyone feels respected and can realise their full potential.\n\n**Recruitment Assessments**\n\nSome of our roles use assessments to help us understand how suitable you are for the role you''ve applied to. If you are invited to take an assessment, this is great news. It means your application has progressed to an important stage of our recruitment process.\n\nVisit our careers website www.sc.com/careers", "requirements": "具备对全球市场和CIB客户景观的深入理解，能够提供全面的交易前后支持，推动流程改进并确保符合风险管理标准。需与销售、运营、COO团队及多个内部利益相关者紧密合作，确保高效执行交易生命周期活动，并支持新业务和产品启动。", "source": "Indeed", "source_warning": "部分数据源抓取失败：linkedin: 抓取超时，已跳过", "search_keyword": "Big Data Analyst", "relevance_score": 24, "relevance_reasons": ["标题部分命中: 大数据分析 / data analyst / big data analyst / data science / business intelligence analyst / data insights specialist", "描述命中: data", "标题命中: analyst", "描述命中: analyst", "描述命中: big", "描述命中: business"], "market_country": "新加坡", "skill_evidence": [{"name": "MIS Data Analysis", "evidence": "Analyse MIS data to identify recurring issues, recommend corrective actions, and enhance process reliability."}, {"name": "Process Improvement", "evidence": "Lead and participate in continuous process improvement initiatives."}, {"name": "Risk Management Standards", "evidence": "Ensure Group Risk Management standards are being maintained / adhered to"}, {"name": "Ops Risk Framework", "evidence": "Adherence to Ops Risk Framework standards of implementation and process management:"}, {"name": "Client Onboarding Coordination", "evidence": "Act as the first point of contact for client and Sales queries, including onboarding coordination and operational que..."}, {"name": "Trade Lifecycle Monitoring", "evidence": "Support Sales on trade lifecycle monitoring/activities (e.g., novation processing, event reporting such as option exp..."}, {"name": "New Product Enablement", "evidence": "Collaborate across CSSG, Sales, COO teams, and Operations on new business initiatives, including new product enableme..."}, {"name": "Control Design", "evidence": "Collaborate across CSSG, Sales, COO teams, and Operations on new business initiatives, including new product enableme..."}], "skills": ["MIS Data Analysis", "Process Improvement", "Risk Management Standards", "Ops Risk Framework", "Client Onboarding Coordination", "Trade Lifecycle Monitoring", "New Product Enablement", "Control Design"]}, {"title": "Manager, Data Center SSD Firmware - Media Management", "company": "Micron Technology", "salary": "面议", "location": "SG", "experience": "不限", "education": "不限", "description": "**Our vision is to transform how the world uses information to enrich life for all.**\n\nJoin an inclusive team passionate about one thing: using their expertise in the relentless pursuit of innovation for customers and partners. The solutions we build help make everything from virtual reality experiences to breakthroughs in neural networks possible. We do it all while committing to integrity, sustainability, and giving back to our communities. Because doing so can fuel the very innovation we are pursuing.\n\nMicron Technology is seeking a **Manager, Data Center SSD Firmware (M1/M2)** to lead the **Media Management (MM)** firmware component team supporting Data Center SSD products. This role combines **people management**, **technical leadership**, and **firmware component ownership** to enable successful delivery of complex SSD firmware solutions.\n\n**Media Management (MM) firmware** is the SSD firmware domain responsible for translating host data requests into reliable and efficient NAND flash operations. It comprises the **Flash Translation Layer (FTL)**, which manages logical‑to‑physical address mapping, data placement, wear leveling, and reliability algorithms, and the **Back End (BE)**, which controls low‑level NAND command execution and media interactions. Together, MM firmware is foundational to SSD **performance, reliability, endurance, and quality of service**.\n\nThe successful candidate will manage and develop a team of firmware engineers, serve as a firmware component lead for Data Center SSD programs, and partner closely with firmware leadership and cross‑functional teams to drive execution, quality, and continuous improvement.\n\n**Responsibilities**\n\n* **People & Functional Management**\n  + Manage and develop the Singapore‑based **DC SSD Firmware Media Management (MM)** team, including hiring, onboarding, performance management, coaching, and career development.\n  + Drive continuous **skill growth and technical depth** across the team to meet current and future business needs.\n  + Foster a culture of accountability, ownership, collaboration, and inclusion.\n* **Firmware Component Leadership**\n  + Serve as **Firmware Component Lead** for Media Management in Data Center SSD programs.\n  + Own firmware component responsibilities including **resource planning, scope definition, execution planning, and delivery tracking**.\n  + Ensure component designs and implementations meet product requirements, quality standards, and schedule commitments.\n* **Program Execution & Delivery**\n  + Partner with SSD firmware project leads and cross‑functional engineering teams to support **successful execution and on‑time delivery** of firmware milestones.\n  + Identify technical and execution risks early; drive mitigation plans and escalate appropriately.\n  + Take on **additional assignments** as needed to support broader **SSD Engineering Group** objectives.\n* **Process & Continuous Improvement**\n  + Collaborate with the **Firmware Leadership Team** to improve engineering processes, development efficiency, and product quality.\n  + Promote best practices in firmware design, code quality, reviews, documentation, and knowledge sharing.\n* **Collaboration & Communication**\n  + Foster strong teamwork and effective communication within the firmware organization and with global partners.\n  + Build trusted working relationships with peer managers, technical leads, and stakeholders.\n* **Micron Values & Leadership**\n  + Act as a **responsible Micron employee**, demonstrating integrity, professionalism, and Micron values.\n  + Lead by example and serve as a positive role model for engineers and peers.\n  + Serve as **Firmware Component Lead** for Media Management in Data Center SSD programs.\n  + Own firmware component responsibilities including **resource planning, scope definition, execution planning, and delivery tracking**.\n  + Ensure component designs and implementations meet product requirements, quality standards, and schedule commitments.\n* **Program Execution & Delivery**\n  + Partner with SSD firmware project leads and cross‑functional engineering teams to support **successful execution and on‑time delivery** of firmware milestones.\n  + Identify technical and execution risks early; drive mitigation plans and escalate appropriately.\n  + Take on **additional assignments** as needed to support broader **SSD Engineering Group** objectives.\n* **Process & Continuous Improvement**\n  + Collaborate with the **Firmware Leadership Team** to improve engineering processes, development efficiency, and product quality.\n  + Promote best practices in firmware design, code quality, reviews, documentation, and knowledge sharing.\n* **Collaboration & Communication**\n  + Foster strong teamwork and effective communication within the firmware organization and with global partners.\n  + Build trusted working relationships with peer managers, technical leads, and stakeholders.\n* **Micron Values & Leadership**\n  + Act as a **responsible Micron employee**, demonstrating integrity, professionalism, and Micron values.\n  + Lead by example and serve as a positive role model for engineers and peers.\n\n**Minimum Qualifications**\n--------------------------\n\n* Bachelor’s degree or equivalent experience in Electrical Engineering, Computer Engineering, Computer Science, or a related field.\n* Min 10 years of relevant firmware or embedded software development experience.\n* Min 4 years of people management experience, including managing managers or senior technical leads.\n* Experience delivering firmware in complex, cross-functional product environments.\n* Strong communication, planning, and execution skills.\n* Demonstrated success scaling teams, developing leaders, and driving execution across multiple projects or components.\n* Strong critical thinking and cross-organizational influence skills.\n\n**Requirements:**\n-----------------\n\n* Experience with Data Center SSD firmware, NAND flash, storage subsystems, or components related to media management.\n* Experience driving firmware projects in a matrixed, global engineering environment.\n* Demonstrated success in talent development and team scaling.\n* Familiarity with continuous improvement, engineering process optimization, and quality metrics.\n\n**About Micron Technology, Inc.**\n\nWe are an industry leader in innovative memory and storage solutions transforming how the world uses information to enrich life *for all*. With a relentless focus on our customers, technology leadership, and manufacturing and operational excellence, Micron delivers a rich portfolio of high-performance DRAM, NAND, and NOR memory and storage products through our Micron® and Crucial® brands. Every day, the innovations that our people create fuel the data economy, enabling advances in artificial intelligence and 5G applications that unleash opportunities — from the data center to the intelligent edge and across the client and mobile user experience.  \n  \nTo learn more, please visit micron.com/careers  \n  \nAll qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, veteran or disability status.  \n  \nTo request assistance with the application process and/or for reasonable accommodations, please contact hrsupport\\_sg@micron.com\n\nMicron Prohibits the use of child labor and complies with all applicable laws, rules, regulations, and other international and industry labor standards.\n\nMicron does not charge candidates any recruitment fees or unlawfully collect any other payment from candidates as consideration for their employment with Micron.\n\nAI alert: Candidates are encouraged to use AI tools to enhance their resume and/or application materials. However, all information provided must be accurate and reflect the candidate''s true skills and experiences. Misuse of AI to fabricate or misrepresent qualifications will result in immediate disqualification.\n\nFraud alert: Micron advises job seekers to be cautious of unsolicited job offers and to verify the authenticity of any communication claiming to be from Micron by checking the official Micron careers website in the About Micron Technology, Inc.", "requirements": "管理并发展新加坡的DC SSD Firmware Media Management团队，负责固件组件的资源规划、范围定义、执行计划和交付跟踪。与跨职能团队合作，确保固件设计和实现符合产品需求、质量标准和时间表。", "source": "Indeed", "source_warning": "部分数据源抓取失败：linkedin: 抓取超时，已跳过", "search_keyword": "Data Science", "relevance_score": 24, "relevance_reasons": ["标题部分命中: 大数据分析 / data analyst / big data analyst / data science / business intelligence analyst / data insights specialist", "标题命中: data", "描述命中: data", "描述命中: science", "描述命中: business", "描述命中: intelligence"], "market_country": "新加坡", "skill_evidence": [{"name": "Flash Translation Layer (FTL)", "evidence": "Media Management (MM) firmware is the SSD firmware domain responsible for translating host data requests into reliabl..."}, {"name": "Back End (BE)", "evidence": "Media Management (MM) firmware is the SSD firmware domain responsible for translating host data requests into reliabl..."}, {"name": "NAND Flash Operations", "evidence": "Media Management (MM) firmware is the SSD firmware domain responsible for translating host data requests into reliabl..."}, {"name": "Firmware Design", "evidence": "Ensure component designs and implementations meet product requirements, quality standards, and schedule commitments."}, {"name": "Code Quality", "evidence": "Promote best practices in firmware design, code quality, reviews, documentation, and knowledge sharing."}, {"name": "Documentation", "evidence": "Promote best practices in firmware design, code quality, reviews, documentation, and knowledge sharing."}, {"name": "Knowledge Sharing", "evidence": "Promote best practices in firmware design, code quality, reviews, documentation, and knowledge sharing."}], "skills": ["Flash Translation Layer (FTL)", "Back End (BE)", "NAND Flash Operations", "Firmware Design", "Code Quality", "Documentation", "Knowledge Sharing"]}, {"title": "Senior Product Operations Specialist", "company": "Open Government Products", "salary": "面议", "location": "S00", "experience": "不限", "education": "不限", "description": "**Who we are**\n--------------\n\n**Open Government Products (OGP)** operates like a startup within the government; We are a fast-paced, dynamic team of engineers, designers, and product managers dedicated to public good. We autonomously identify opportunities to solve public problems using tech, rapidly prototype, and launch solutions - from citizen apps to automating public agency operations. Embracing an open-sourced and flat hierarchy, we cut through bureaucracy to focus on real-world, user-centric innovations that drive change.\n\n**About the role**\n------------------\n\nWe are looking for a **Senior Product Operations Specialist** to join the **Health Appointment System (HAS)** team.\n\nThis role is for someone who can run strong feedback and support loops, investigate issues, draw insights from user and operational data, and drive improvements across product, workflow, training, and support.\n\nYou should be comfortable using the right tools to analyse issues, build useful working materials, improve reporting, and help the team make better product and workflow decisions.\n\n**What you’ll do**\n------------------\n\n* Run and improve support and feedback loops for HAS\n* Investigate issues raised through tickets, stakeholder feedback, rollouts, and operational observations\n* Synthesise recurring issues into clear recommendations for product, process, training, or communication improvements\n* Support rollouts by ensuring readiness across testing, user guidance, training, and issue management\n* Work closely with product managers, engineers, designers, and stakeholders to ground decisions in user and operational reality\n* Identify workflow gaps, repetitive manual work, and areas of friction, then drive improvements or automation\n* Build and maintain practical structures such as dashboards, trackers, templates, playbooks, and workflows\n* Contribute to stronger Product Ops practices by documenting and sharing reusable ways of working\n\n**What we’re looking for**\n--------------------------\n\n### **Working skills**\n\n* Strong working knowledge of **SQL**, including the ability to write queries from scratch or refine existing/tool-generated queries to get the right output\n* Strong ability to **structure ambiguous problems** into clear lines of investigation or action\n* Strong **prompt-writing and tool-use skills** to analyse issues, synthesise information, and produce useful working outputs\n* Comfort using **dashboards, spreadsheets, and reporting tools** to identify patterns and surface actionable insights\n* Experience working with **CRM, ticketing, or support systems** to structure information, identify recurring issues, and draw insights from data\n* Ability to translate user, stakeholder, and operational signals into practical recommendations\n* Ability to build or improve operational structures such as dashboards, trackers, templates, workflows, and playbooks\n\n### **Ways of working**\n\n* Strong judgment and user empathy\n* Comfortable managing **tough or complex stakeholders**\n* Able to work across product, engineering, design, and operations\n* Strong written communication, especially for updates, guides, issue summaries, and stakeholder-facing materials\n* Able to independently own problems and drive improvements\n* Comfortable operating in ambiguity\n* A bias toward making recurring work more scalable, robust, and easier to run\n\n**How you’ll add value**\n------------------------\n\n* You help the team clearly understand what users and stakeholders are struggling with\n* You turn messy signals into actionable insights and recommendations\n* You improve the team’s ability to detect, respond to, and learn from recurring issues\n* You make rollouts and ongoing operations easier to run and support\n* You strengthen the systems, workflows, and structures that help HAS scale effectively\n\n**Overall**\n-----------\n\nThis role is suited for someone who is practical, analytical, structured, and user-centric — someone who can close the loop between user reality, operational signals, and product decisions.\n\n**Working at OGP**\n------------------\n\n**Ownership and Autonomy** — Beyond technical tasks, this means having autonomy to voice opinions and suggest future directions. Building what you believe in drives the creation of great solutions.\n\n**Rapid Prototyping** — We prioritize testing ideas over debating them, allowing us to identify problems quickly and convey possibilities to others. This fail-fast approach accelerates innovation.\n\n**Flexibility** — We provide flexible work arrangements based on what works best for our team and its members, fostering a productive and supportive environment.\n\n**Continuous Learning** — Drive professional growth by exploring new architectures, frameworks, and technologies. With dedicated yearly learning months and hackathons, continuous learning is essential as we tackle innovative ideas and challenges.\n\n**Mission-Driven** — Our work is dedicated to the public good, aiming to improve the lives of Singapore citizens. We focus on creating impactful solutions that enhance the community and the place we call home.\n\nProjects we have worked on include:\n\n* **Covid-19 Vaccination National Appointment System** - A suite of systems built to enable Singapore''s national vaccination campaign for Covid-19. This includes informational sites, appointment booking systems, and records management systems.\n* **Data.gov.sg** - An open repository of all the Singapore Government''s public data. It helps people understand the data using visualisations and articles, and provides real-time APIs for developers to use.\n* **Parking.sg** - A mobile app alternative to parking coupons. It lets users pay, extend, and refund their parking sessions just using their phones.\n* **FormSG** - A form builder tool for agencies to self-service and create online forms that capture classified data, with the goal of replacing paper forms.\n* **Isomer** - Isomer provides government agencies with an easy-to-deploy static website building and hosting service to create usable, secure and faster informational websites quickly.\n* **RedeemSG** - RedeemSG helps the Singapore Government to create, send and track redemptions of digital vouchers easily.\n* **PaySG** - PaySG was developed to enable digital payments for government services, and was initially used for payments for COVID-19 swab tests and Stay-Home Notices for incoming travellers to Singapore.\n\nAn overview of other OGP products can be found on our website: https://www.open.gov.sg/products/\n\n**Consent to Use and Disclosure of Personal Data**\n\nI hereby give my consent to Open Government Products, Government Technology Agency (“OGP”) to: Obtain and verify information from or with any source (including third parties) as may be deemed appropriate by OGP and/or any relevant Government agency for the purposes of assessing my application for employment and/or for recommendation to a third party for employment with or engagement by that third party (see below for more information). Share my personal data set out in this application form and any other personal data subsequently provided by me arising out of or in connection with my application for employment with other Government agencies or a third party vendor appointed by OGP for the purposes of recruitment and/or review of recruitment practices, and for such personal data to also be used as part of de-identified and aggregated data for reporting purposes.\n\nAdditionally, where relevant, OGP may share my personal data set out in this application form and any other personal data subsequently provided by me to a third party for that third party to consider employing or otherwise engaging me to undertake work relevant to OGP. I understand and acknowledge that the collection, use and/or disclosure of such personal data may also be subject to that third party’s privacy terms. I declare that all the information given by me is true to the best of my knowledge and voluntarily given. By clicking the ''Apply'' button, I hereby certify that I have read and understood all of the clauses above and that I agree to all of them.", "requirements": "具备SQL查询能力，能够分析问题并生成有用的工作输出；熟悉使用仪表盘、电子表格和报告工具进行数据分析；有使用CRM、工单或支持系统的经验；能够将用户、利益相关者和运营信号转化为实际建议。", "source": "Indeed", "source_warning": "部分数据源抓取失败：linkedin: 抓取超时，已跳过", "search_keyword": "Data Insights Specialist", "relevance_score": 24, "relevance_reasons": ["标题部分命中: 大数据分析 / data analyst / big data analyst / data science / business intelligence analyst / data insights specialist", "描述命中: data", "描述命中: big", "描述命中: insights", "标题命中: specialist", "描述命中: specialist"], "market_country": "新加坡", "skill_evidence": [{"name": "SQL", "evidence": "Strong working knowledge of SQL, including the ability to write queries from scratch or refine existing/tool-generate..."}, {"name": "Dashboards", "evidence": "Build and maintain practical structures such as dashboards, trackers, templates, playbooks, and workflows"}, {"name": "Spreadsheets", "evidence": "Comfort using dashboards, spreadsheets, and reporting tools to identify patterns and surface actionable insights"}, {"name": "Reporting Tools", "evidence": "Comfort using dashboards, spreadsheets, and reporting tools to identify patterns and surface actionable insights"}, {"name": "CRM", "evidence": "Experience working with CRM, ticketing, or support systems to structure information, identify recurring issues, and d..."}, {"name": "Ticketing", "evidence": "Experience working with CRM, ticketing, or support systems to structure information, identify recurring issues, and d..."}, {"name": "Support Systems", "evidence": "Experience working with CRM, ticketing, or support systems to structure information, identify recurring issues, and d..."}], "skills": ["SQL", "Dashboards", "Spreadsheets", "Reporting Tools", "CRM", "Ticketing", "Support Systems"]}, {"title": "Arbitration Specialist", "company": "Wise", "salary": "面议", "location": "Geylang", "experience": "不限", "education": "不限", "description": "**Company Description**\n\nWise is a global technology company, building the best way to move and manage the world’s money.  \n**Min fees. Max ease. Full speed.**\n\nWhether people and businesses are sending money to another country, spending abroad, or making and receiving international payments, Wise is on a mission to make their lives easier and save them money.\n\nAs part of our team, you will be helping us create an entirely new network for the world''s money.  \n**For everyone, everywhere.**\n\nMore about **our mission** and **what we offer**.\n\n **Job Description**\n\nWe’re looking for an Arbitration Specialist to join our growing team.\n\n**Purpose of the role**\n\nWe’re looking for an Arbitration Specialist to join our growing team, with a critical focus on the APAC region, where the role is based. Purpose of the role The job of the Complaints Arbitration Specialist is to right wrongs through fairness, accountability and transparency, with a clear understanding of the local market and regulatory landscape in APAC. The Complaints Arbitration Specialist will be responsible to communicate with Wise’s arbitration body’s, representing Wise and ensuring we’re able to come to correct outcomes based on the information provided by the Specialist. The role will require to maintain a healthy and professional relationship with arbitration bodies, contribute to root cause analysis, and actively participate in shaping future policies and operational decisions within the complaints team. The role demands diligence, legal acumen, consistency, and the ability to handle sensitive information with the utmost care.\n\n**Your responsibilities:**\n\n* Case Management: Investigate arbitration cases thoroughly, providing detailed information. Conduct audits on the internal handling of the Customer complaint journey, ensuring a fair outcome.\n* Arbitration decision process: Assess cases and decisions made by the arbitration body, taking responsibility for the legally binding decision. Ensure Wise presents all necessary evidence based on this assessment.\n* APAC Market & Regulatory Expertise: Serve as the primary expert for the APAC region. Maintain an in-depth understanding of local regulatory frameworks, evolving arbitration body assessments, and the unique differences in jurisdictional complaints, ensuring compliance and optimal outcomes for Wise and its customers in the APAC market. Proactively monitor regulatory changes and interpret their impact on our customers and processes.\n* Strategic Growth & Scaling Insight: Apply an awareness of Wise''s growth and scaling challenges in the APAC market to all case management and policy contributions, ensuring solutions are scalable and future-proof.\n* Cross-Functional Influence & Action: Build and maintain effective working relationships with Compliance, Operations, and Product teams to effectively translate arbitration insights and regulatory changes into actionable policy and process improvements.\n* Root Cause analysis and feedback: Collect vital company data on complaints, record arbitration decisions for use in Root Cause Analysis, and share feedback with relevant teams within Wise.\n* Mitigate reputational damage from adverse decisions: Defend Wise against adverse decisions to safeguard the company''s reputation.\n* Work across multiple teams: Communicate with relevant product/operational teams to ensure a comprehensive understanding of cases and the ability to articulate this information to the arbitration body.\n* Consistently hitting SLAs: Consistently handling cases within Wise’s SLAs, as well ensuring we do not Breach cases based on the arbitration body deadline.\n* Strong Fincrime knowledge: Maintain up-to-date knowledge on scam and deactivation complaints, understanding how they are handled across the business.\n* Contribute to the team culture in a positive manner: Positively contribute to the team culture by assisting other Complaints specialists and officers, sharing decisions, and providing feedback when necessary.\n\n**About the role**\n\n* Starting salary: SGD 5,800\n\n  \n**Qualifications**\n\n**About you**\n\n* You have at least 12 months working in a customer and compliance focused role in the APAC markets.\n* You’re a great communicator. You’ve got impeccable verbal and written English skills and you’ve worked internationally, cross-team, or cross-geo before so you’ll quickly pick up on how best to communicate effectively across different cultures, time zones, and whatever else - You also welcome an open feedback culture, happy both giving and receiving feedback to or from anyone in the organization\n* On top of this, you’re able to adapt to Wise type of communication\n* You pay attention to details, when completing tasks you’re thorough and accurate\n* You’re analytical: you are comfortable working with data, noticing patterns, trends and things of note and you can draw meaningful conclusions from them. You can use this to solve problems, make decisions and provide recommendations to your leads, colleagues and other stakeholders of your job\n* On top of this, you have a good command of Looker or other BI tools\n* You’re able to detect and solve problematic cases and/or processes, and escalate them as needed.\n* You look for incremental improvements in work processes and results. You constantly look for ways to streamline work processes, eliminating steps that don’t add value or rearranging them to facilitate the workflows. You look beyond the symptoms to uncover root causes of problems and question the status quo to ensure the processes and results continue to be relevant. You know different problem solving techniques like 5 Whys, Fishbone diagrams or you’re willing to learn\n* You’re punctual, well organized and able to divide their time between specific activities in order to get things done\n* You’re autonomous. You’re able to work independently and take decisions in main problem solving cases\n* You’re reliable, adaptable and display commitment to the team’s goals.\n* While getting things done, you know how to manage your time and energies. You can organise and plan how long you spend on specific activities\n* You possess exceptional local market and regulatory awareness of the APAC region, and understand how to apply this knowledge to a complex, fast-growing global business.\n* You are aware of and put into practice data security procedures\n* You’re customer-focused. This should go without saying, but this is your guiding light. Our customers come first and we make no compromises on that, so you always have the customer’s best interest in mind\n\n  \n**Additional Information**\n\nFor everyone, everywhere. We''re people building money without borders — without judgement or prejudice, too. We believe teams are strongest when they are diverse, equitable and inclusive.\n\nWe''re proud to have a truly international team, and we celebrate our differences.  \nInclusive teams help us live our values and make sure every Wiser feels respected, empowered to contribute towards our mission and able to progress in their careers.\n\nIf you want to find out more about what it''s like to work at Wise visit Wise.Jobs.\n\nKeep up to date with life at Wise by following us on LinkedIn and Instagram.", "requirements": "负责仲裁案件的调查和管理，确保公平结果；具备对APAC地区法律和监管环境的深入了解；能够与合规、运营和产品团队协作，推动政策和流程改进；具备处理敏感信息的能力，确保公司声誉不受损害。", "source": "Indeed", "source_warning": "部分数据源抓取失败：linkedin: 抓取超时，已跳过", "search_keyword": "Data Insights Specialist", "relevance_score": 24, "relevance_reasons": ["标题部分命中: 大数据分析 / data analyst / big data analyst / data science / business intelligence analyst / data insights specialist", "描述命中: data", "描述命中: business", "描述命中: insights", "标题命中: specialist", "描述命中: specialist"], "market_country": "新加坡", "skills": [], "skill_evidence": []}, {"title": "Strategy Insights & Planning Consultant", "company": "ZS Associates", "salary": "面议", "location": "S00", "experience": "3-5年", "education": "博士及以上", "description": ":\n\n**ZS** is a place where passion changes lives. As a management consulting and technology firm focused on improving life and how we live it, we transform ideas into impact by **bringing together data, science, technology** and **human ingenuity** to deliver better outcomes for all. Here you’ll work side-by-side with a powerful collective of thinkers and experts shaping life-changing solutions for patients, caregivers and consumers, worldwide. ZSers drive impact by bringing a **client-first mentality** to each and every engagement. We partner collaboratively with our clients to develop custom solutions and technology products that create value and deliver company results across critical areas of their business. Bring your curiosity for learning, bold ideas, courage and passion to drive life-changing impact to ZS.\n\n  \n:\n\n**S****trategy Insights & Planning Consultant**\n\n**ZS''s** **Insights & Analytics** **group** partners with clients to design and deliver solutions to help them tackle a broad range of business challenges. Our teams work on multiple projects simultaneously, leveraging advanced data analytics and problem-solving techniques. Our recommendations and solutions are based on rigorous research and analysis underpinned by deep expertise and thought leadership.\n\n**Strategy Insights & Planning****Consultant**\n\nStrategy Insights & Planning Consultants deliver high-quality solutions for our clients. Consultants possess unstructured problem-solving skills as well as strong analytic, synthesis and communication skills. Consultants may work on multiple projects simultaneously. As Consultants advance in their career, they specialize in a particular industry, practice area and/or client relationship.\n\n**What** **You’ll** **Do**\n\n* Work with project leadership to define project scope and develop approach.\n* Lead project task execution by ensuring progress, organizing project data and coordinating team meetings.\n* Conduct issue analysis and develop hypotheses on the key client issues.\n* Design and execute qualitative and/or quantitative analyses to test and analyze hypotheses.\n* Synthesize findings, develop recommendations, and communicate results to clients and internal teams.\n* Provide thought leadership and innovation within projects and practice areas.\n* Participate in business development.\n* Contribute to internal firm activities.\n* Coach and mentor junior team members.\n\n**What** **You’ll** **Bring**\n\n* MBA with bachelor''s (and often graduate) degrees with a strong academic record in business, economics, marketing, psychology, physical or life sciences, engineering, applied math, statistics, or related fields. Alternately, candidates may possess a PhD in marketing, economics, decision sciences or related field with a business application. In lieu of an MBA or PhD, 5-8 years of relevant work experience may substitute.\n* Up to 3 years of post-MBA relevant work experience, and 3-5 years of pre-MBA work experience.\n* High motivation, good work ethic, maturity and personal initiative.\n* Aptitude for, and enjoyment of, leading and managing teams.\n* Effective oral and written communication skills that enable personal impact with senior-level decision makers.\n* Strong attention to detail, with a quality-focused mindset.\n\n* Analytic problem-solving skills, with a creative and innovative outlook;\n* Client service orientation.\n* Fluency in English\n* Client-first mentality\n* Intense work ethic\n* Collaborative spirit and problem-solving approach\n\n:\n\n**How you’ll grow:**\n\n* Cross-functional skills development & custom learning pathways\n* Milestone training programs aligned to career progression opportunities\n* Internal mobility paths that empower growth via s-curves, individual contribution and role expansions\n\n**Perks & Benefits:**\n\nAt ZS, your growth matters. We offer a comprehensive total rewards package that supports your health and well‑being, financial future, time away, and professional development. With robust skills‑building programs, multiple career progression paths, internal mobility, and a deeply collaborative culture, you’ll have the opportunity to do meaningful work, expand your capabilities, and thrive as part of a global community. For details on total rewards in Singapore, visit ZS Singapore office locations | Where we work | ZS.\n\n**Hybrid working model:**\n\nWe are committed to giving our employees a flexible and connected way of working. A flexible and connected ZS allows us to combine work from home and on-site presence at clients/ZS offices for the majority of our week. The magic of ZS culture and innovation thrives in both planned and spontaneous face-to-face connections.\n\n**Travel:**\n\nTravel is a requirement at ZS for client facing ZSers; business needs of your project and client are the priority. While some projects may be local, all client-facing ZSers should be prepared to travel as needed. Travel provides opportunities to strengthen client relationships, gain diverse experiences, and enhance professional growth by working in different environments and cultures.\n\n**Considering applying?**\n\nAt ZS, we honor the visible and invisible elements of our identities, personal experiences, and belief systems—the ones that comprise us as individuals, shape who we are, and make us unique. We believe your personal interests, identities, and desire to learn are integral to your success here. We are committed to building a team that reflects a broad variety of backgrounds, perspectives, and experiences. Learn more about our inclusion and belonging efforts and the networks ZS supports to assist our ZSers in cultivating community spaces and obtaining the resources they need to thrive.\n\nIf you’re eager to grow, contribute, and bring your unique self to our work, we encourage you to apply.  \n  \nZS is an equal opportunity employer and is committed to providing equal employment and advancement opportunities without regard to any class protected by applicable law.  \n  \nTo complete your application:  \nCandidates must possess or be able to obtain work authorization for their intended country of employment. An on-line application, including a full set of transcripts (official or unofficial), is required to be considered.  \n  \nNO AGENCY CALLS, PLEASE.  \n  \nFind Out More At:  \nwww.zs.com", "requirements": "Candidates must have an MBA with a strong academic record in relevant fields or a PhD in marketing, economics, or related areas. They should have up to 3 years of post-MBA experience and 3-5 years of pre-MBA experience. Strong analytic problem-solving skills are required.", "source": "Indeed", "source_warning": "部分数据源抓取失败：linkedin: 抓取超时，已跳过", "search_keyword": "Data Science", "relevance_score": 24, "relevance_reasons": ["标题部分命中: 大数据分析 / data analyst / big data analyst / data science / business intelligence analyst / data insights specialist", "描述命中: data", "描述命中: science", "描述命中: business", "标题命中: insights", "描述命中: insights"], "market_country": "新加坡", "skill_evidence": [{"name": "Data Analytics", "evidence": "leveraging advanced data analytics and problem-solving techniques"}, {"name": "Problem-solving Techniques", "evidence": "leveraging advanced data analytics and problem-solving techniques"}, {"name": "Qualitative Analysis", "evidence": "Design and execute qualitative and/or quantitative analyses to test and analyze hypotheses"}, {"name": "Quantitative Analysis", "evidence": "Design and execute qualitative and/or quantitative analyses to test and analyze hypotheses"}], "skills": ["Data Analytics", "Problem-solving Techniques", "Qualitative Analysis", "Quantitative Analysis"]}, {"title": "Specialist [Development & Innovation]", "company": "Rainbow Centre", "salary": "面议", "location": "Queenstown", "experience": "不限", "education": "不限", "description": "**Job no:** 492739  \n**Work type:** Fixed Term Full-time  \n**Location:** Margaret Drive  \n**Categories:** Corporate Services, Research & Development\n\nThe **Specialist for Development & Innovation** supports the design, implementation, and evaluation of innovation and service development initiatives across RC. The role contributes to the operational delivery of the innovation lifecycle—from concept development and prototyping to pilot implementation, evaluation, and integration into core services.\n\nWorking closely with service teams, corporate units, research partners, and funders, the Specialist helps ensure that development initiatives are well-designed, ethically implemented, evidence-informed, and aligned with RC’s strategic priorities and Good Life outcomes.\n\nThe role combines analytical, project management, and collaborative capabilities, helping translate ideas into structured pilots, capturing learning from innovation projects, and strengthening RC’s organisational capacity for disciplined experimentation and continuous improvement.\n\n**Critical Work Functions**\n\n**Innovation Development & Pilot Implementation**\n\n* Support the design and development of innovation concepts, prototypes, and pilot initiatives aligned with RC’s mission, Good Life Framework, and strategic priorities.\n\n* Work with service teams, practitioners, and partners to translate ideas into structured pilots, including defining objectives, target populations, implementation plans, and evaluation approaches.\n\n* Coordinate the implementation of innovation pilots and development initiatives across services, ensuring activities are organised, documented, and aligned with agreed project plans.\n\n* Facilitate collaboration between multidisciplinary stakeholders - including educators, therapists, social workers, digital teams, and external partners- to support the successful delivery of pilot projects.\n\n* Document pilot processes, operational insights, and emerging challenges to support organisational learning and decision-making.\n\n**Evaluation, Data & Organisational Learning**\n\n* Support the development of evaluation frameworks for innovation initiatives, including defining outcomes, indicators, and learning objectives.\n\n* Collect, organise, and analyse qualitative and quantitative data from pilots and development initiatives to support evaluation and reporting.\n\n* Prepare clear summaries of pilot outcomes, implementation lessons, and cost-effectiveness considerations to inform stage-gate decisions (e.g., continuation, scaling, integration, or discontinuation).\n\n* Contribute to the development of innovation dashboards, reports, and knowledge resources that support organisation-wide learning and improvement.\n\n* Support the documentation and dissemination of learning from innovation initiatives across RC teams and programmes.\n\n**Governance, Risk & Compliance Support**\n\n* Support the implementation of RC’s innovation governance processes, including documentation of proposals, pilot plans, evaluation reports, and stage-gate reviews.\n\n* Ensure development initiatives comply with relevant organisational policies and external requirements, including safeguarding standards, PDPA, research ethics considerations, and grant conditions where applicable.\n\n* Assist in maintaining documentation related to innovation initiatives, including partnership agreements, pilot protocols, reporting requirements, and internal approval processes.\n\n* Support the identification and escalation of operational risks, ethical considerations, or implementation challenges arising from innovation pilots\n\n**Project Management & Operational Coordination**\n\n* Coordinate project timelines, deliverables, and stakeholder engagement across innovation initiatives and pilot projects.\n\n* Support grant-funded or externally funded innovation projects by assisting with reporting, documentation, and compliance with funder requirements.\n\n* Facilitate meetings, working groups, and project discussions related to development initiatives, ensuring clear documentation of decisions and actions.\n\n* Track implementation progress and support the preparation of progress updates for internal leadership, funders, and partners.\n\n**Partnerships & Collaboration**\n\n* Work collaboratively with RC service teams to support the design and testing of new service approaches.\n\n* Support engagement with external partners such as research institutions, social innovators, technology providers, and sector collaborators involved in innovation initiatives.\n\n* Assist in coordinating partnership activities, pilot engagements, and collaborative projects, ensuring clear communication and documentation.\n\n* Contribute to knowledge-sharing with sector partners where appropriate to support responsible innovation and collective learning.\n\n**Job Holder Requirements**\n\n* A recognised good Bachelor’s degree in a relevant discipline such as Social Work, Psychology, Special Education, Allied Health, Public Health, Social Sciences, Innovation, Design, or related fields\n* At least 3 years of relevant professional experience in roles involving service development, programme evaluation, research, project management, or innovation initiatives within social services, education, healthcare, public sector, or non-profit environments.\n* Training or exposure in areas such as service design, project management, programme evaluation, data analysis, or innovation methodologies would be advantageous.\n* Candidates with strong direct practice experience (e.g. educators, therapists, social workers, or allied professionals)\n\n**Rainbow Centre is recognised as one of top 300 employers under the** **Singapore Opportunity Index****, as a Career Builder that continuously creates meaningful opportunities for career advancement.**", "requirements": "支持创新和开发项目的整个生命周期，包括概念设计、原型开发、试点实施、评估和整合。协助制定评估框架，收集和分析数据以支持报告和决策。确保项目符合组织政策和外部要求，如数据保护和研究伦理。协调多方利益相关者，管理项目时间表和交付成果。", "source": "Indeed", "source_warning": "部分数据源抓取失败：linkedin: 抓取超时，已跳过", "search_keyword": "Data Insights Specialist", "relevance_score": 24, "relevance_reasons": ["标题部分命中: 大数据分析 / data analyst / big data analyst / data science / business intelligence analyst / data insights specialist", "描述命中: data", "描述命中: science", "描述命中: insights", "标题命中: specialist", "描述命中: specialist"], "market_country": "新加坡", "skill_evidence": [{"name": "Innovation Governance Processes", "evidence": "Support the implementation of RC’s innovation governance processes, including documentation of proposals, pilot plans..."}, {"name": "Evaluation Frameworks", "evidence": "Support the development of evaluation frameworks for innovation initiatives, including defining outcomes, indicators,..."}, {"name": "Data Analysis", "evidence": "Collect, organise, and analyse qualitative and quantitative data from pilots and development initiatives to support e..."}, {"name": "Project Management", "evidence": "Coordinate project timelines, deliverables, and stakeholder engagement across innovation initiatives and pilot projects."}, {"name": "Documentation And Reporting", "evidence": "Assist in maintaining documentation related to innovation initiatives, including partnership agreements, pilot protoc..."}], "skills": ["Innovation Governance Processes", "Evaluation Frameworks", "Data Analysis", "Project Management", "Documentation And Reporting"]}, {"title": "Procurement Analyst II - Singapore", "company": "BAE Systems USA", "salary": "$61278 - $104173", "location": "S00", "experience": "不限", "education": "本科及以上", "description": "**Job Description**  \nThe individual should be able to:  \nAnalyze purchase requisitions  \nInitiate RFQs/RFPs review bids  \nSelect suppliers  \nNegotiate terms & conditions, and pricing of materials/services to be procured.  \nProcure materials, equipment, supplies and services of a complex nature based on program-specific requirements and specifications.  \nDevelops purchase orders in accordance with specifications, requirements, work statements and terms and conditions.  \nLead procurement activities and assigned commodities required for the sourcing of complex programs for material, software, and services.  \nWill help develop, support and execute sourcing strategies based on existing and forecasted spend, demand and supply challenges and marketplace conditions, ensuring alignment with the Business Area objectives.  \nSelects or recommends suppliers, creates purchase orders files for review, prepares awards and administers resulting purchase orders.  \nNegotiates additions, deletions, or modifications to purchase orders and resolves invoicing issues.  \nFollow and execute to established and approved procurement policies and procedures in order to provide the best value consistent with quality and service requirements while maintaining good supplier relations.  \nResponsible for Procurement Compliance and Cost/Price Analysis.  \nAbility to work independently, as well as manage cross functional program teams on all procurement related issues; multi-tasking is crucial for success.  \nMust be able to assess, prioritize, drive issues to closure and be assertive when required.  \nExercise discretion and independent judgment in the performance of duties.  \nExhibit best practice work habits and collaborate with other team members to promote operational excellence. Deliver quality customer service to both internal and external customers and foster and maintain good supplier relationships.  \nAdvise management of contractual rights and obligations; compile and analyze data; and maintain historical information and compliant file documentation.  \nNegotiate Terms and Conditions and specific terms and conditions including price, delivery, quality, and performance requirements.  \nSupport proposal preparation activities and execute supplier management activities to provide for acquisition and fulfillment of direct requirements in accordance with company policies, legal requirements, and customer specifications.  \nManage suppliers through all phases of program execution. Respond to supplier inquires, resolve invoice issues, participate on proposal evaluation team(s) in fact finding, technical evaluation, and cost/price analysis.  \nDocuments the entire fact finding and negotiation process. Ensures that discussions, correspondence and agreements with potential and actual suppliers are in accordance with government law, corporate and company policy and program special provisions.  \n  \n**Required Education, Experience, & Skills**  \nTypically Bachelor''s Degree or relevant work experience within DoD contracting Naval experience.  \nExperience in Procurement or Supply Chain or Data Analytics\n  \nAbility to prioritize and multitask within a fast-paced environment with shifting demands  \n  \n**Pay Information**  \nFull-Time Salary Range: $61278 - $104173  \n  \nPlease note: This range is based on our market pay structures. However, individual salaries are determined by a variety of factors including, but not limited to: business considerations, local market conditions, and internal equity, as well as candidate qualifications, such as skills, education, and experience.\n  \n  \nEmployee Benefits: At BAE Systems, we support our employees in all aspects of their life, including their health and financial well-being. Regular employees scheduled to work 20+ hours per week are offered: health, dental, and vision insurance; health savings accounts; a 401(k) savings plan; disability coverage; and life and accident insurance. We also have an employee assistance program, a legal plan, and other perks including discounts on things like home, auto, and pet insurance. Our leave programs include paid time off, paid holidays, as well as other types of leave, including paid parental, military, bereavement, and any applicable federal and state sick leave. Employees may participate in the company recognition program to receive monetary or non-monetary recognition awards. Other incentives may be available based on position level and/or job specifics.  \n  \n**About BAE Systems Platforms & Services**  \nBAE Systems, Inc. is the U.S. subsidiary of BAE Systems plc, an international defense, aerospace and security company which delivers a full range of products and services for air, land and naval forces, as well as advanced electronics, security, information technology solutions and customer support services. Improving the future and protecting lives is an ambitious mission, but it’s what we do at BAE Systems. Working here means using your passion and ingenuity where it counts – defending national security with breakthrough technology, superior products, and intelligence solutions. As you develop the latest technology and defend national security, you will continually hone your skills on a team—making a big impact on a global scale. At BAE Systems, you’ll find a rewarding career that truly makes a difference.  \n  \nThe Platforms & Services (P&S) sector under BAE Systems, Inc does the big stuff: the armored combat vehicles, naval guns, missile launchers, and ship repair…just to name a few. Our employees take pride in the work they do and why they do it. They are on the front lines every day, building our products to protect the lives of those who serve. We may be biased, but we think P&S does some of the coolest work around, and we think you will too.", "requirements": "The candidate must be able to analyze purchase requisitions, negotiate terms and conditions, and manage supplier relationships. They should also be capable of developing purchase orders and ensuring compliance with procurement policies and procedures.", "source": "Indeed", "source_warning": "部分数据源抓取失败：linkedin: 抓取超时，已跳过", "search_keyword": "Big Data Analyst", "relevance_score": 24, "relevance_reasons": ["标题部分命中: 大数据分析 / data analyst / big data analyst / data science / business intelligence analyst / data insights specialist", "描述命中: data", "标题命中: analyst", "描述命中: big", "描述命中: business", "描述命中: intelligence"], "market_country": "新加坡", "skill_evidence": [{"name": "RFQs/RFPs review bids", "evidence": "Initiate RFQs/RFPs review bids"}, {"name": "Negotiate terms & conditions", "evidence": "Negotiate terms & conditions, and pricing of materials/services to be procured."}, {"name": "Develop Purchase Orders", "evidence": "Develops purchase orders in accordance with specifications, requirements, work statements and terms and conditions."}, {"name": "Procurement Compliance", "evidence": "Follow and execute to established and approved procurement policies and procedures"}, {"name": "Cost/Price Analysis", "evidence": "Responsible for Procurement Compliance and Cost/Price Analysis."}, {"name": "Supplier Management", "evidence": "Manage suppliers through all phases of program execution"}, {"name": "Proposal Preparation", "evidence": "Support proposal preparation activities"}, {"name": "Invoicing Issues Resolution", "evidence": "Negotiates additions, deletions, or modifications to purchase orders and resolves invoicing issues"}], "skills": ["RFQs/RFPs review bids", "Negotiate terms & conditions", "Develop Purchase Orders", "Procurement Compliance", "Cost/Price Analysis", "Supplier Management", "Proposal Preparation", "Invoicing Issues Resolution"]}, {"title": "Sr. Worldwide Partner Specialist - Database & Analytics, Data & AI GTM", "company": "Amazon Web Services", "salary": "面议", "location": "Arlington", "experience": "不限", "education": "不限", "description": "**DESCRIPTION**\n---------------\n\nRole Description  \n  \nThe Partner GTM organization within AWS is seeking a Partner Programs Strategy Lead to architect, scale, and orchestrate the end-to-end partner journey for Data & AI across AWS. This role is central to designing the strategic frameworks, programs, and resources that enable partner success throughout their Data & AI journey with AWS. You will be responsible for identifying gaps in the current partner experience, securing cross-organizational investments, and building scalable mechanisms that drive awareness and adoption of the partner journey through both direct partner engagement and field enablement.  \n  \nThis is a highly strategic role requiring exceptional program design capabilities, stakeholder management skills, and the ability to orchestrate complex initiatives across multiple AWS organizations including Partner Core, field teams, and product groups. You''ll serve as the architect of the partner journey, ensuring we have the right programs and resources in place—whether self-managed by our team or delivered through partnerships with other AWS initiatives—to support our preferred partners'' success in Data & AI.  \n  \nA critical component of this role is creating and executing a comprehensive scaling and adoption plan that reaches partners through multiple channels: direct partner engagement, PDM (Partner Development Manager) and PDS (Partner Development Specialist) enablement, regional team coordination, and innovative GenAI tools and interfaces that streamline partner access to journey resources. Additionally, you will be the external face of AWS Data & AI partner programs, serving as a thought leader who continuously refines our approach based on market research, customer insights, and partner feedback.  \n  \nKey job responsibilities  \nPartner Journey Strategy & Continuous Innovation  \n  \nOwn and continuously evolve the end-to-end Data & AI partner journey framework, building on the existing foundation to ensure it remains relevant and competitive  \nConduct systematic gap analysis of current partner programs and experiences to identify improvement opportunities  \nSynthesize partner feedback, market research, and customer insights to inform journey evolution and influence team priorities and strategies  \nMaintain a big-picture view on health of partner investments and support across the journey, identifying where additional resources or program changes are needed  \nCreate measurement frameworks to track partner progression and program effectiveness  \nThought Leadership & External Brand  \n  \nServe as the external face and voice of AWS Data & AI partner programs at industry events, partner conferences, and executive forums  \nCollaborate with market research teams to ensure partner journey design reflects current customer needs, partner capabilities, and market dynamics  \nPublish thought leadership content that articulates the value of the Data & AI partner journey and showcases partner success stories  \nBuild AWS''s reputation as a thought leader in Data & AI partner ecosystem development  \nProgram Orchestration & Investment Securing  \n  \nIdentify and secure the right mix of self-managed programs and cross-AWS initiatives to support the partner journey  \nDevelop compelling business cases to secure budget allocations and organizational capacity commitments for priority partner programs  \nBuild strong partnerships with AWS Partner Core, field organizations, and product teams to leverage existing programs and resources  \nDesign governance models and operating mechanisms to ensure cohesive program delivery across multiple teams  \nAwareness & Adoption Scaling  \n  \nBuild scalable mechanisms to drive awareness of the Data & AI partner journey directly to partners and through PDM/PDS enablement  \nCreate standardized messaging, playbooks, and toolkits that can be leveraged across field teams  \nEstablish feedback loops with partners and field teams to continuously improve the journey experience  \nDesign and implement innovative GenAI tools and interfaces that streamline partner access to journey resources and enable self-service adoption  \nCoordinate with regional teams to ensure localized execution of the scaling and adoption plan  \nStrategic Planning & Team Coordination  \n  \nSupport yearly operational and quarterly planning cycles by providing strategic input on partner journey priorities and resource needs  \nFacilitate team coordination activities to ensure alignment on partner programs strategy  \nEstablish reporting mechanisms to track progress against partner journey metrics and team objectives  \n  \nAbout the team  \nDiverse Experiences  \nAWS values diverse experiences. Even if you do not meet all of the preferred qualifications and skills listed in the job description, we encourage candidates to apply. If your career is just starting, hasn’t followed a traditional path, or includes alternative experiences, don’t let it stop you from applying.\n  \nWhy AWS?  \nAmazon Web Services (AWS) is the world’s most comprehensive and broadly adopted cloud platform. We pioneered cloud computing and never stopped innovating — that’s why customers from the most successful startups to Global 500 companies trust our robust suite of products and services to power their businesses.  \nInclusive Team Culture  \nAWS values curiosity and connection. Our employee-led and company-sponsored affinity groups promote inclusion and empower our people to take pride in what makes us unique. Our inclusion events foster stronger, more collaborative teams. Our continual innovation is fueled by the bold ideas, fresh perspectives, and passionate voices our teams bring to everything we do.  \nMentorship & Career Growth  \nWe’re continuously raising our performance bar as we strive to become Earth’s Best Employer. That’s why you’ll find endless knowledge-sharing, mentorship and other career-advancing resources here to help you develop into a better-rounded professional.\n  \nWork/Life Balance  \nWe value work-life harmony. Achieving success at work should never come at the expense of sacrifices at home, which is why we strive for flexibility as part of our working culture. When we feel supported in the workplace and at home, there’s nothing we can’t achieve.\n\n**BASIC QUALIFICATIONS**\n------------------------\n\n* 5+ years of developing, negotiating and executing business agreements experience\n* 5+ years of Go-To-Market, Business Development, Sales, or Consulting experience\n* 5+ years of working with Data & AI related technologies, including, but not limited to, AI/ML, GenAI, Analytics, Database, and/or Storage experience\n* Experience developing strategies that influence leadership decisions at the organizational level\n* Experience working and communicating with multiple stakeholders and cross functional teams including direct and channel marketing, solution architect teams, product management and account management teams\n* Experience working with stakeholders to plan and execute programs that are strategic in nature\n* Experience in external enterprise customer-facing role as a technical lead, with strong oral and written communication skills, presenting to both large and small audiences\n* Experience in strategic planning\n\n**PREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS**\n----------------------------\n\n* Knowledge of AWS services, market segments, customer base and industry verticals\n* Experience with analytical tools and ability to dive deep into metrics and reporting\n* 4+ years of market research analyst, product manager, or equivalent experience\n\n  \nAmazon is an equal opportunity employer and does not discriminate on the basis of protected veteran status, disability, or other legally protected status.  \n  \nLos Angeles County applicants: Job duties for this position include: work safely and cooperatively with other employees, supervisors, and staff; adhere to standards of excellence despite stressful conditions; communicate effectively and respectfully with employees, supervisors, and staff to ensure exceptional customer service; and follow all federal, state, and local laws and Company policies. Criminal history may have a direct, adverse, and negative relationship with some of the material job duties of this position. These include the duties and responsibilities listed above, as well as the abilities to adhere to company policies, exercise sound judgment, effectively manage stress and work safely and respectfully with others, exhibit trustworthiness and professionalism, and safeguard business operations and the Company’s reputation. Pursuant to the Los Angeles County Fair Chance Ordinance, we will consider for employment qualified applicants with arrest and conviction records.  \n  \nPursuant to the San Francisco Fair Chance Ordinance, we will consider for employment qualified applicants with arrest and conviction records.  \n  \nOur inclusive culture empowers Amazonians to deliver the best results for our customers. If you have a disability and need a workplace accommodation or adjustment during the application and hiring process, including support for the interview or onboarding process, please visit https://amazon.jobs/content/en/how-we-hire/accommodations for more information. If the country/region you’re applying in isn’t listed, please contact your Recruiting Partner.\n\nThe base salary range for this position is listed below. Your Amazon package will include sign-on payments and restricted stock units (RSUs). Final compensation will be determined based on factors including experience, qualifications, and location. Amazon also offers comprehensive benefits including health insurance (medical, dental, vision, prescription, Basic Life & AD&D insurance and option for Supplemental life plans, EAP, Mental Health Support, Medical Advice Line, Flexible Spending Accounts, Adoption and Surrogacy Reimbursement coverage), 401(k) matching, paid time off, and parental leave. Learn more about our benefits at https://amazon.jobs/en/benefits.\n\n  \nUSA, CA, Mountain View - 162,700.00 - 220,200.00 USD annually  \nUSA, CA, San Francisco - 162,700.00 - 220,200.00 USD annually  \nUSA, NY, New York - 162,700.00 - 220,200.00 USD annually  \nUSA, TX, Dallas - 147,900.00 - 200,100.00 USD annually  \nUSA, VA, Arlington - 147,900.00 - 200,100.00 USD annually  \nUSA, WA, Seattle - 147,900.00 - 200,100.00 USD annually", "requirements": "负责设计和执行数据与AI合作伙伴旅程的扩展和采用计划；建立合作伙伴旅程的测量框架以跟踪合作伙伴进展和项目效果；与市场研究团队合作确保合作伙伴旅程设计符合客户需求和市场动态。", "source": "Indeed", "source_warning": "部分数据源抓取失败：linkedin: 抓取超时，已跳过；部分搜索词抓取失败：大数据分析: linkedin: 抓取超时，已跳过", "search_keyword": "Big Data Analyst", "relevance_score": 46, "relevance_reasons": ["标题部分命中: 大数据分析 / data analyst / big data analyst / data science / analytics specialist / data insights", "标题命中: data", "描述命中: data", "描述命中: analyst", "描述命中: big", "标题命中: analytics", "描述命中: analytics", "标题命中: specialist", "描述命中: specialist", "描述命中: insights"], "market_country": "美国", "skill_evidence": [{"name": "GenAI Tools And Interfaces", "evidence": "innovative GenAI tools and interfaces that streamline partner access to journey resources"}], "skills": ["GenAI Tools And Interfaces"]}, {"title": "Sr. Customer Insights Analyst, eero CX", "company": "Amazon.com", "salary": "面议", "location": "San Francisco", "experience": "不限", "education": "不限", "description": "**DESCRIPTION**\n---------------\n\nAt eero, our mission is to serve as the central nervous system of the home. While we began by revolutionizing home WiFi, we aim to create comprehensive solutions that serve both wireless and wired connectivity needs for customers and businesses across the globe.Our cross-functional team, spanning hardware, software, and manufacturing, develops advanced Ethernet switching and gateway products, alongside state of the art security features, to complement our award-winning mesh WiFi systems. As an Amazon company, we combine the best of startup culture with the resources and stability of one of the world''s leading technology companies. Our team builds products that customers love - from mesh routers to high-performance wired networking devices - and we''re looking for you to join us in shaping the future of the connected home.  \n  \neero is seeking an experienced Customer Insights Analyst to join our Customer Experience organization. This role combines deep analytical expertise with business intelligence engineering to transform customer support data into actionable insights that drive operational excellence and enhance customer experience. The ideal candidate will build scalable analytics solutions, develop predictive models, and partner with leadership to make data-driven decisions that improve efficiency and customer satisfaction.  \n  \nKey job responsibilities  \nAs a Sr. Customer Insights Analyst, you will serve as the analytical backbone of our Customer Experience organization, translating complex data into clear insights that inform strategy and operations. You''ll design and maintain business intelligence infrastructure, create self-service analytics tools for support leaders, and uncover patterns in customer behavior that drive product and process improvements.\n  \n  \n\n* This role requires both technical depth in data engineering and analytics, as well as the business acumen to understand what questions matter most to our customers and organization.\n\n  \n\n* You will establish and maintain the key performance indicators that measure Customer Support effectiveness. This includes defining metrics, setting targets, building tracking systems, and creating regular reporting cadences. You''ll work with support leadership to ensure KPIs align with organizational goals and provide meaningful insights into team performance, customer experience, and operational efficiency.\n\n  \n\n* You''ll develop automated alerting systems that flag anomalies or concerning trends, enabling proactive intervention before issues escalate. You''ll also conduct regular KPI reviews with stakeholders, explaining trends and recommending actions based on data.\n\n  \n\n* You will work closely with Customer Support leadership, Product teams, Engineering, and cross-functional stakeholders to identify opportunities for improvement, measure the impact of initiatives, and build a culture of data-driven decision-making. Your work will directly influence how we support millions of eero customers and shape the future of our support operations.\n\n  \nA day in the life  \nAn expert in advanced analytics — You are passionate about turning data into actionable insights that will inform product development and strategy.  \nAn innovator.\n  \n  \nYou seek to develop a deep understanding of our metrics, reporting tools, and data structures in order to identify and drive resolution of issues, provide actionable intelligence with existing metrics or identify, develop, and propose new metrics, dashboards, scorecards or new tools.  \n  \nYou are a motivated self-starter, comfortable navigating through ambiguity to evaluate complex data, analyze data from multiple angles, and deliver insights that directly impact the business.  \n  \nYou are intellectually curious. You seek to learn and understand business needs, and are always looking to translate data to real world tangible offerings.  \n  \nYou have excellent interpersonal skills to collaborate with cross-functional partners to share knowledge, communicate findings, and integrate feedback.  \n  \nAbout the team  \nInterested in exploring career opportunities with eero?\n  \n  \nVisit our careers page to view all open positions: https://www.amazon.jobs/content/en/teams/devices-services/hardware-eero?country%5B%5D=US&keyword%5B%5D=eero\n\n**BASIC QUALIFICATIONS**\n------------------------\n\n* 10+ years of professional or military experience\n* 5+ years of SQL experience\n* 1+ years of SQL, ETL or Oracle experience\n* 1+ years of processing large, multi-dimensional datasets from multiple sources experience\n* 1+ years of performing statistical analysis experience\n* 1+ years of developing automated reporting experience\n* Experience programming to extract, transform and clean large (multi-TB) data sets\n* Experience with theory and practice of design of experiments and statistical analysis of results\n* Experience with AWS technologies\n* Experience in scripting for automation (e.g. Python) and advanced SQL skills.\n* Experience with theory and practice of information retrieval, data science, machine learning and data mining\n\n**PREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS**\n----------------------------\n\n* Experience working directly with business stakeholders to translate between data and business needs\n* Experience managing, analyzing and communicating results to senior leadership\n\n  \nAmazon is an equal opportunity employer and does not discriminate on the basis of protected veteran status, disability, or other legally protected status.  \n  \nLos Angeles County applicants: Job duties for this position include: work safely and cooperatively with other employees, supervisors, and staff; adhere to standards of excellence despite stressful conditions; communicate effectively and respectfully with employees, supervisors, and staff to ensure exceptional customer service; and follow all federal, state, and local laws and Company policies. Criminal history may have a direct, adverse, and negative relationship with some of the material job duties of this position. These include the duties and responsibilities listed above, as well as the abilities to adhere to company policies, exercise sound judgment, effectively manage stress and work safely and respectfully with others, exhibit trustworthiness and professionalism, and safeguard business operations and the Company’s reputation. Pursuant to the Los Angeles County Fair Chance Ordinance, we will consider for employment qualified applicants with arrest and conviction records.  \n  \nPursuant to the San Francisco Fair Chance Ordinance, we will consider for employment qualified applicants with arrest and conviction records.  \n  \nOur inclusive culture empowers Amazonians to deliver the best results for our customers. If you have a disability and need a workplace accommodation or adjustment during the application and hiring process, including support for the interview or onboarding process, please visit https://amazon.jobs/content/en/how-we-hire/accommodations for more information. If the country/region you’re applying in isn’t listed, please contact your Recruiting Partner.\n\nThe base salary range for this position is listed below. Your Amazon package will include sign-on payments and restricted stock units (RSUs). Final compensation will be determined based on factors including experience, qualifications, and location. Amazon also offers comprehensive benefits including health insurance (medical, dental, vision, prescription, Basic Life & AD&D insurance and option for Supplemental life plans, EAP, Mental Health Support, Medical Advice Line, Flexible Spending Accounts, Adoption and Surrogacy Reimbursement coverage), 401(k) matching, paid time off, and parental leave. Learn more about our benefits at https://amazon.jobs/en/benefits.\n\n  \nUSA, CA, San Francisco - 149,900.00 - 202,800.00 USD annually  \nUSA, WA, Seattle - 130,400.00 - 176,300.00 USD annually", "requirements": "具备深厚的数据分析和业务智能工程能力，能够将客户支持数据转化为可操作的见解。需要建立和维护关键绩效指标以衡量客户支持效果，并开发自动化警报系统以识别异常或令人担忧的趋势。", "source": "Indeed", "source_warning": "部分数据源抓取失败：linkedin: 抓取超时，已跳过；部分搜索词抓取失败：大数据分析: linkedin: 抓取超时，已跳过", "search_keyword": "Data Analyst", "relevance_score": 38, "relevance_reasons": ["标题部分命中: 大数据分析 / data analyst / big data analyst / data science / analytics specialist / data insights", "描述命中: data", "标题命中: analyst", "描述命中: analyst", "描述命中: big", "描述命中: science", "描述命中: analytics", "标题命中: insights", "描述命中: insights"], "market_country": "美国", "skill_evidence": [{"name": "Business Intelligence Engineering", "evidence": "transform customer support data into actionable insights that drive operational excellence and enhance customer exper..."}, {"name": "Data Engineering", "evidence": "technical depth in data engineering and analytics"}, {"name": "Analytics", "evidence": "deep analytical expertise with business intelligence engineering to transform customer support data into actionable i..."}, {"name": "Predictive Modeling", "evidence": "develop predictive models"}, {"name": "Automated Alerting Systems", "evidence": "develop automated alerting systems that flag anomalies or concerning trends"}], "skills": ["Business Intelligence Engineering", "Data Engineering", "Analytics", "Predictive Modeling", "Automated Alerting Systems"]}, {"title": "Sr. Customer Insights Analyst, eero CX", "company": "Amazon.com", "salary": "面议", "location": "Seattle", "experience": "不限", "education": "不限", "description": "**DESCRIPTION**\n---------------\n\nAt eero, our mission is to serve as the central nervous system of the home. While we began by revolutionizing home WiFi, we aim to create comprehensive solutions that serve both wireless and wired connectivity needs for customers and businesses across the globe.Our cross-functional team, spanning hardware, software, and manufacturing, develops advanced Ethernet switching and gateway products, alongside state of the art security features, to complement our award-winning mesh WiFi systems. As an Amazon company, we combine the best of startup culture with the resources and stability of one of the world''s leading technology companies. Our team builds products that customers love - from mesh routers to high-performance wired networking devices - and we''re looking for you to join us in shaping the future of the connected home.  \n  \neero is seeking an experienced Customer Insights Analyst to join our Customer Experience organization. This role combines deep analytical expertise with business intelligence engineering to transform customer support data into actionable insights that drive operational excellence and enhance customer experience. The ideal candidate will build scalable analytics solutions, develop predictive models, and partner with leadership to make data-driven decisions that improve efficiency and customer satisfaction.  \n  \nKey job responsibilities  \nAs a Sr. Customer Insights Analyst, you will serve as the analytical backbone of our Customer Experience organization, translating complex data into clear insights that inform strategy and operations. You''ll design and maintain business intelligence infrastructure, create self-service analytics tools for support leaders, and uncover patterns in customer behavior that drive product and process improvements.\n  \n  \n\n* This role requires both technical depth in data engineering and analytics, as well as the business acumen to understand what questions matter most to our customers and organization.\n\n  \n\n* You will establish and maintain the key performance indicators that measure Customer Support effectiveness. This includes defining metrics, setting targets, building tracking systems, and creating regular reporting cadences. You''ll work with support leadership to ensure KPIs align with organizational goals and provide meaningful insights into team performance, customer experience, and operational efficiency.\n\n  \n\n* You''ll develop automated alerting systems that flag anomalies or concerning trends, enabling proactive intervention before issues escalate. You''ll also conduct regular KPI reviews with stakeholders, explaining trends and recommending actions based on data.\n\n  \n\n* You will work closely with Customer Support leadership, Product teams, Engineering, and cross-functional stakeholders to identify opportunities for improvement, measure the impact of initiatives, and build a culture of data-driven decision-making. Your work will directly influence how we support millions of eero customers and shape the future of our support operations.\n\n  \nA day in the life  \nAn expert in advanced analytics — You are passionate about turning data into actionable insights that will inform product development and strategy.  \nAn innovator.\n  \n  \nYou seek to develop a deep understanding of our metrics, reporting tools, and data structures in order to identify and drive resolution of issues, provide actionable intelligence with existing metrics or identify, develop, and propose new metrics, dashboards, scorecards or new tools.  \n  \nYou are a motivated self-starter, comfortable navigating through ambiguity to evaluate complex data, analyze data from multiple angles, and deliver insights that directly impact the business.  \n  \nYou are intellectually curious. You seek to learn and understand business needs, and are always looking to translate data to real world tangible offerings.  \n  \nYou have excellent interpersonal skills to collaborate with cross-functional partners to share knowledge, communicate findings, and integrate feedback.  \n  \nAbout the team  \nInterested in exploring career opportunities with eero?\n  \n  \nVisit our careers page to view all open positions: https://www.amazon.jobs/content/en/teams/devices-services/hardware-eero?country%5B%5D=US&keyword%5B%5D=eero\n\n**BASIC QUALIFICATIONS**\n------------------------\n\n* 10+ years of professional or military experience\n* 5+ years of SQL experience\n* 1+ years of SQL, ETL or Oracle experience\n* 1+ years of processing large, multi-dimensional datasets from multiple sources experience\n* 1+ years of performing statistical analysis experience\n* 1+ years of developing automated reporting experience\n* Experience programming to extract, transform and clean large (multi-TB) data sets\n* Experience with theory and practice of design of experiments and statistical analysis of results\n* Experience with AWS technologies\n* Experience in scripting for automation (e.g. Python) and advanced SQL skills.\n* Experience with theory and practice of information retrieval, data science, machine learning and data mining\n\n**PREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS**\n----------------------------\n\n* Experience working directly with business stakeholders to translate between data and business needs\n* Experience managing, analyzing and communicating results to senior leadership\n\n  \nAmazon is an equal opportunity employer and does not discriminate on the basis of protected veteran status, disability, or other legally protected status.  \n  \nLos Angeles County applicants: Job duties for this position include: work safely and cooperatively with other employees, supervisors, and staff; adhere to standards of excellence despite stressful conditions; communicate effectively and respectfully with employees, supervisors, and staff to ensure exceptional customer service; and follow all federal, state, and local laws and Company policies. Criminal history may have a direct, adverse, and negative relationship with some of the material job duties of this position. These include the duties and responsibilities listed above, as well as the abilities to adhere to company policies, exercise sound judgment, effectively manage stress and work safely and respectfully with others, exhibit trustworthiness and professionalism, and safeguard business operations and the Company’s reputation. Pursuant to the Los Angeles County Fair Chance Ordinance, we will consider for employment qualified applicants with arrest and conviction records.  \n  \nPursuant to the San Francisco Fair Chance Ordinance, we will consider for employment qualified applicants with arrest and conviction records.  \n  \nOur inclusive culture empowers Amazonians to deliver the best results for our customers. If you have a disability and need a workplace accommodation or adjustment during the application and hiring process, including support for the interview or onboarding process, please visit https://amazon.jobs/content/en/how-we-hire/accommodations for more information. If the country/region you’re applying in isn’t listed, please contact your Recruiting Partner.\n\nThe base salary range for this position is listed below. Your Amazon package will include sign-on payments and restricted stock units (RSUs). Final compensation will be determined based on factors including experience, qualifications, and location. Amazon also offers comprehensive benefits including health insurance (medical, dental, vision, prescription, Basic Life & AD&D insurance and option for Supplemental life plans, EAP, Mental Health Support, Medical Advice Line, Flexible Spending Accounts, Adoption and Surrogacy Reimbursement coverage), 401(k) matching, paid time off, and parental leave. Learn more about our benefits at https://amazon.jobs/en/benefits.\n\n  \nUSA, CA, San Francisco - 149,900.00 - 202,800.00 USD annually  \nUSA, WA, Seattle - 130,400.00 - 176,300.00 USD annually", "requirements": "具备深厚的数据分析和业务智能工程能力，能够将客户支持数据转化为可操作的见解。需要建立和维护关键绩效指标，开发自动化警报系统，并与跨职能团队合作以推动改进。", "source": "Indeed", "source_warning": "部分数据源抓取失败：linkedin: 抓取超时，已跳过；部分搜索词抓取失败：大数据分析: linkedin: 抓取超时，已跳过", "search_keyword": "Data Analyst", "relevance_score": 38, "relevance_reasons": ["标题部分命中: 大数据分析 / data analyst / big data analyst / data science / analytics specialist / data insights", "描述命中: data", "标题命中: analyst", "描述命中: analyst", "描述命中: big", "描述命中: science", "描述命中: analytics", "标题命中: insights", "描述命中: insights"], "market_country": "美国", "skill_evidence": [{"name": "Business Intelligence Engineering", "evidence": "transform customer support data into actionable insights that drive operational excellence and enhance customer exper..."}, {"name": "Data Engineering", "evidence": "technical depth in data engineering and analytics"}, {"name": "Analytics", "evidence": "deep analytical expertise with business intelligence engineering"}, {"name": "Automated Alerting Systems", "evidence": "develop automated alerting systems that flag anomalies or concerning trends"}, {"name": "Predictive Models", "evidence": "develop predictive models"}], "skills": ["Business Intelligence Engineering", "Data Engineering", "Analytics", "Automated Alerting Systems", "Predictive Models"]}, {"title": "Senior Leader, ProServe AI/GenAI/Agentic Specialists, Healthcare and Life Sciences", "company": "Amazon Web Services", "salary": "面议", "location": "Arlington", "experience": "不限", "education": "不限", "description": "**DESCRIPTION**\n---------------\n\nThe Amazon Web Services (AWS) Professional Services (ProServe) team is seeking an experienced technology leader to build our Healthcare and Life Sciences (HCLS) Agentic AI Specialist Team. This is a team of ProServe Cloud Architects (PCAs) with expertise at the intersection of HCLS domains (e.g. Research, Clinical Development, Commercial, Manufacturing, Enterprise IT) and AI, GenAI and Agentic AI. In this position, you''ll counsel senior HCLS executives on designing AI transformation programs that deliver business outcomes. You''ll develop perspectives on how AI, GenAI, and Agentic AI unlock business value, creating repeatable partnership models and tools that scale across industry customers.  \n  \nYou''ll collaborate with colleagues in the ProServe HCLS team, GenAI Innovation Center, and external Partners, working backwards from customer outcomes to design fit-for-purpose solutions and programs.  \n  \nThis role requires expertise in AI, GenAI, and Agentic AI within HCLS, paired with experience in business development or professional services. You think big, innovate, focus on customer objectives, execute at high standards, and maintain continuous curiosity.  \n  \nKey job responsibilities  \n\n* Building and leading a team that continually maintains leading-edge expertise in AI, GenAI and Agentic AI transformation in HCLS\n\n  \n\n* Counseling HCLS executive customers to explore the art of the possible with AI and to push the frontiers of innovation to achieve breakthrough outcomes\n\n  \n\n* Collaborating with internal teams, including GenAI Innovation Center, Applied AI team, and the HCLS Sales team to innovate AWS solutions, services, accelerators, and demos to meet evolving customer needs\n\n  \n\n* Designing complex, scalable, and secure AWS AI, GenAI and Agentic AI solutions to achieve customer business outcomes (CBOs)\n\n  \n\n* Driving large complex opportunities, either personally or through your team, from ideation, through vision building and scoping, all the way to closure and participate in the delivery\n\n  \n\n* Acting as a thought leader and trusted advisor to customers and internal colleagues on industry AI, GenAI, Agentic AI trends and emerging technologies\n\n  \nAbout the team  \nAbout AWS:\n  \nDiverse Experiences: AWS values diverse experiences. Even if you do not meet all of the preferred qualifications and skills listed in the job below, we encourage candidates to apply. If your career is just starting, hasn’t followed a traditional path, or includes alternative experiences, don’t let it stop you from applying.\n  \n  \nWhy AWS? Amazon Web Services (AWS) is the world’s most comprehensive and broadly adopted cloud platform. We pioneered cloud computing and never stopped innovating — that’s why customers from the most successful startups to Global 500 companies trust our robust suite of products and services to power their businesses.\n  \n  \nInclusive Team Culture - Here at AWS, it’s in our nature to learn and be curious. Our employee-led affinity groups foster a culture of inclusion that empower us to be proud of our differences. Ongoing events and learning experiences, including our Conversations on Race and Ethnicity (CORE) and AmazeCon (diversity) conferences, inspire us to never stop embracing our uniqueness.\n  \n  \nMentorship & Career Growth - We’re continuously raising our performance bar as we strive to become Earth’s Best Employer. That’s why you’ll find endless knowledge-sharing, mentorship and other career-advancing resources here to help you develop into a better-rounded professional.\n  \n  \nWork/Life Balance - We value work-life harmony. Achieving success at work should never come at the expense of sacrifices at home, which is why we strive for flexibility as part of our working culture. When we feel supported in the workplace and at home, there’s nothing we can’t achieve in the cloud.\n  \n  \n10044\n\n**BASIC QUALIFICATIONS**\n------------------------\n\n* 7+ years of working with Data & AI related technologies, including, but not limited to, AI/ML, GenAI, Analytics, Database, and/or Storage experience\n* 7+ years of solving problems with technology in the Healthcare/Life Sciences Industry experience\n* 3+ years of team leadership experience\n* Bachelor''s degree in Computer Science, Engineering, Mathematics, or a related field\n* 5+ years Professional services business development and/or technology sales experience\n\n**PREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS**\n----------------------------\n\n* Knowledge of security and compliance standards including HIPAA and GDPR\n* Advanced technology degree or AWS Professional level certifications (e.g., Solutions Architect Professional, DevOps Engineer Professional, GenAI Developer Professional) preferred\n* Deep understanding of AWS services, including Bedrock, AgentCore, SageMaker, Kiro, and compute, storage, networking, security, databases, machine learning, and serverless technologies\n* Excellent communication skills, with the ability to explain technical concepts to both technical and non-technical audiences as part of pre-sales motion\n* Experience shaping large, complex AI, GenAI and Agentic AI transformation programs in HCLS\n\n  \nAmazon is an equal opportunity employer and does not discriminate on the basis of protected veteran status, disability, or other legally protected status.  \n  \nOur inclusive culture empowers Amazonians to deliver the best results for our customers. If you have a disability and need a workplace accommodation or adjustment during the application and hiring process, including support for the interview or onboarding process, please visit https://amazon.jobs/content/en/how-we-hire/accommodations for more information. If the country/region you’re applying in isn’t listed, please contact your Recruiting Partner.\n\nThe base salary range for this position is listed below. Your Amazon package will include sign-on payments and restricted stock units (RSUs). Final compensation will be determined based on factors including experience, qualifications, and location. Amazon also offers comprehensive benefits including health insurance (medical, dental, vision, prescription, Basic Life & AD&D insurance and option for Supplemental life plans, EAP, Mental Health Support, Medical Advice Line, Fl