telligence projects\n* Develop standardized metrics to evaluate and benchmark pertaining to short and long term network planning and forecasting\n* Communicate complex analysis and insights to stakeholders and business leaders, both verbally and in writing\n\n**BASIC QUALIFICATIONS**\n------------------------\n\n* High school or equivalent diploma\n* Knowledge of Excel at an intermediate level (e.g., pivot tables & charts, multiple criteria lookups, nested logical/IF formulas, data cleansing, array formulas, etc.)\n* Experience managing large data sets and utilizing to drive performance and process improvements\n\n**PREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS**\n----------------------------\n\n* Bachelor''s degree\n* 1+ years of program management, logistics, operations, supply chain, transportation, or equivalent experience\n* 1+ years of management experience\n* Experience with SQL\n\n  \nAmazon is an equal opportunity employer and does not discriminate on the basis of protected veteran status, disability, or other legally protected status.  \n  \nOur inclusive culture empowers Amazonians to deliver the best results for our customers. If you have a disability and need a workplace accommodation or adjustment during the application and hiring process, including support for the interview or onboarding process, please visit https://amazon.jobs/content/en/how-we-hire/accommodations for more information. If the country/region you’re applying in isn’t listed, please contact your Recruiting Partner.\n\nThe base salary range for this position is listed below. Your Amazon package will include sign-on payments and restricted stock units (RSUs). Final compensation will be determined based on factors including experience, qualifications, and location. Amazon also offers comprehensive benefits including health insurance (medical, dental, vision, prescription, Basic Life & AD&D insurance and option for Supplemental life plans, EAP, Mental Health Support, Medical Advice Line, Flexible Spending Accounts, Adoption and Surrogacy Reimbursement coverage), 401(k) matching, paid time off, and parental leave. Learn more about our benefits at https://amazon.jobs/en/benefits.\n\n  \nUSA, AZ, Tempe - 25.00 - 32.00 USD hourly  \nUSA, WA, Bellevue - 25.00 - 32.00 USD hourly", "requirements": "Perform complex data analysis to identify opportunities for cost reduction and efficiency improvements. Design and develop KPIs to monitor analysis and provide strategic insights. Ability to manage reoccurring and ad-hoc business intelligence projects. Experience with SQL is preferred.", "source": "Indeed", "source_warning": "部分数据源抓取失败：linkedin: 抓取超时，已跳过；部分搜索词抓取失败：大数据分析: linkedin: 抓取超时，已跳过", "search_keyword": "Data Analyst", "relevance_score": 35, "relevance_reasons": ["标题部分命中: 大数据分析 / data analyst / big data analyst / data science / analytics specialist / data insights", "描述命中: data", "标题命中: analyst", "描述命中: analyst", "描述命中: big", "标题命中: analytics", "描述命中: analytics", "描述命中: insights"], "market_country": "美国", "skill_evidence": [{"name": "Data Analysis", "evidence": "Perform complex data analysis to identify opportunities to reduce fulfillment costs as well as improve efficiencies a..."}, {"name": "KPIs Design", "evidence": "Design, develop and establish KPIs to monitor analysis and provide strategic insights to drive growth and performance"}, {"name": "Business Intelligence Projects", "evidence": "Ability to perform/own reoccurring and ad-hoc business intelligence projects"}, {"name": "SQL", "evidence": "Experience with SQL"}], "skills": ["Data Analysis", "KPIs Design", "Business Intelligence Projects", "SQL"]}, {"title": "Transportation Analyst, STRIDE Analytics, ATS", "company": "Amazon.com", "salary": "25.00 - 32.00 USD hourly", "location": "Tempe", "experience": "不限", "education": "硕士及以上", "description": "**DESCRIPTION**\n---------------\n\nAmazon Transportation Services (ATS) Line Haul is looking for a talented Transportation Analyst who will own analytics and develop solutions to drive insights and optimization for Network Planning and Forecasting. As a member of this team, you will have an opportunity to be a thought leader in Amazon Logistics and work with a group of talented program managers, product managers, research scientists, software developers, and business leaders to design the Amazon network of the future.\n  \n  \nThis position requires superior analytical thinking, ability to quickly approach large ambiguous problems and apply analytics, technical and engineering expertise to rapidly analyze, validate, visualize, prototype and deliver solutions. This position also requires significant cross functional work and integration with transportation, tech, operations and finance. Successful candidates must thrive in a fast-paced environment\n  \n  \nAs you further your career at Amazon, you will focus on improving corporate reporting frameworks and data visualization. You will analyze performance data, discover and solve real world problems and build metrics and business cases to improve decision making. We are focused on your success and want to build strong leaders within Amazon Transportation Services. You can expect to leverage your analytical skills and have full ownership of the projects you work on.\n  \n  \n#NALH  \n  \nKey job responsibilities  \n\n* Perform complex data analysis to identify opportunities to reduce fulfillment costs as well as improve efficiencies and customer experience\n* Design, develop and establish KPIs to monitor analysis and provide strategic insights to drive growth and performance\n* Ability to perform/own reoccurring and ad-hoc business intelligence projects\n* Develop standardized metrics to evaluate and benchmark pertaining to short and long term network planning and forecasting\n* Communicate complex analysis and insights to stakeholders and business leaders, both verbally and in writing\n\n**BASIC QUALIFICATIONS**\n------------------------\n\n* High school or equivalent diploma\n* Knowledge of Excel at an intermediate level (e.g., pivot tables & charts, multiple criteria lookups, nested logical/IF formulas, data cleansing, array formulas, etc.)\n* Experience managing large data sets and utilizing to drive performance and process improvements\n\n**PREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS**\n----------------------------\n\n* Bachelor''s degree\n* 1+ years of program management, logistics, operations, supply chain, transportation, or equivalent experience\n* 1+ years of management experience\n* Experience with SQL\n\n  \nAmazon is an equal opportunity employer and does not discriminate on the basis of protected veteran status, disability, or other legally protected status.  \n  \nOur inclusive culture empowers Amazonians to deliver the best results for our customers. If you have a disability and need a workplace accommodation or adjustment during the application and hiring process, including support for the interview or onboarding process, please visit https://amazon.jobs/content/en/how-we-hire/accommodations for more information. If the country/region you’re applying in isn’t listed, please contact your Recruiting Partner.\n\nThe base salary range for this position is listed below. Your Amazon package will include sign-on payments and restricted stock units (RSUs). Final compensation will be determined based on factors including experience, qualifications, and location. Amazon also offers comprehensive benefits including health insurance (medical, dental, vision, prescription, Basic Life & AD&D insurance and option for Supplemental life plans, EAP, Mental Health Support, Medical Advice Line, Flexible Spending Accounts, Adoption and Surrogacy Reimbursement coverage), 401(k) matching, paid time off, and parental leave. Learn more about our benefits at https://amazon.jobs/en/benefits.\n\n  \nUSA, AZ, Tempe - 25.00 - 32.00 USD hourly  \nUSA, WA, Bellevue - 25.00 - 32.00 USD hourly", "requirements": "Perform complex data analysis to identify opportunities for cost reduction and efficiency improvements. Design and develop KPIs to monitor analysis and provide strategic insights. Manage reoccurring and ad-hoc business intelligence projects. Experience with SQL is preferred.", "source": "Indeed", "source_warning": "部分数据源抓取失败：linkedin: 抓取超时，已跳过；部分搜索词抓取失败：大数据分析: linkedin: 抓取超时，已跳过", "search_keyword": "Data Analyst", "relevance_score": 35, "relevance_reasons": ["标题部分命中: 大数据分析 / data analyst / big data analyst / data science / analytics specialist / data insights", "描述命中: data", "标题命中: analyst", "描述命中: analyst", "描述命中: big", "标题命中: analytics", "描述命中: analytics", "描述命中: insights"], "market_country": "美国", "skill_evidence": [{"name": "Data Analysis", "evidence": "Perform complex data analysis to identify opportunities to reduce fulfillment costs as well as improve efficiencies a..."}, {"name": "KPIs Design", "evidence": "Design, develop and establish KPIs to monitor analysis and provide strategic insights to drive growth and performance"}, {"name": "Business Intelligence Projects", "evidence": "Ability to perform/own reoccurring and ad-hoc business intelligence projects"}, {"name": "SQL", "evidence": "Experience with SQL"}], "skills": ["Data Analysis", "KPIs Design", "Business Intelligence Projects", "SQL"]}, {"title": "Location Analyst, WWGS Growth & Development", "company": "Amazon.com", "salary": "面议", "location": "Seattle", "experience": "不限", "education": "不限", "description": "**DESCRIPTION**\n---------------\n\nAt Amazon we are passionate about creating a shopping experience that customers will love. If you’re interested in a fast-paced, ambiguous, and highly-collaborative environment that’s more start-up than big company, we want to talk to you.  \n  \nWorldwide Grocery Stores (WWGS), Growth & Development team is seeking a Location Analyst to support strategic site selection and location planning across all Amazon physical retail concepts. This role sits at the intersection of advanced analytics, real estate strategy, and customer experience, leveraging geospatial intelligence and demographic modeling to identify optimal locations that drive growth and deliver exceptional value to customers.  \n  \nAs a Location Analyst, you will be responsible for conducting comprehensive market assessments, building sophisticated analytical models, and providing data-driven recommendations that inform multi-million dollar real estate investment decisions. You''ll work with GIS technology, large-scale demographic datasets, and proprietary customer data to evaluate trade areas, forecast site performance, and identify expansion opportunities across diverse retail formats and geographies.  \n  \nThis role requires a unique blend of technical expertise and business acumen. You''ll translate complex spatial data and statistical analyses into clear, actionable insights for cross-functional partners including Real Estate Development, Operations, Finance, and senior leadership. Your work will directly influence where and how Amazon serves communities nationwide, ensuring our physical retail presence meets customers where they are with the right format, in the right location, at the right time.  \n  \nThe ideal candidate thrives in a fast-paced environment where speed and accuracy are equally critical. You''ll balance rigorous analytical standards with the urgency required in competitive real estate markets, often delivering rapid assessments on time-sensitive opportunities while maintaining the data quality and methodological rigor that inform high-stakes decisions. This position offers the opportunity to shape Amazon''s physical retail footprint and make a measurable impact on how millions of customers access Amazon''s products and services in their daily lives.  \n  \nKey job responsibilities  \n\n* Develop and maintain demographic datasets and geospatial tools to support location analysis across Amazon''s physical retail concepts.\n* Execute site screening analyses and produce comprehensive reports that evaluate market potential, trade area characteristics, and competitive dynamics.\n* Apply advanced statistical methods and GIS software to calculate demographic metrics, forecast performance, and assess site viability.\n* Create thematic maps and data visualizations that communicate complex spatial patterns and insights to stakeholders.\n* Audit data for accuracy and consistency, ensuring high-quality inputs for location decision-making.\n* Build and maintain research tracking systems, historical databases, and reporting frameworks for site analysis.\n* Partner with Real Estate, Operations, and Finance teams to provide data-driven recommendations on location strategy.\n* Conduct market research and competitive analysis to identify expansion opportunities across retail formats.\n* Support forecasting activities including site visits, market assessments, and performance modeling.\n* Drive process improvements through automation and optimization of analytical workflows using ETL tools.\n* Present findings and recommendations to senior leadership, translating technical analysis into actionable business insights.\n* Move quickly to deliver timely insights that enable rapid decision-making on time-sensitive real estate opportunities.\n\n  \nA day in the life  \nYour morning starts analyzing demographic data for urgent site assessments, running GIS models to evaluate trade areas across Amazon''s retail concepts. You collaborate with Real Estate and Operations teams, presenting location recommendations backed by statistical forecasts. Afternoons involve automating analytical workflows, auditing data quality, and preparing executive presentations. You respond rapidly to competitive opportunities, delivering actionable insights that inform multi-million dollar real estate decisions. Every analysis connects back to one goal: identifying optimal locations that best serve customers across Amazon''s physical retail portfolio.  \n  \nAbout the team  \nOur mission is to leverage new technology, comprehensive data analysis, and deep market insights to help WWGS identify and secure optimal locations for the Amazon omnichannel offer. We provide actionable insights through site forecasting, competitive intelligence, and mapping and data visualization for store and geo strategy.\n  \n  \nWe value independent thinking with a focus on providing our customers high quality products informed by extensive research and experience.\n\n**BASIC QUALIFICATIONS**\n------------------------\n\n* Bachelor''s degree or above in statistics, business analytics, data analytics, data science, computer science or related field\n* Knowledge of at least one data-focused technology tool, such as Python, SQL, Alteryx, Amazon QuickSight, or similar\n* Experience analyzing data and creating reports for leadership\n* Experience managing multiple projects and priorities across teams in a fast-paced, deadline-driven environment\n* 3+ years of professional experience in location analytics, site selection, or geospatial analysis\n* Advanced proficiency with GIS software (ArcGIS, QGIS, or similar platforms)\n* Experience with data modeling\n\n**PREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS**\n----------------------------\n\n* Knowledge of data analysis languages (e.g., R, Stata, Python, etc.) or other statistical software\n* Experience in data science, business analytics, business intelligence, or similar experience in big data environments\n* Experience working with, presenting to and influencing senior executives up to VP level\n* Experience in retail site selection, real estate analytics, or location planning\n* Experience in demographic analysis and market research methodologies\n\n  \nAmazon is an equal opportunity employer and does not discriminate on the basis of protected veteran status, disability, or other legally protected status.  \n  \nOur inclusive culture empowers Amazonians to deliver the best results for our customers. If you have a disability and need a workplace accommodation or adjustment during the application and hiring process, including support for the interview or onboarding process, please visit https://amazon.jobs/content/en/how-we-hire/accommodations for more information. If the country/region you’re applying in isn’t listed, please contact your Recruiting Partner.\n\nThe base salary range for this position is listed below. Your Amazon package will include sign-on payments and restricted stock units (RSUs). Final compensation will be determined based on factors including experience, qualifications, and location. Amazon also offers comprehensive benefits including health insurance (medical, dental, vision, prescription, Basic Life & AD&D insurance and option for Supplemental life plans, EAP, Mental Health Support, Medical Advice Line, Flexible Spending Accounts, Adoption and Surrogacy Reimbursement coverage), 401(k) matching, paid time off, and parental leave. Learn more about our benefits at https://amazon.jobs/en/benefits.\n\n  \nUSA, IL, Chicago - 74,300.00 - 130,100.00 USD annually  \nUSA, MA, WALTHAM - 74,300.00 - 130,100.00 USD annually  \nUSA, TN, Nashville - 66,900.00 - 117,000.00 USD annually  \nUSA, TX, Austin - 74,300.00 - 130,100.00 USD annually  \nUSA, WA, Seattle - 82,700.00 - 130,100.00 USD annually", "requirements": "具备高级统计方法和GIS软件的应用能力，能够处理大规模人口统计数据和客户数据。需要能够将复杂的空间数据和分析结果转化为清晰的业务见解，并与跨职能团队合作提供数据驱动的建议。同时，需具备快速交付及时洞察的能力以支持紧迫的房地产机会决策。", "source": "Indeed", "source_warning": "部分数据源抓取失败：linkedin: 抓取超时，已跳过；部分搜索词抓取失败：大数据分析: linkedin: 抓取超时，已跳过", "search_keyword": "Data Analyst", "relevance_score": 30, "relevance_reasons": ["标题部分命中: 大数据分析 / data analyst / big data analyst / data science / analytics specialist / data insights", "描述命中: data", "标题命中: analyst", "描述命中: analyst", "描述命中: big", "描述命中: science", "描述命中: analytics", "描述命中: insights"], "market_country": "美国", "skill_evidence": [{"name": "GIS Technology", "evidence": "You''ll work with GIS technology, large-scale demographic datasets, and proprietary customer data to evaluate trade ar..."}, {"name": "Demographic Datasets", "evidence": "You''ll work with GIS technology, large-scale demographic datasets, and proprietary customer data to evaluate trade ar..."}, {"name": "Proprietory Customer Data", "evidence": "You''ll work with GIS technology, large-scale demographic datasets, and proprietary customer data to evaluate trade ar..."}, {"name": "ETL Tools", "evidence": "Drive process improvements through automation and optimization of analytical workflows using ETL tools."}, {"name": "Data Visualization", "evidence": "Create thematic maps and data visualizations that communicate complex spatial patterns and insights to stakeholders."}, {"name": "Statistical Analysis", "evidence": "Apply advanced statistical methods and GIS software to calculate demographic metrics, forecast performance, and asses..."}, {"name": "Market Research", "evidence": "Conduct market research and competitive analysis to identify expansion opportunities across retail formats."}, {"name": "Competitive Analysis", "evidence": "Conduct market research and competitive analysis to identify expansion opportunities across retail formats."}, {"name": "Forecasting", "evidence": "Support forecasting activities including site visits, market assessments, and performance modeling."}, {"name": "Process Improvement", "evidence": "Drive process improvements through automation and optimization of analytical workflows using ETL tools."}, {"name": "Data Auditing", "evidence": "Audit data for accuracy and consistency, ensuring high-quality inputs for location decision-making."}], "skills": ["GIS Technology", "Demographic Datasets", "Proprietory Customer Data", "ETL Tools", "Data Visualization", "Statistical Analysis", "Market Research", "Competitive Analysis", "Forecasting", "Process Improvement", "Data Auditing"]}, {"title": "Location Analyst, WWGS Growth & Development", "company": "Amazon.com", "salary": "面议", "location": "Chicago", "experience": "不限", "education": "不限", "description": "**DESCRIPTION**\n---------------\n\nAt Amazon we are passionate about creating a shopping experience that customers will love. If you’re interested in a fast-paced, ambiguous, and highly-collaborative environment that’s more start-up than big company, we want to talk to you.  \n  \nWorldwide Grocery Stores (WWGS), Growth & Development team is seeking a Location Analyst to support strategic site selection and location planning across all Amazon physical retail concepts. This role sits at the intersection of advanced analytics, real estate strategy, and customer experience, leveraging geospatial intelligence and demographic modeling to identify optimal locations that drive growth and deliver exceptional value to customers.  \n  \nAs a Location Analyst, you will be responsible for conducting comprehensive market assessments, building sophisticated analytical models, and providing data-driven recommendations that inform multi-million dollar real estate investment decisions. You''ll work with GIS technology, large-scale demographic datasets, and proprietary customer data to evaluate trade areas, forecast site performance, and identify expansion opportunities across diverse retail formats and geographies.  \n  \nThis role requires a unique blend of technical expertise and business acumen. You''ll translate complex spatial data and statistical analyses into clear, actionable insights for cross-functional partners including Real Estate Development, Operations, Finance, and senior leadership. Your work will directly influence where and how Amazon serves communities nationwide, ensuring our physical retail presence meets customers where they are with the right format, in the right location, at the right time.  \n  \nThe ideal candidate thrives in a fast-paced environment where speed and accuracy are equally critical. You''ll balance rigorous analytical standards with the urgency required in competitive real estate markets, often delivering rapid assessments on time-sensitive opportunities while maintaining the data quality and methodological rigor that inform high-stakes decisions. This position offers the opportunity to shape Amazon''s physical retail footprint and make a measurable impact on how millions of customers access Amazon''s products and services in their daily lives.  \n  \nKey job responsibilities  \n\n* Develop and maintain demographic datasets and geospatial tools to support location analysis across Amazon''s physical retail concepts.\n* Execute site screening analyses and produce comprehensive reports that evaluate market potential, trade area characteristics, and competitive dynamics.\n* Apply advanced statistical methods and GIS software to calculate demographic metrics, forecast performance, and assess site viability.\n* Create thematic maps and data visualizations that communicate complex spatial patterns and insights to stakeholders.\n* Audit data for accuracy and consistency, ensuring high-quality inputs for location decision-making.\n* Build and maintain research tracking systems, historical databases, and reporting frameworks for site analysis.\n* Partner with Real Estate, Operations, and Finance teams to provide data-driven recommendations on location strategy.\n* Conduct market research and competitive analysis to identify expansion opportunities across retail formats.\n* Support forecasting activities including site visits, market assessments, and performance modeling.\n* Drive process improvements through automation and optimization of analytical workflows using ETL tools.\n* Present findings and recommendations to senior leadership, translating technical analysis into actionable business insights.\n* Move quickly to deliver timely insights that enable rapid decision-making on time-sensitive real estate opportunities.\n\n  \nA day in the life  \nYour morning starts analyzing demographic data for urgent site assessments, running GIS models to evaluate trade areas across Amazon''s retail concepts. You collaborate with Real Estate and Operations teams, presenting location recommendations backed by statistical forecasts. Afternoons involve automating analytical workflows, auditing data quality, and preparing executive presentations. You respond rapidly to competitive opportunities, delivering actionable insights that inform multi-million dollar real estate decisions. Every analysis connects back to one goal: identifying optimal locations that best serve customers across Amazon''s physical retail portfolio.  \n  \nAbout the team  \nOur mission is to leverage new technology, comprehensive data analysis, and deep market insights to help WWGS identify and secure optimal locations for the Amazon omnichannel offer. We provide actionable insights through site forecasting, competitive intelligence, and mapping and data visualization for store and geo strategy.\n  \n  \nWe value independent thinking with a focus on providing our customers high quality products informed by extensive research and experience.\n\n**BASIC QUALIFICATIONS**\n------------------------\n\n* Bachelor''s degree or above in statistics, business analytics, data analytics, data science, computer science or related field\n* Knowledge of at least one data-focused technology tool, such as Python, SQL, Alteryx, Amazon QuickSight, or similar\n* Experience analyzing data and creating reports for leadership\n* Experience managing multiple projects and priorities across teams in a fast-paced, deadline-driven environment\n* 3+ years of professional experience in location analytics, site selection, or geospatial analysis\n* Advanced proficiency with GIS software (ArcGIS, QGIS, or similar platforms)\n* Experience with data modeling\n\n**PREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS**\n----------------------------\n\n* Knowledge of data analysis languages (e.g., R, Stata, Python, etc.) or other statistical software\n* Experience in data science, business analytics, business intelligence, or similar experience in big data environments\n* Experience working with, presenting to and influencing senior executives up to VP level\n* Experience in retail site selection, real estate analytics, or location planning\n* Experience in demographic analysis and market research methodologies\n\n  \nAmazon is an equal opportunity employer and does not discriminate on the basis of protected veteran status, disability, or other legally protected status.  \n  \nOur inclusive culture empowers Amazonians to deliver the best results for our customers. If you have a disability and need a workplace accommodation or adjustment during the application and hiring process, including support for the interview or onboarding process, please visit https://amazon.jobs/content/en/how-we-hire/accommodations for more information. If the country/region you’re applying in isn’t listed, please contact your Recruiting Partner.\n\nThe base salary range for this position is listed below. Your Amazon package will include sign-on payments and restricted stock units (RSUs). Final compensation will be determined based on factors including experience, qualifications, and location. Amazon also offers comprehensive benefits including health insurance (medical, dental, vision, prescription, Basic Life & AD&D insurance and option for Supplemental life plans, EAP, Mental Health Support, Medical Advice Line, Flexible Spending Accounts, Adoption and Surrogacy Reimbursement coverage), 401(k) matching, paid time off, and parental leave. Learn more about our benefits at https://amazon.jobs/en/benefits.\n\n  \nUSA, IL, Chicago - 74,300.00 - 130,100.00 USD annually  \nUSA, MA, WALTHAM - 74,300.00 - 130,100.00 USD annually  \nUSA, TN, Nashville - 66,900.00 - 117,000.00 USD annually  \nUSA, TX, Austin - 74,300.00 - 130,100.00 USD annually  \nUSA, WA, Seattle - 82,700.00 - 130,100.00 USD annually", "requirements": "具备高级统计方法和GIS软件的应用能力，能够处理大规模人口统计数据和客户数据。需要能够将复杂的空间数据和分析结果转化为清晰的可操作见解，并与跨职能团队合作提供数据驱动的建议。同时，需具备快速交付及时洞察的能力，以支持紧迫的房地产机会决策。", "source": "Indeed", "source_warning": "部分数据源抓取失败