rtunities across diverse retail formats and geographies.  \n  \nThis role requires a unique blend of technical expertise and business acumen. You''ll translate complex spatial data and statistical analyses into clear, actionable insights for cross-functional partners including Real Estate Development, Operations, Finance, and senior leadership. Your work will directly influence where and how Amazon serves communities nationwide, ensuring our physical retail presence meets customers where they are with the right format, in the right location, at the right time.  \n  \nThe ideal candidate thrives in a fast-paced environment where speed and accuracy are equally critical. You''ll balance rigorous analytical standards with the urgency required in competitive real estate markets, often delivering rapid assessments on time-sensitive opportunities while maintaining the data quality and methodological rigor that inform high-stakes decisions. This position offers the opportunity to shape Amazon''s physical retail footprint and make a measurable impact on how millions of customers access Amazon''s products and services in their daily lives.  \n  \nKey job responsibilities  \n\n* Develop and maintain demographic datasets and geospatial tools to support location analysis across Amazon''s physical retail concepts.\n* Execute site screening analyses and produce comprehensive reports that evaluate market potential, trade area characteristics, and competitive dynamics.\n* Apply advanced statistical methods and GIS software to calculate demographic metrics, forecast performance, and assess site viability.\n* Create thematic maps and data visualizations that communicate complex spatial patterns and insights to stakeholders.\n* Audit data for accuracy and consistency, ensuring high-quality inputs for location decision-making.\n* Build and maintain research tracking systems, historical databases, and reporting frameworks for site analysis.\n* Partner with Real Estate, Operations, and Finance teams to provide data-driven recommendations on location strategy.\n* Conduct market research and competitive analysis to identify expansion opportunities across retail formats.\n* Support forecasting activities including site visits, market assessments, and performance modeling.\n* Drive process improvements through automation and optimization of analytical workflows using ETL tools.\n* Present findings and recommendations to senior leadership, translating technical analysis into actionable business insights.\n* Move quickly to deliver timely insights that enable rapid decision-making on time-sensitive real estate opportunities.\n\n  \nA day in the life  \nYour morning starts analyzing demographic data for urgent site assessments, running GIS models to evaluate trade areas across Amazon''s retail concepts. You collaborate with Real Estate and Operations teams, presenting location recommendations backed by statistical forecasts. Afternoons involve automating analytical workflows, auditing data quality, and preparing executive presentations. You respond rapidly to competitive opportunities, delivering actionable insights that inform multi-million dollar real estate decisions. Every analysis connects back to one goal: identifying optimal locations that best serve customers across Amazon''s physical retail portfolio.  \n  \nAbout the team  \nOur mission is to leverage new technology, comprehensive data analysis, and deep market insights to help WWGS identify and secure optimal locations for the Amazon omnichannel offer. We provide actionable insights through site forecasting, competitive intelligence, and mapping and data visualization for store and geo strategy.\n  \n  \nWe value independent thinking with a focus on providing our customers high quality products informed by extensive research and experience.\n\n**BASIC QUALIFICATIONS**\n------------------------\n\n* Bachelor''s degree or above in statistics, business analytics, data analytics, data science, computer science or related field\n* Knowledge of at least one data-focused technology tool, such as Python, SQL, Alteryx, Amazon QuickSight, or similar\n* Experience analyzing data and creating reports for leadership\n* Experience managing multiple projects and priorities across teams in a fast-paced, deadline-driven environment\n* 3+ years of professional experience in location analytics, site selection, or geospatial analysis\n* Advanced proficiency with GIS software (ArcGIS, QGIS, or similar platforms)\n* Experience with data modeling\n\n**PREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS**\n----------------------------\n\n* Knowledge of data analysis languages (e.g., R, Stata, Python, etc.) or other statistical software\n* Experience in data science, business analytics, business intelligence, or similar experience in big data environments\n* Experience working with, presenting to and influencing senior executives up to VP level\n* Experience in retail site selection, real estate analytics, or location planning\n* Experience in demographic analysis and market research methodologies\n\n  \nAmazon is an equal opportunity employer and does not discriminate on the basis of protected veteran status, disability, or other legally protected status.  \n  \nOur inclusive culture empowers Amazonians to deliver the best results for our customers. If you have a disability and need a workplace accommodation or adjustment during the application and hiring process, including support for the interview or onboarding process, please visit https://amazon.jobs/content/en/how-we-hire/accommodations for more information. If the country/region you’re applying in isn’t listed, please contact your Recruiting Partner.\n\nThe base salary range for this position is listed below. Your Amazon package will include sign-on payments and restricted stock units (RSUs). Final compensation will be determined based on factors including experience, qualifications, and location. Amazon also offers comprehensive benefits including health insurance (medical, dental, vision, prescription, Basic Life & AD&D insurance and option for Supplemental life plans, EAP, Mental Health Support, Medical Advice Line, Flexible Spending Accounts, Adoption and Surrogacy Reimbursement coverage), 401(k) matching, paid time off, and parental leave. Learn more about our benefits at https://amazon.jobs/en/benefits.\n\n  \nUSA, IL, Chicago - 74,300.00 - 130,100.00 USD annually  \nUSA, MA, WALTHAM - 74,300.00 - 130,100.00 USD annually  \nUSA, TN, Nashville - 66,900.00 - 117,000.00 USD annually  \nUSA, TX, Austin - 74,300.00 - 130,100.00 USD annually  \nUSA, WA, Seattle - 82,700.00 - 130,100.00 USD annually", "requirements": "具备高级统计方法和GIS软件的应用能力，能够处理大规模人口统计数据和客户数据；能够开发和维护人口数据集及地理空间工具；能够通过数据可视化传达复杂的空间模式和见解；能够使用ETL工具优化分析流程。", "source": "Indeed", "source_warning": "部分数据源抓取失败：linkedin: 抓取超时，已跳过；部分搜索词抓取失败：大数据分析: linkedin: 抓取超时，已跳过", "search_keyword": "Data Analyst", "relevance_score": 30, "relevance_reasons": ["标题部分命中: 大数据分析 / data analyst / big data analyst / data science / analytics specialist / data insights", "描述命中: data", "标题命中: analyst", "描述命中: analyst", "描述命中: big", "描述命中: science", "描述命中: analytics", "描述命中: insights"], "market_country": "美国", "skill_evidence": [{"name": "Demographic Datasets", "evidence": "Develop and maintain demographic datasets and geospatial tools to support location analysis across Amazon''s physical..."}, {"name": "Geospatial Tools", "evidence": "Develop and maintain demographic datasets and geospatial tools to support location analysis across Amazon''s physical..."}, {"name": "GIS Technology", "evidence": "Apply advanced statistical methods and GIS software to calculate demographic metrics, forecast performance, and asses..."}, {"name": "Demographic Modeling", "evidence": "leveraging geospatial intelligence and demographic modeling to identify optimal locations that drive growth and deliv..."}, {"name": "Data Visualization", "evidence": "Create thematic maps and data visualizations that communicate complex spatial patterns and insights to stakeholders."}, {"name": "ETL Tools", "evidence": "Drive process improvements through automation and optimization of analytical workflows using ETL tools."}, {"name": "Statistical Methods", "evidence": "Apply advanced statistical methods and GIS software to calculate demographic metrics, forecast performance, and asses..."}], "skills": ["Demographic Datasets", "Geospatial Tools", "GIS Technology", "Demographic Modeling", "Data Visualization", "ETL Tools", "Statistical Methods"]}, {"title": "Sr. Sales Compensation Analyst, Ads Sales Incentive Compensation", "company": "Amazon.com", "salary": "面议", "location": "Seattle", "experience": "不限", "education": "本科及以上", "description": "**DESCRIPTION**\n---------------\n\nThe Amazon Advertising Sales Incentive Compensation team is seeking a Sr. Sales Compensation Analyst to drive analytics throughout the Ads incentive compensation program. The charter for our team is to Enable the growth of Amazon Ads through effective sales compensation design, governance and operations.  \n  \nThe ideal candidate for the role will be an exceptionally strong analytical thinker who excels in written and verbal communication, data analysis, modeling and process improvements. They will demonstrate teamwork, relationship building and the ability to influence at all levels of the organization, while thriving in a fast-paced dynamic environment that has a considerable amount of ambiguity. They help deliver data-driven insights that will be foundational to optimizing sales planning, performance targets, and sales compensation for Amazon Ads. They will have deep experience with variable compensation plans and associated analytics to drive data driven decisions. They will partner with Amazon Ads’ sales incentive compensation design, planning, policy, and enablement teams.  \n  \nKey job responsibilities  \nKey job responsibilities  \n\n* Develop a deep understanding of the foundational data and key business drivers to Amazon Ads variable compensation.\n* Design and implement a comprehensive reporting & analytical roadmap to derive key decisions. Build out capabilities for Gen AI to deliver insights into existing data, tools and workstreams. Automate repeated processes around monthly, quarterly and annual processes.\n* Compensation cost controllership: Cost and administer in plan and above plan incentives (e.g., Quotas, SPIF, MBO). Support financial budgeting and forecasting processes across total portfolio.\n* Strong verbal and written communications to share findings with business leaders, finance, and technical teams to influence decision-making and product enhancements.\n* Have a passion for sales compensation and the impact the work will have on all customers.\n* Quality and timely insights. Scale quarterly insights that provide details to leaders throughout organization. Ability to provide team and seller level trends and performance to teams that provide actionable insights.\n* Automation. Build out capabilities for AI to deliver insights into existing data, tools and workstreams. Automate repeated processes around monthly, quarterly and annual processes.\n* Cross Functional Collaboration. Partner with finance team to align compensation impact to financial plan. Run analysis around correlation of SIC payouts to overall financial performance.\n\n  \nAbout the team  \nWe are the innovative minds behind Amazon Advertising''s sales compensation ecosystem. Our team sits at the intersection of technology, finance, and human motivation, creating programs that attract, retain, and inspire top sales talent. We are passionate about designing compensation strategies that not only reward performance, but also drive meaningful business impact.\n\n**BASIC QUALIFICATIONS**\n------------------------\n\n* Bachelor''s degree in Business Administration, Finance, Economics, Computer Science, Engineering, or related field\n* 5+ years of finance, business management and sales operations experience\n\n**PREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS**\n----------------------------\n\n* Experience working within a high-growth, technology company\n* Experience developing business analytics or equivalent\n* Experience using Microsoft Excel to manipulate and analyze data\n* Experience with data visualization software (e.g., AWS QuickSight or Tableau) or open-source project\n* Experience developing and implementing systems/tools utilized for CRM, variable compensation, revenue reporting, forecasting, Salesforce automation, etc.\n* Experience with sales CRM tools such as Salesforce or similar software\n\n  \nAmazon is an equal opportunity employer and does not discriminate on the basis of protected veteran status, disability, or other legally protected status.  \n  \nLos Angeles County applicants: Job duties for this position include: work safely and cooperatively with other employees, supervisors, and staff; adhere to standards of excellence despite stressful conditions; communicate effectively and respectfully with employees, supervisors, and staff to ensure exceptional customer service; and follow all federal, state, and local laws and Company policies. Criminal history may have a direct, adverse, and negative relationship with some of the material job duties of this position. These include the duties and responsibilities listed above, as well as the abilities to adhere to company policies, exercise sound judgment, effectively manage stress and work safely and respectfully with others, exhibit trustworthiness and professionalism, and safeguard business operations and the Company’s reputation. Pursuant to the Los Angeles County Fair Chance Ordinance, we will consider for employment qualified applicants with arrest and conviction records.  \n  \nOur inclusive culture empowers Amazonians to deliver the best results for our customers. If you have a disability and need a workplace accommodation or adjustment during the application and hiring process, including support for the interview or onboarding process, please visit https://amazon.jobs/content/en/how-we-hire/accommodations for more information. If the country/region you’re applying in isn’t listed, please contact your Recruiting Partner.\n\nThe base salary range for this position is listed below. Your Amazon package will include sign-on payments and restricted stock units (RSUs). Final compensation will be determined based on factors including experience, qualifications, and location. Amazon also offers comprehensive benefits including health insurance (medical, dental, vision, prescription, Basic Life & AD&D insurance and option for Supplemental life plans, EAP, Mental Health Support, Medical Advice Line, Flexible Spending Accounts, Adoption and Surrogacy Reimbursement coverage), 401(k) matching, paid time off, and parental leave. Learn more about our benefits at https://amazon.jobs/en/benefits.\n\n  \nUSA, CA, Culver City - 88,100.00 - 154,100.00 USD annually  \nUSA, NY, New York - 96,900.00 - 169,500.00 USD annually  \nUSA, WA, Seattle - 88,100.00 - 154,100.00 USD annually", "requirements": "Develop a deep understanding of the foundational data and key business drivers to Amazon Ads variable compensation. Design and implement a comprehensive reporting & analytical roadmap to derive key decisions. Partner with finance team to align compensation impact to financial plan.", "source": "Indeed", "source_warning": "部分数据源抓取失败：linkedin: 抓取超时，已跳过；部分搜索词抓取失败：大数据分析: linkedin: 抓取超时，已跳过", "search_keyword": "Data Analyst", "relevance_score": 30, "relevance_reasons": ["标题部分命中: 大数据分析 / data analyst / big data analyst / data science / analytics specialist / data insights", "描述命中: data", "标题命中: analyst", "描述命中: analyst", "描述命中: big", "描述命中: science", "描述命中: analytics", "描述命中: insights"], "market_country": "美国", "skill_evidence": [{"name": "Gen AI", "evidence": "Build out capabilities for Gen AI to deliver insights into existing data, tools and workstreams"}, {"name": "Data Analysis", "evidence