e benefits including health insurance (medical, dental, vision, prescription, Basic Life & AD&D insurance and option for Supplemental life plans, EAP, Mental Health Support, Medical Advice Line, Flexible Spending Accounts, Adoption and Surrogacy Reimbursement coverage), 401(k) matching, paid time off, and parental leave. Learn more about our benefits at https://amazon.jobs/en/benefits.\n\n  \nUSA, WA, Bellevue - 82,700.00 - 117,100.00 USD annually  \nUSA, WA, Redmond - 82,700.00 - 117,100.00 USD annually", "requirements": "Support Multimodal Logistics and Warehousing by consolidating financial information, forecasting, reporting and analysis. Partner with the team designing the global logistic network to deliver terrestrial and orbital infrastructure. Need to be strategic, analytical, and have the demonstrated ability to work effectively with cross-functional teams in a start-up like environment.", "source": "Indeed", "source_warning": "部分数据源抓取失败：linkedin: 抓取超时，已跳过；部分搜索词抓取失败：大数据分析: linkedin: 抓取超时，已跳过", "search_keyword": "Big Data Analyst", "relevance_score": 24, "relevance_reasons": ["标题部分命中: 大数据分析 / data analyst / big data analyst / data science / analytics specialist / data insights", "描述命中: data", "标题命中: analyst", "描述命中: analyst", "描述命中: big", "描述命中: insights"], "market_country": "美国", "skill_evidence": [{"name": "Financial Modeling", "evidence": "Develop and implement long range business planning. Develop financial models for new business concepts and resulting..."}, {"name": "P&L management", "evidence": "Build out and enhance P&L models for new and existing businesses, develop business insights and KPI dashboards, and l..."}, {"name": "Data Mining", "evidence": "Work with big data and transforming it into insights and information."}, {"name": "Reporting Tools", "evidence": "Develop financial models for new business concepts and resulting financial impact to help drive data driven decision..."}, {"name": "SQL", "evidence": "Experience working with large-scale data mining and reporting tools (examples: SQL, MS Access, Essbase, Cognos) and o..."}, {"name": "MS Access", "evidence": "Experience working with large-scale data mining and reporting tools (examples: SQL, MS Access, Essbase, Cognos) and o..."}, {"name": "Essbase", "evidence": "Experience working with large-scale data mining and reporting tools (examples: SQL, MS Access, Essbase, Cognos) and o..."}, {"name": "Cognos", "evidence": "Experience working with large-scale data mining and reporting tools (examples: SQL, MS Access, Essbase, Cognos) and o..."}, {"name": "Oracle", "evidence": "Experience working with large-scale data mining and reporting tools (examples: SQL, MS Access, Essbase, Cognos) and o..."}, {"name": "SAP", "evidence": "Experience working with large-scale data mining and reporting tools (examples: SQL, MS Access, Essbase, Cognos) and o..."}, {"name": "Lawson", "evidence": "Experience working with large-scale data mining and reporting tools (examples: SQL, MS Access, Essbase, Cognos) and o..."}, {"name": "JD Edwards", "evidence": "Experience working with large-scale data mining and reporting tools (examples: SQL, MS Access, Essbase, Cognos) and o..."}], "skills": ["Financial Modeling", "P&L management", "Data Mining", "Reporting Tools", "SQL", "MS Access", "Essbase", "Cognos", "Oracle", "SAP", "Lawson", "JD Edwards"]}, {"title": "Business Analyst II, Relay Supply Products and Technology", "company": "Amazon.com", "salary": "面议", "location": "Nashville", "experience": "不限", "education": "本科及以上", "description": "**DESCRIPTION**\n---------------\n\nWould you like to be part of a team focused on driving innovation in the transportation industry? If you have great instincts and a drive to build new mechanisms and simplify process across teams, you may be just right for the Business Analyst role. It’s no secret that Amazon relies on its technology to deliver millions of packages every day to its customers – on time, with low cost. We are seeking candidates with an entrepreneurial spirit who are quick learners and comfortable operating in a fast-paced environment.  \n  \nYou should be detail-oriented and comfortable performing both qualitative and quantitative analysis. You know and love working with business intelligence tools (excel, visualization tools, and SQL), and can effectively partner with business leaders to deep-dive complex business problems. This position will require working cross-functionally and with a diverse set of stakeholders.  \n  \nAs you further your career as a Business Analyst at Amazon, you will focus on improving corporate reporting frameworks and data visualization. You will analyze performance data, discover and solve real world problems and build metrics and business cases to improve decision making. We are focused on your success and want to build strong leaders within Amazon Transportation Services. You can expect to leverage your analytical skills and have full ownership of the projects you work on.  \n  \nKey job responsibilities  \n\n* Own the design, development, and maintenance of ongoing and ad-hoc metrics, reports, and analyses, to drive key business decisions\n* Enable effective decision making by retrieving and aggregating data from multiple sources and compiling it into a digestible and actionable format\n* Define the data elements to enable analytical and reporting capabilities, and work cross-functionally with other research teams when needed\n* Design and influence operational best practices for reporting and analytics to enable the team to scale as we grow\n* Develop standardized metrics to evaluate and benchmark pertaining to Click-Stream KPIs and reoccurring Adhoc needs\n* Participate in strategic & tactical planning discussions\n* Communicate complex insights to stakeholders, both verbally and in writing\n\n  \nAbout the team  \nWe are a team of product managers and BA''s, who work closely with SDE''s, research scientists and business leaders.\n\n**BASIC QUALIFICATIONS**\n------------------------\n\n* 3+ years of Excel (including VBA, pivot tables, array functions, power pivots, etc.) and data visualization tools such as Tableau experience\n* 3+ years of business or financial analysis experience\n* Bachelor''s degree or equivalent\n* Experience defining requirements and using data and metrics to draw business insights\n* Experience with Excel\n* Experience with SQL\n* Experience making business recommendations and influencing stakeholders\n\n**PREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS**\n----------------------------\n\n* Experience in transportation and supply chain\n\n  \nAmazon is an equal opportunity employer and does not discriminate on the basis of protected veteran status, disability, or other legally protected status.  \n  \nOur inclusive culture empowers Amazonians to deliver the best results for our customers. If you have a disability and need a workplace accommodation or adjustment during the application and hiring process, including support for the interview or onboarding process, please visit https://amazon.jobs/content/en/how-we-hire/accommodations for more information. If the country/region you’re applying in isn’t listed, please contact your Recruiting Partner.\n\nThe base salary range for this position is listed below. Your Amazon package will include sign-on payments and restricted stock units (RSUs). Final compensation will be determined based on factors including experience, qualifications, and location. Amazon also offers comprehensive benefits including health insurance (medical, dental, vision, prescription, Basic Life & AD&D insurance and option for Supplemental life plans, EAP, Mental Health Support, Medical Advice Line, Flexible Spending Accounts, Adoption and Surrogacy Reimbursement coverage), 401(k) matching, paid time off, and parental leave. Learn more about our benefits at https://amazon.jobs/en/benefits.\n\n  \nUSA, TN, Nashville - 66,900.00 - 117,000.00 USD annually  \nUSA, WA, Bellevue - 82,700.00 - 130,100.00 USD annually", "requirements": "Candidates must have 3+ years of business or financial analysis experience and a Bachelor''s degree or equivalent. They should be proficient in Excel (including VBA, pivot tables, array functions, power pivots) and data visualization tools such as Tableau, with experience in SQL.", "source": "Indeed", "source_warning": "部分数据源抓取失败：linkedin: 抓取超时，已跳过；部分搜索词抓取失败：大数据分析: linkedin: 抓取超时，已跳过", "search_keyword": "Data Analyst", "relevance_score": 24, "relevance_reasons": ["标题部分命中: 大数据分析 / data analyst / big data analyst / data science / analytics specialist / data insights", "描述命中: data", "标题命中: analyst", "描述命中: analyst", "描述命中: analytics", "描述命中: insights"], "market_country": "美国", "skill_evidence": [{"name": "Excel", "evidence": "You know and love working with business intelligence tools (excel, visualization tools, and SQL)"}, {"name": "VBA", "evidence": "3+ years of Excel (including VBA, pivot tables, array functions, power pivots, etc.) and data visualization tools suc..."}, {"name": "Pivot Tables", "evidence": "3+ years of Excel (including VBA, pivot tables, array functions, power pivots, etc.) and data visualization tools suc..."}, {"name": "Array Functions", "evidence": "3+ years of Excel (including VBA, pivot tables, array functions, power pivots, etc.) and data visualization tools suc..."}, {"name": "Power Pivots", "evidence": "3+ years of Excel (including VBA, pivot tables, array functions, power pivots, etc.) and data visualization tools suc..."}, {"name": "Data Visualization Tools", "evidence": "You know and love working with business intelligence tools (excel, visualization tools, and SQL)"}, {"name": "Tableau", "evidence": "data visualization tools such as Tableau experience"}, {"name": "SQL", "evidence": "You know and love working with business intelligence tools (excel, visualization tools, and SQL)"}], "skills": ["Excel", "VBA", "Pivot Tables", "Array Functions", "Power Pivots", "Data Visualization Tools", "Tableau", "SQL"]}, {"titl