and reporting capabilities, and work cross-functionally with other research teams when needed\n* Design and influence operational best practices for reporting and analytics to enable the team to scale as we grow\n* Develop standardized metrics to evaluate and benchmark pertaining to Click-Stream KPIs and reoccurring Adhoc needs\n* Participate in strategic & tactical planning discussions\n* Communicate complex insights to stakeholders, both verbally and in writing\n\n  \nAbout the team  \nWe are a team of product managers and BA''s, who work closely with SDE''s, research scientists and business leaders.\n\n**BASIC QUALIFICATIONS**\n------------------------\n\n* 3+ years of Excel (including VBA, pivot tables, array functions, power pivots, etc.) and data visualization tools such as Tableau experience\n* 3+ years of business or financial analysis experience\n* Bachelor''s degree or equivalent\n* Experience defining requirements and using data and metrics to draw business insights\n* Experience with Excel\n* Experience with SQL\n* Experience making business recommendations and influencing stakeholders\n\n**PREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS**\n----------------------------\n\n* Experience in transportation and supply chain\n\n  \nAmazon is an equal opportunity employer and does not discriminate on the basis of protected veteran status, disability, or other legally protected status.  \n  \nOur inclusive culture empowers Amazonians to deliver the best results for our customers. If you have a disability and need a workplace accommodation or adjustment during the application and hiring process, including support for the interview or onboarding process, please visit https://amazon.jobs/content/en/how-we-hire/accommodations for more information. If the country/region you’re applying in isn’t listed, please contact your Recruiting Partner.\n\nThe base salary range for this position is listed below. Your Amazon package will include sign-on payments and restricted stock units (RSUs). Final compensation will be determined based on factors including experience, qualifications, and location. Amazon also offers comprehensive benefits including health insurance (medical, dental, vision, prescription, Basic Life & AD&D insurance and option for Supplemental life plans, EAP, Mental Health Support, Medical Advice Line, Flexible Spending Accounts, Adoption and Surrogacy Reimbursement coverage), 401(k) matching, paid time off, and parental leave. Learn more about our benefits at https://amazon.jobs/en/benefits.\n\n  \nUSA, TN, Nashville - 66,900.00 - 117,000.00 USD annually  \nUSA, WA, Bellevue - 82,700.00 - 130,100.00 USD annually", "requirements": "具备3年以上Excel和数据可视化工具（如Tableau）经验，熟悉SQL，有业务或财务分析经验，持有学士学位或同等学历。需要能够使用数据和指标定义需求并提出商业建议，同时具备跨职能协作能力。", "source": "Indeed", "source_warning": "部分数据源抓取失败：linkedin: 抓取超时，已跳过；部分搜索词抓取失败：大数据分析: linkedin: 抓取超时，已跳过", "search_keyword": "Data Analyst", "relevance_score": 24, "relevance_reasons": ["标题部分命中: 大数据分析 / data analyst / big data analyst / data science / analytics specialist / data insights", "描述命中: data", "标题命中: analyst", "描述命中: analyst", "描述命中: analytics", "描述命中: insights"], "market_country": "美国", "skill_evidence": [{"name": "Excel", "evidence": "You know and love working with business intelligence tools (excel, visualization tools, and SQL)"}, {"name": "VBA", "evidence": "3+ years of Excel (including VBA, pivot tables, array functions, power pivots, etc.) and data visualization tools suc..."}, {"name": "Pivot Tables", "evidence": "3+ years of Excel (including VBA, pivot tables, array functions, power pivots, etc.) and data visualization tools suc..."}, {"name": "Array Functions", "evidence": "3+ years of Excel (including VBA, pivot tables, array functions, power pivots, etc.) and data visualization tools suc..."}, {"name": "Power Pivots", "evidence": "3+ years of Excel (including VBA, pivot tables, array functions, power pivots, etc.) and data visualization tools suc..."}, {"name": "Data Visualization Tools", "evidence": "You know and love working with business intelligence tools (excel, visualization tools, and SQL)"}, {"name": "Tableau", "evidence": "data visualization tools such as Tableau experience"}, {"name": "SQL", "evidence": "You know and love working with business intelligence tools (excel, visualization tools, and SQL)"}], "skills": ["Excel", "VBA", "Pivot Tables", "Array Functions", "Power Pivots", "Data Visualization Tools", "Tableau", "SQL"]}, {"title": "BVT Analyst_03/21/2026", "company": "WFNQASD5", "salary": "面议", "location": "Anchorage", "experience": "不限", "education": "本科及以上", "description": "**About the Role:**\n\nThe BVT Analyst plays a crucial role in analyzing and interpreting data related to business value transformation initiatives. This position is responsible for identifying trends, generating insights, and providing actionable recommendations to enhance operational efficiency and drive strategic decision-making. The analyst will collaborate with cross-functional teams to ensure that data-driven strategies align with organizational goals. By leveraging analytical tools and methodologies, the BVT Analyst will contribute to the continuous improvement of processes and performance metrics. Ultimately, this role aims to support the organization in achieving its business transformation objectives through informed analysis and strategic insights.\n\n**Minimum Qualifications:**\n\n* Bachelor''s degree in Business Administration, Data Analytics, or a related field.\n* Proven experience in data analysis and reporting, preferably in a business transformation context.\n* Strong proficiency in data analysis tools such as Excel, SQL, or similar software.\n\n**Preferred Qualifications:**\n\n* Master''s degree in a relevant field.\n* Experience with business intelligence tools like Tableau or Power BI.\n* Familiarity with project management methodologies and frameworks.", "requirements": "具备数据分析和报告经验，熟悉Excel、SQL等工具，有Tableau或Power BI经验者优先，熟悉项目管理方法论。", "source": "Indeed", "source_warning": "部分数据源抓取失败：linkedin: 抓取超时，已跳过；部分搜索词抓取失败：大数据分析: linkedin: 抓取超时，已跳过", "search_keyword": "Data Analyst", "relevance_score": 24, "relevance_reasons": ["标题部分命中: 大数据分析 / data analyst / big data analyst / data science / analytics specialist / data insights", "描述命中: data", "标题命中: analyst", "描述命中: analyst", "描述命中: analytics", "描述命中: insights"], "market_country": "美国", "skill_evidence": [{"name": "Data Analysis", "evidence": "Proven experience in data analysis and reporting"}, {"name": "Data Analysis Tools", "evidence": "Strong proficiency in data analysis tools such as Excel, SQL, or similar software"}, {"name": "Business Intelligence Tools", "evidence": "Experience with business intelligence tools like Tableau or Power BI"}, {"name": "Project Management Methodologies And Frameworks", "evidence": "Familiarity with project management methodologies and frameworks"}], "skills": ["Data Analysis", "Data Analysis Tools", "Business Intelligence Tools", "Project Management Methodologies And Frameworks"]}, {"title": "Senior Tax Analyst - Tax Operations", "company": "Amazon.com", "salary": "面议", "location": "Seattle", "experience": "不限", "education": "本科及以上", "description": "**DESCRIPTION**\n---------------\n\nIf you are interested in this position, please apply on Twitch''s Career site https://www.twitch.tv/jobs/en/  \n  \nAbout Us:  \n  \nTwitch is the world’s biggest live streaming service, with global communities built around gaming, entertainment, music, sports, cooking, and more. It is where thousands of communities come together for whatever, every day.  \n  \nWe’re about community, inside and out. You’ll find coworkers who are eager to team up, collaborate, and smash (or elegantly solve) problems together. We’re on a quest to empower live communities, so if this sounds good to you, see what we’re up to on LinkedIn and X, and discover the projects we’re solving on our Blog. Be sure to explore our Interviewing Guide to learn how to ace our interview process.  \n  \nTwitch Tax is looking for an experienced Senior Tax Analyst to be part of and contribute to our dynamic business. The Tax Senior will be an important contributor to the Tax Team and will help manage our Vertex instance, perform data analysis, compile data for global information reporting and/or tax compliance, support AI and other automation efforts, and contribute to our overall tax compliance and operational excellence. You will report to the Tax Director that leads the tax operations and tax compliance teams. As Twitch continues to grow its live streaming platform with our amazing social community, we are looking for a candidate with project management experience who will support our business and community through deployment of their technical tax knowledge and skills, and collaboration with cross -functional teams.\n  \n  \nYou can work in Seattle, WA or San Francisco, CA.  \n  \nYou Will  \n  \n\n* Partner with internal business partners on the collection, preparation, and submission of global information reporting forms\n* Assist in the maintenance, operation, and configuration of Vertex for Twitch\n* Support continuing efforts to incorporate AI and other scalable automation into existing tax compliance and reporting processes\n* Partner with Tax Team members on complex data driven projects\n* Assist with other system implementation projects and New Product Initiatives\n* Assist in the preparation of Forms 1099 and 1042S\n* Prepare and analyze monthly reconciliation of transaction upload reports to revenue reports, and reconciliation of indirect tax accounts for financial reporting\n* Partner with the Tax Team to respond to tax inquiries from customers, vendors, and internal departments\n* Partner with internal business partners on the collection, preparation, and submission of indirect tax, DST, SALT, and other gross receipts or transactional tax compliance as requested\n* Help with other ad hoc tax compliance, operations and/or planning projects as requested\n\n  \nPerks  \n\n* Medical, Dental, Vision & Disability Insurance\n* 401(k)\n* Maternity & Parental Leave\n* Flexible PTO\n* Amazon Employee Discount\n\n**BASIC QUALIFICATIONS**\n------------------------\n\n* Bachelor''s degree in accounting, finance, business or related field\n* Experience in an ERP environment (SAP and/or Oracle)\n* 4+ years of experience in tax (Big 4 or Tech Industry)\n* Significant experience in Vertex (including rule mapping, transaction testing, MDU/SR updates, and systems integration of Vertex)\n* Proficiency in Alteryx\n* Proficiency with productivity tools (Microsoft Suite, Google Workspace)\n* Proficiency with tax research tools (CCH, RIA, and BNA)\n\n**PREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS**\n----------------------------\n\n* CPA or MS in Tax\n* Experience with large data set analysis and summarization\n\n  \nTwitch is an equal opportunity employer and does not discriminate on the basis of protected veteran status, disability, or other legally protected status.  \n  \nLos Angeles County applicants: Job duties for this position include: work safely and cooperatively with other employees, supervisors, and staff; adhere to standards of excellence despite stressful conditions; communicate effectively and respectfully with employees, supervisors, and staff to ensure exceptional customer service; and follow all federal, state, and local laws and Company policies. Criminal history may have a direct, adverse, and negative relationship with some of the material job duties of this position. These include the duties and responsibilities listed above, as well as the abilities to adhere to company policies, exercise sound judgment, effectively manage stress and work safely and respectfully with others, exhibit trustworthiness and professionalism, and safeguard business operations and the Company’s reputation. Pursuant to the Los Angeles County Fair Chance Ordinance, we will consider for employment qualified applicants with arrest and conviction records.  \n  \nPursuant to the San Francisco Fair Chance Ordinance, we will consider for employment qualified applicants with arrest and conviction records.  \n  \nOur inclusive culture empowers Amazonians to deliver the best results for our customers. If you have a disability and need a workplace accommodation or adjustment during the application and hiring process, including support for the interview or onboarding process, please visit https://amazon.jobs/content/en/how-we-hire/accommodations for more information. If the country/region you’re applying in isn’t listed, please contact your Recruiting Partner.\n\nThe base salary range for this position is listed below. Your Amazon package will include sign-on payments and restricted stock units (RSUs). Final compensation will be determined based on factors including experience, qualifications, and location. Amazon also offers comprehensive benefits including health insurance (medical, dental, vision, prescription, Basic Life & AD&D insurance and option for Supplemental life plans, EAP, Mental Health Support, Medical Advice Line, Flexible Spending Accounts, Adoption and Surrogacy Reimbursement coverage), 401(k) matching, paid time off, and parental leave. Learn more about our benefits at https://amazon.jobs/en/benefits.\n\n  \nUSA, CA, SAN FRANCISCO - 72,600.00 - 123,500.00 USD annually  \nUSA, CA, San Francisco - 72,600.00 - 123,500.00 USD annually  \nUSA, WA, SEATTLE - 82,700.00 - 112,300.00 USD annually  \nUSA, WA, Seattle - 82,700.00 - 112,300.00 USD annually", "requirements": "具备4年以上税务经验，熟悉Vertex系统及税务研究工具；熟练使用Alteryx、Microsoft Suite和Google Workspace；需具备ERP环境（如SAP或Oracle）经验。", "source": "Indeed", "source_warning": "部分数据源抓取失败：linkedin: 抓取超时，已跳过；部分搜索词抓取失败：大数据分析: linkedin: 抓取超时，已跳过", "search_keyword": "Big Data Analyst", "relevance_score": 21, "relevance_reasons": ["标题部分命中: 大数据分析 / data analyst / big data analyst / data science / analytics specialist / data insights", "描述命中: data", "标题命中: analyst", "描述命中: analyst", "描述命中: big"], "market_country": "美国", "skill_evidence": [{"name": "Vertex", "evidence": "Assist in the maintenance, operation, and configuration of Vertex for Twitch"}, {"name": "Alteryx", "evidence": "Proficiency in Alteryx"}, {"name": "ERP environment (SAP and/or Oracle)", "evidence": "Experience in an ERP environment (SAP and/or Oracle)"}, {"name": "tax research tools (CCH, RIA, and BNA)", "evidence": "Proficiency with tax research tools (CCH, RIA, and BNA)"}, {"name": "Microsoft Suite", "evidence": "Proficiency with productivity tools (Microsoft Suite, Google Workspace)"}, {"name": "Google Workspace", "evidence": "Proficiency with productivity tools (Microsoft Suite, Google Workspace)"}], "skills": ["Vertex", "Alteryx", "ERP environment (SAP and/or Oracle)", "tax research tools (CCH, RIA, and BNA)", "Microsoft Suite", "Google Workspace"]}, {"title": "数据分析/数据挖掘实习生（机器学习方向）", "company": "Philips", "salary": "面议", "location": "Shanghai", "experience": "不限", "education": "本科及以上", "description": "Job Title\n  \n  \n数据分析/数据挖掘实习生（机器学习方向）\n  \n  \n**Job Description**\nJob Description\n  \n  \n岗位职责：\n  \n  \n\n* 数据处理： 使用SQL进行数据提取、清洗及预处理。\n* 分析挖掘： 基于业务需求，运用Python进行数据分析、特征工程及机器学习建模（如回归、聚类等）。\n* 工具应用： 利用BI工具（PowerBI）制作可视化报表；结合AI工具提升数据分析与编程效率。\n\n任职要求：\n  \n  \n\n* 学历专业： 本科及以上在读，统计学、计算机、数学、数据科学等相关专业。\n* Hard Skill：\n* SQL：能熟练编写SQL（包括多表连接、聚合、窗口函数）\n* Python： 基础扎实。熟悉Pandas/NumPy进行数据清洗与预处理；\n* AI/ML基础：理解常见机器学习算法原理，有项目或竞赛经历者优先。\n* 加分项：熟悉PowerBI；会使用AI工具辅助编程\n* Soft Skill： 逻辑清晰，自驱力强，对AI技术有好奇心。\n\n实习时间：每周至少三天on-site", "requirements": "熟练编写SQL，基础扎实的Python技能，熟悉Pandas/NumPy进行数据清洗与预处理，理解常见机器学习算法原理，有项目或竞赛经历者优先。", "source": "Linkedin", "search_keyword": "数据分析师", "relevance_score": 29, "relevance_reasons": ["标题部分命中: 大数据分析 / 数据分析师 / 大数据工程师 / 数据分析 / 数据挖掘 / 数据处理", "标题命中: 数据分析", "描述命中: 数据分析", "标题命中: 数据挖掘", "描述命中: 数据挖掘", "描述命中: 数据处理"], "market_country": "中国", "skill_evidence": [{"name": "SQL", "evidence": "使用SQL进行数据提取、清洗及预处理"}, {"name": "Python", "evidence": "运用Python进行数据分析、特征工程及机器学习建模（如回归、聚类等）"}, {"name": "机器学习算法", "evidence": "理解常见机器学习算法原理，有项目或竞赛经历者优先"}], "skills": ["SQL", "Python", "机器学习算法"]}, {"title": "淘天集团-高级数据分析师-AI产品", "company": "Alibaba", "salary": "面议", "location": "C02", "experience": "1-3年", "education": "硕士及以上", "description": "**基础信息**\n\n所属部门:\n\n淘天集团\n\n学历:\n\n硕士\n\n工作年限:\n\n1 年\n\n**职位描述**\n\n1、负责电商用户AI产品的商业分析，包括全链路数据指标体系梳理和搭建、数据产品建设和策略支持；\n2、负责AI产品的数据体系的建设，包括数据指标的设计，数据清晰和数据埋点方案的设计，以及和算法，技术以及数仓的协同，推动AI产品的数据体系建设。\n3、负责AI产品的实验方案设计和优化，结合AB实验、归因分析等方法量化产品以及大模型的效果，为用户侧AI产品决策提供数据洞察与可落地的产品解决方案；\n4、基于对业务理解，熟练运用多种分析手段和方法（如海量数据分析和挖掘手段、资料收集&分析、行业研究、竞争分析等），探索商业模式，发现商业机会，诊断业务问题、评估运营效果等，在战略、战术上提供决策支持和参考；\n5、通过对业务数据的挖掘，对专项问题、指定方向的重点研究与分析，能书写并输出专项的商业分析报告。\n\n**职位要求**\n\n1、 清晰的分析逻辑以及良好的业务洞察能力，能快速发现问题、拆解问题并定位到影响业务的关键点；\n2、 数据处理能力强，可使用多种方式提取数据并进行分析，熟练掌握hive、SQL、excel等相关数据提取工具；\n3、 良好的沟通能力和团队协作能力，能够有效地和业务方，数据技术团队沟通交流，具有跨团队的推进项目的能力，并且能够以分析师的视角给业务提供建议；\n4、 具备数据运营与产品运营能力，针对业务问题，可以透过实验设计，并制定有效解决方案及衡量方法；\n5、 良好的数据敏感度,能从海量数据提炼核心结果，有丰富的数据分析、挖掘、清洗和建模经验，能独立编写商业数据分析报告；\n6、 有AI产品分析相关经验，了解C端AI产品、AIGC内容生成、大模型评估相关的优先。", "requirements": "具备数据运营与产品运营能力，能独立编写商业数据分析报告；有AI产品分析相关经验，了解C端AI产品、AIGC内容生成、大模型评估相关的优先。", "source": "Indeed", "search_keyword": "数据分析师", "relevance_score": 26, "relevance_reasons": ["标题部分命中: 大数据分析 / 数据分析师 / 大数据工程师 / 数据分析 / 数据挖掘 / 数据处理", "标题命中: 数据分析师", "标题命中: 数据分析", "描述命中: 数据分析", "描述命中: 数据处理"], "market_country": "中国", "skill_evidence": [{"name": "数据指标体系梳理和搭建", "evidence": "负责电商用户AI产品的商业分析，包括全链路数据指标体系梳理和搭建、数据产品建设和策略支持"}, {"name": "数据产品建设", "evidence": "负责电商用户AI产品的商业分析，包括全链路数据指标体系梳理和搭建、数据产品建设和策略支持"}, {"name": "数据埋点方案设计", "evidence": "数据清晰和数据埋点方案的设计"}, {"name": "AB实验", "evidence": "实验方案设计和优化，结合AB实验、归因分析等方法量化产品以及大模型的效果"}, {"name": "归因分析", "evidence": "实验方案设计和优化，结合AB实验、归因分析等方法量化产品以及大模型的效果"}, {"name": "海量数据分析和挖掘手段", "evidence": "基于对业务理解，熟练运用多种分析手段和方法（如海量数据分析和挖掘手段、资料收集&分析、行业研究、竞争分析等）"}, {"name": "数据提取工具", "evidence": "数据处理能力强，可使用多种方式提取数据并进行分析，熟练掌握hive、SQL、excel等相关数据提取工具"}, {"name": "SQL", "evidence": "数据处理能力强，可使用多种方式提取数据并进行分析，熟练掌握hive、SQL、excel等相关数据提取工具"}, {"name": "Hive", "evidence": "数据处理能力强，可使用多种方式提取数据并进行分析，熟练掌握hive、SQL、excel等相关数据提取工具"}, {"name": "数据分析报告编写", "evidence": "能书写并输出专项的商业分析报告"}], "skills": ["数据指标体系梳理和搭建", "数据产品建设", "数据埋点方案设计", "AB实验", "归因分析", "海量数据分析和挖掘手段", "数据提取工具", "SQL", "Hive", "数据分析报告编写"]}, {"title": "Data Analyst Intern - Shanghai 数据分析师 (实习) - 上海", "company": "flowith", "salary": "面议", "location": "Shanghai", "experience": "不限", "education": "不限", "description": "你是连接\"用户行为\"与\"产品决策\"的翻译官。在这个岗位上，数据不是冷冰冰的数字，而是鲜活的用户故事。你需要深入产品运营的核心，通过分析用户在 Flowith中的行为路径，发现提升各种数据的关键线索。\n  \n  \n**工作内容：**\n用户旅程诊断： 深入分析用户的全链路数据，识别流失节点，为产品运营策略调整提供直接依据。\n  \n  \n\n* 增长实验复盘： 协助设计并评估 A/B Test 效果，用数据验证运营动作的有效性，驱动核心指标增长。\n* 核心指标监控： 搭建并维护产品运营看板，实时追踪 DAU、功能渗透率、用户生命周期价值等关键指标，及时预警异常。\n* 定性与定量结合： 结合 Customer Service 收集的用户反馈，利用数据验证用户痛点的普遍性，辅助产品确定需求优先级。\n* 内部 Agent 共建： 参与搭建内部使用的 market agent，让非技术团队也能通过自然语言获取分析产品数据。\n\n**Requirements**\n\n* 数据驱动运营思维： 不仅会跑数，更懂业务。能提出\"数据背后代表了用户什么心理/遭遇了什么困难\"的假设。\n* 硬核分析能力： 熟练掌握 PostgreSQL，能独立编写复杂查询（多表 JOIN、窗口函数、CTE），进行用户分群、漏斗分析、留存计算。\n* 逻辑与沟通： 能够将复杂的数据分析结果转化为可视化的图表和通俗易懂的运营建议（Actionable Insights）。\n* 拥抱新技术： 对 AI 充满热情，渴望探索如何用 Agent 技术革新传统的数据分析流程。\n* 加分项： 有互联网产品运营、用户增长（User Growth）、数据分析实习经验，或统计学/计算机相关背景，或有软件开发经验。\n\n**Benefits**\n\n* Workspace, Culture & Lifestyle\n\n+ Awesome Teammates: Work alongside a kind, creative, and hardworking crew of occasional \"geeks\" and visionaries\n+ Building the AGI Future: Participate in the in-house development of rapidly evolving AI agents and explore the future of AGI interactive interfaces\n+ Cool Offices in SH & SF: Enjoy our ultra-open workspaces with the ultimate freedom to seamlessly switch between our Shanghai and San Francisco locations\n+ Pet-Friendly Workplace: Bring your furry friends to work! Come play with our resident Orange Tabby and Golden Retriever Mix, or bring your own pets to hang out\n+ Island Hackathons: Join our annual internal hackathons, where we select a new city or country each year for innovative coding sessions and team bonding\n+ Free AI Tools & Tech Gear